text:
Abhyuday Bhai jab pehli baar facebook pai baat chalu hui thi uss waqt kabhi ni socha tha itna lamba safar sath mai chalenge. Tum ni hote to kitni jagah na jane kitni baar akele marwa chuka hota. Abhi bhi yaad hai kaise sath mai dono CS201 ki quiz se leke TA ki attendace se leke CS330 mai marwaye hai. Mera class ni jana and tera maje lena ki aj Quiz hogya(jo kafi time sach tha), phir raat ko jante hue ki canteen ni aega...tera aana puchne and chalne k liye kehna was all the quality that I assume only one of the best friends can do for someone. Mere nazar mai koi mujhse puche to bhai you are like Dhoni to me(as I always said to you), Teri Kismat ki hawa kabhi naram garam hote hue dheka hai maine and seeing you not loosing hope till end (2nd year k summer intern k liye apply jab kr rhe the khaas krke) and last ball mai 6 marna, tumse sikha hai maine. 

Wo Diwali mai harr baar Mall jana and McD mai khana and raat mai Munna bhai dhekna are few of the Gems memories of IITK(Bhai McD mai kha k bhi KFC mai ni khane ka kabhi afsos ni hua tere sath). Kya pata kitni baar tumne maari hai aur hum dono kitna argue and ladai kiye ho(yaad hai C411 ki apni ladai), but You always stood together and defended, kitna baar mere fucked up life se bachaya hai tumne can't be counted. Perfect combination of chapuness and harami panti ho tum but bhai dil k sabse saaf insaan ho. Jab mera kuch problem chal rha tha tum raat bhar sath mai jaga Assignment k liye and harr assignment mai support kiya, tere support k bina mai waqqt pai graduate tak ni hota(ML aur OS k assignment se leke personal life advice tak sath tha tum). Teri advice are like orders for me as I know they are coming out of you with multitude of SWOT analysis XD ,You were one of the friend like elder brother to me on whom I could have relied on blindly in the worst of my times(Although kabhi kabhi ullu bhi bana dete the to thora filter krna parta tha XD). 

One thing that I'm sure of is kitno se kitna din connected rahun, you are among few of the person jisse mai I know definitely connected rhunga, and you will be my first roll on calling someone whenever I land in Delhi. Baki formality to hogyi bhai aur kitni batein likhun tere sath to mera college ka significant percent beeta hai tereko pata hi hai...aja call pai baat krte hai aage ;P.
author: Deepesh Kumar Lall

text:
How "abey tum mereko janta ni hai be"(Hard tone) to "Bhai" in these 4 years changed was a miracle. Bhai you are one the most talented person jisse hardwork and consistency ki definition seekhi hai maine. You are living ideal for me and I see you not as a friend but as BROTHER and bahot gadar chapoge aage I know it.

 Baki lamba para likhenge ni I know aage bahot baatein hongi and Bahot jagah help aur krna parega tujhe mereko but bhai tum ni hota to bahot kuch ni sikhta mai. Wo CS202 ki assignment yaad hai, Pura tumne bna diya tha XD and maine jab pehli baar tera code dheka meri to usme hi phatt gyi thi. Although tumne mera aur bhi bahot sara assignmnent banaya hai ML se leke CS251 tk and bahot kuch seekhne mila hai tumse and you always taught and helped me like a family. Memories from `first year mai laptop tere room se leke bhaag jana, Teri jo phati thi bhai maza agya tha` to `watching dictator together and high ho k flat hojana` are few of the things jo iss memoir mai likhna possible ni. Jald hi milte hai Ranchi aaye to aur kuch logo se milna hai (IFYWIM) ;P
author: Deepesh Kumar Lall

text:
Nipun Bhai Tere sath itni saari dosti ki wo yaadein juri hai ki gina mushkil hai. Zakir khan kehta hai na wo dost jo dil tutne pai kehte hai chal do peg lagate hai -- wo tu hai mere liye bas difference ye hai ki peg ka saman sb tu lata tha. Midsem k late night se early morning tk jagne wala partner tha bhai tum, and wo late night thakan mai sutta ki alg alg brand se introduce krwana and library k neeche rm side tk jaake phukna and uske baad phir tute dil ki dastan se ... ek ladki ko dheka to aesa laga tak ka safar mai sath nibhaya hai tune. Jab bhi sutta, hukka ya daru ki jaroort parti thi you were my first response in last 4 years(saale bigar diye the tum mereko, shukraguzar hai tere XD). Wo sath mai Shivam ka lena XD aur Tera drams wali crush ka story sunne mai kya maza ata tha bhai. Although meri suggestions tujhe uss waqt mushkil lagti thi but aaj tu agree krega!

I still remember the first time 2nd year mai jab mai tujhe gym mai bata rha tha ye karo and wo uthao (;P)se, how it changed to you teaching me "Ohh behen k la*de roj subh chana khaunga tu bhi khya kr aur subh gym chal mere sath". Aur Kehte na bhai nashe mai kahi hui baat dil ki hoti hai....maine jitne nashe kiye tere sath itna samjh gya tu dil ka bahot saaf banda hai. Bandi ko teri dhek ke although bahot buri wali phatt ti hai and teri kismat kharab hai but uske peeche bhi ek bahot shareef bhola wajah rheta hai. Although marks dhek k jo teri phatt ti hai uspe ni comment krunga mai ;P(Just kidding). Tere se jo mangu wo apna sa lagta tha bhai chaye wo late night sutta ka naya brand ho ya teri cycle ;P itna apna ki mai lautana hi bhul jata ;P. Aur Library mai tera harr midsem kehna ki Iss baar Drams club chordunga se endsem tk drams club mai wapas ghus jana was something that mere hote college mai to ni hi ho paya. Bhai khane k mamle mai to dono ka taste kitna match kiya hai! like exam k waqt late night aake jo sath mai daba k kahte the dono canteen mai and wo sath mai Kathi role and wazwan k paas chicken khana jab koi aur ni chalte the and sath mai pehli baar hukka marna ;P. Aese kitni yaadein hai bhai jo iss memoir mai likh k ni keh paunga but You are one the friends jo family sa feel krwayi campus mai.

I know bhai aage khoob chapoge and jaldi graduate ho phir milte hai, iss baar uss level wali party hogi jaisa mai tere room aya tha hali mai subh aur tu utha k mereko room legya tha XD. Insta pai to meme share krte hi hai aja uspe :D.

text:
Parth Bhai tere liye bhale bahot SAE wale senior ho, mere liye aap hi SAE wale senior the jinhone Car ka engine ka working se leke SAE k workshop tk mai entry karwayi thi. 1st year mai jab pehli baar mile the tumse dhek ke laga tha sabse bhole ho but Jab pehli baar P@rth@***i wala scam hua tb samjha ni ye sabse tedhi cheej hai. But ussi year bhai tumne mera NSS mai mere badle jaake report submit krke ye bhi sabit krdiya tha ki tum devmanus ho(Iski kitni bhi treat dedun I agree wo kum hi hai). 

Tumhare advices although humesa sabse chalu rhe hai but wo sbse effective bhi the. And wo raat mai jab tum canteen mai apne jee waale room mate ka jaise maare the...literally meri phatt gyi thi bhai uss waqqt laga the sakshat Sardar khan jaise kehta hai ki keh k lunga wala scene chal rha tha. Harr break k baad bhai tum 10 tarah ki khane ki cheej laate the, never thought tum iss baar jaoge to wapas jaldi mulakat ni ho paegi, Koi dikat ni milenge wapas tb pizza waise hi mangwaya jaega sath mai. 

Sabse sahi wali memories wo thi jisme tumne chipkali ki maari thi, mujhe literally laga tha tu uska wahi asthi saja dega XD and harr summer cooler repair krdena hum log ka bahot mehnat bach jata tha bhai chapu to tum the bahot pehle se. And ofcousre Teri cycle to sabse best lagti thi mujhe In my opinion one of the reason Maine naya cycle ni liya was tumhari cycle kuch jyada hi achi thi ;P. GTA5 se leke Netflix tak ka jugad lagwate the bhai tum na jaane kitne sari cheejein torrent karwayi hai tumse XD. Corona kaal k baad milte hai bhai aur bakchodi pelenge.

text:
I remember we first met because of basketball, and also our roll nos were close so we were even in the same PE group bhai. Kafi entertaining rehta tha wo time because of you and your always ready witty puns and jokes. 

But things changed jab ham dono ne Summer camp join kia, I mean they really changed man!!.  For me personally it was one of the best time of my stay at IITK. Jannat tha bhai. And it was all because you were there, Bhut shi bonding kri hai bhai hmne us 1 mahine me. Subh uthate the ek dusre ko jse tese, Pura din pel ke basketball khelna subh or raat or bs bch me khana or wpis sona. In sab ke bch jo hamne bakchodiyan ki hai, will never forgot them. Sbse jyada tuning/sync court pe bhi tujhse bethti thi, cheers to both us rebounders. Bhut shi time tha yr wo, Truly it was more like a dream when I think of it now, and you have been a major part of it. Also yaad hoga Reading room me Ac ke chakkar me pde rhte the :P hall 2 ke. 

Apart from this apne paths kbhi na kbhi cross hote hi rhe kbhi arts ka course to kbhi kuch, and Iâ€™m so glad they did, infact last ke 1 months bhi hmko khelne ko mila, relive krne ko mila whi time phle wla, im so happy that happened. 

I canâ€™t thank you enough for being a part of my life at IITK, I will always cherish the time Iâ€™ve spent with you man! and I will always look forward to have more of it. You have such a warm and happy personality bro, also youâ€™re an amazing artist . I cant afford to lose gems like you <3 . Youâ€™ll do wonders in life, Stay in touch and Take care. 

PS â€“ Cheers to our 100 streak on snapchat <3 wpis ayega to fir bnaenge and  For every shot we missed  "Lakri ka board hota to jati !!!" :P

text:
Hello Pal! Kaisa hai bro? 
Having you in the same college was probably the best thing that happened to me in these four years. Our bond goes back to school when you joined it in 2012. 10th tk mai terko khaas nhi jaanta tha but 11th se tumne reputation bna hi li thi A section ke sbse chaapu launde waali ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚. Phr 12th mai thodi baat hoti rehti thi ki haa yar IIT jaana hai dono ne. Mujhe yaad hai 12th mai, Sunday breakfast ke baad kabhi kabhi tu Singh house ke saamne aaya krta tha aur vaha hum yehi discuss krte the ki yar bs IIT hojaae. 
When we passed out from school, I never thought that weâ€™d still get the chance to see each other for at least the next five years. We got so lucky. 
Fortunately, we got the same batch in Resonance and so I had a friend in RJ1. Kota mai times kaafi hard the yar mentally but having you by my side in classes really helped me get through them. Hum class mai aksar saath baithte the and it was so much fun, pata nhi 1.5 1.5 ghante ke lectures kaise jhele humne bhaiğŸ˜…ğŸ˜…ğŸ˜… Kher jaise bhi jhele, they were worth it. Mujhe abhi bhi yaad aata hai kaise hum 15 min break hota tha jo classes ke beech, usme 5th floor pe jaake patties khaya krte the, Allen kee sheets pe ğŸ˜‚. Kota mai mai tere room bhi aksar aaya karta tha, specially Diwali ke baad se, aur bhut accha lagta tha yar vaha aake. Hum sab jb bahar khana khaane jaate the, vo tea breaks and bahar se paneer laake room pe khaana. Tumhare heater mai roti pe ghee lagake paratha bnana. It was all so much fun. Kabhi kabhi jb Kota yaad aata hai, aisa lagta hai vo din bhut mst the (aisa us time kabhi socha nhi tha ki ye din bhi yaad aaenge ğŸ˜‚). Pr baat yehi hai ki vo din islie yaad aate hai kyunki bhai humne saath mai itne maje jo kie. 
Phr bhagwaan ki dua se hum IITK aagye, jo ki bhut hi mst hua yar. Tune mujhe starting ke  days mai cycle road pe chalana sikhaya tha ğŸ˜‚, aaj ke din ye bhut hi simple sound krra hai mujhe but then it was a big deal for me. Hum un 2 3 din campus ke round maara krte the and it was so much fun. Tu mujhe kehta rehta tha, â€œ Peeche waala break maara kar, aage waale break se phisal skte haiâ€. Million dollar advice hai bhai ye, iss advice ki vajah se hi mai 4 saal IITK mai salamati se cycle chalata raha, including barsaat mai bhi. 
First year kaafi sahi nikla yar, hum class mai saath baith paate the, courses bhi same the aur kaafi accha lagta tha. Merko yaad hai ek baar August mai bhut baarish hui thi, roads pe paani bhara hua tha and mera chashma toot gya tha, to tu mere saath Kanpur city aaya tha chashma banwaane. Thankyou so much for that bro. Mujhe pata tha kit ere alawa koi nhi hai jo mere saath aaega and islie maine bs tujhe call kia. 
Phr hume ek din OAT mai Shekhar bsb mil gye and tu Hockey mai chala gaya. Bhai I am so happy that you found hockey, vaha tujhe bhut naye bande mile and you had the chance to grow so much with them. You found a family there and got a reason to work hard, stay fit and you found a purpose overall. Haa tu humesha khush nhi tha hockey mai, kabhi kabhi bhut frustrate ho jaata tha politics se aur Inter-IIT jaane ki team list se, but overall kaafi accha raha tere lie. Khaali room pe baithke dimaag kharab hi hota hai, ye tune jo 1 sem hockey miss kia us time dekh hi lia hoga. I personally think hockey helped you build a great personality. Tu pehle kaafi shy tha, ab sbse easily baat kr leta hai and indirectly hockey brought you many opportunities like working in Council and Udhgosh. 
2nd and 3rd year mai kaafi mulakaat hui and kabhi kabhi bahar party pe bhi jaaya krte the hum Shekhar bsb ke saath. Kaafi maja aata tha. Mai kbhi kbhi tere room pe aa jaata tha, aur kbhi kbhi hum tere wing ki chatt pe baith jaate the. Yar mst memories hai ye, humaari baatein bhut masaledaar rhi hai humesha ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ and mujhe yaad aaengi mujhe. Koi nhi ab phone pe baat krenge jb tk mil nhi paaenge. 
Kota and IITK mai tu mera support system tha bro. Jab bhi mera dimaag kharab hota tha from the pressure, stress ya koi aur baat hoti thi, mai tujhi ko sbse pehle batata tha and you were always there for me and never used to turn me away. You always listened to me patiently before giving me any advice. Thankyou so much for that bro!
You have worked very hard in life, Anshuman. Even Ghorakhal aane se pehle se hi tu bhut mehnat krta aara hai. Jo tu 3rd class mai Olympiad mai rank laaya tha use bhi pehle se. And you have also achieved so much in life because of that and the many sacrifices you have made along the way. At times, life will get tougher bro, specially with the UPSC preparation, but tu himmat mt haarna bhai. Kuch bhi ho jaae lage rehna. Mai tere alaawa aur kisiko nhi jaanta jo itna deserve krta hai UPSC nikaalna. And I know you will work very very hard for it. I believe in you with all my heart. Mujhe pata hai a few years down the line you will make it. It will be so great to see you succeed again and again in life. So keep going. Jaada kabhi stress ho to I am only one call away bhai. Vaise bhi itni koi dikkat nhi hai, mai call krta rahunga tujhe time to time. 
Wishing you an awful lot of success, fulfilment and prosperity in life bro. Stay healthy and happy forever. Aur haa, keep smiling bhai. Terpe smiling face hi jachta hai. 
Keep in touch bro. (Goobye nhi kehra kyunki hum humesha milte rahenge.)

text:
Dipak Frickinâ€™ Mahajan!!! Bro, how are you doing? 
It was worthwhile to have you, Aditya and Shubham in the adjacent room in the freshman year. The memories that we made in that short time itself are priceless. I remember that time when a bunch of 3rd years from 2-Bot caught us so happy that they couldnâ€™t bear it and took us to the lawn and asked me to sing and you to dance to it. I never told you, but I was terrified that night and the only reason I felt safe was that you were there with me and I thought, I have my friend by my side and whatever happens, weâ€™ll get through this together. Contrary to our apprehension, the night took a rather hilarious turn, and we got an anecdote to laugh our asses off for the rest of our lives. I remember those numerous nights, when you, Shubham and I used to get together and mess with anyone we could possibly find in the wing (mostly, Tamonud â€“ Sorry Tamonud!) and used to make so much noise that Aditya could never sleep. And I remember the night before the PHY103 midsem when we pulled a night out in CC and you helped me get through all the tutorials and notes so that I could pass the next day. And I did. 

I remember the few but glorious trips that we took to BBQ or malls to watch a movie. Also, the time you and Tamonud treated the whole wing there (We love you for it!). I remember the time we watched Avengers: Infinity War (me, you, Aditya and Tamonud) and had to walk kilometres afterwards to find a ride back to college (What a day it was!). 

I remember the times in the sophomore, junior and senior years when I called on you for advice and guidance and you never turned me away, and the times you watched out for me when I was crashing academically. I also remember the innumerable times you helped me find greater clarity about my life and the times you saw me through my various never-ending crises and ever-recurring crossroads. 
I thank you for every one of these times. Thank you for being by my side, thank you for taking the time, thank you for every one of your advice, thank you for all the fun times, thank you for everything. 

Lastly, may I add how breath-taking it was to have had the chance to watch you grow and become this fabulous individual that you have become. That stooped, awkward kid that walked uneasily through the gates of Hall 03 in July 2017, inconfident, is now this confident, mature and more-learned-than-ever leader that is walking out head held high with a blazing charisma, having touched and enriched hundreds of lives, including mine. The way that you have lived these four years, fully and joyfully, inspires me and will continue to inspire me throughout my life. It is an honour to know you and have you as my bhai. I was very lucky that our paths crossed and I, whole-heartedly and unconditionally, wish you the best in life. May you be a thousand times more successful than anyone who has ever lived, and may you rise to your full potential, because you are INFINITE my friend. You are a fricking star, so please be and stay that way forever.

Humaari sabse pehle baat hui thi jb hum freshers inferno mai Hall 3 ke lie basketball khele the saath. Aur uske baad to CPA mai milna hota rehta tha. 

Pr tumhe acche se jaanne ka mauka to Summer Camp mai hi mila aur hum kaafi acche dost bhi bn gye. Bhai summer camp mere in 4 saalo mai sbse best time tha and you were one of the reasons for it. Summer camp ka time yaad krta hu to aisa lagta hai jaise camp koi sapna tha, kyunki hum us time bs khate, khelte aur soya krte the. Court se thakkr aate the aur jb so nhi rahe hote the to hasi majak chalta rehta tha. Vo time bhut mst tha yar aur jo humaari team thi vo bhi sb mst bnde the. 2nd year ke Udhgosh se maine basketball khelna chor dia tha but dost to humesha hi rahenge. 

Uske baad bhi kaafi baar mulakaat aur baatein hoti rahi. 2nd year mai saath SG bhi rahe aur hall mai kbhi kbhi mess ya quad mai milte rehte the. Ek shaam quad mai 3 bot ke saamne baithke humne dher saari baatein bhi ki thi sur apni problems bhi share ki thi ek doosre se. OAT mai saath milkar, basketball team ko humne birthday treat bhi krai thi. To mulakaate to bhut hui pr kaafi nhi ho paai kbhi pandemic ki vajah se, pr jitni bhi hui, uske lie mai bhut grateful hu bro. 

Tumne basketball 3rd year ke end tk continue rakha and actually you were the only one from our batch to do so. I have huge respect for you because of that. You were always deeply dedicated to everything you committed to, from studies to basketball. That's why I'm sure you'll do great in life and will rise to your maximum potential. 

Thank you for all the experiences we lived together bhai. It has been so much fun to know you. You are a genuinely good person. Also you are one of those very few people I've met, that think about life in long-term. Always take advantage of that. Terse baat krke humesha accha lagta tha because you used to listen so patiently and genuinely. I will miss you a lot brother. I wish you all the success in the world bhai. May you find your purpose and have a fulfilled and prosperous life. Stay healthy and happy. Take care bhai. I'll stay in touch. 

P.S. PhD aur research krne ka sapna kabhi mt chorna bro. Bhale hi due to pandemic, situation thodi tough hogyi hai but never give up on your dreams, ever.

text:
Harshu, mere bhai <3
Without a doubt, tere saath sabse jyada bakchodi ki hai maine pure IITK me!

What started off as 'CS202 me team up karega?' became what I am sure is lifelong friendship. For the longest time, tu mere liye woh 'go-to' person raha hai. Be it padhai, or treat, or just about anything, you'd be the first jo dimaag me aata tha, and hai.

Hab bhi jarurat ho, upar uthaane ke liye tu hamesha mere saath raha hai (so much so ki 252 me 'independently' kaam karke bhi same app bana diya tha :p). Tere saath baat karte time I don't feel the need to use a filter, kyuki pata hai tu meko samajh hi jaega.

And of course, teri maarne ka to alag hi maza hai - gande jokes, kharab angrezi, lack of sarcasm. Kabhi kabhi lagta ekdum innocent hai bc.

Teko thoda bhi idea nahi hai how much you matter to me. Bas ek hi request hai ab - reunions organize karwaate reh, you are the glue of our group. I am proud to call you bhai.
author: Durgesh Rajendra Agrawal

text:

author: Durgesh Rajendra Agrawal

text:
Bhai, 
kaafi samay tak teri image mere mann me 'introverted padhaku' wali thi - jo unconditionally help kar dega anytime I ask. Of course, 5th sem waale antics and trauma to hamesha yaad rahenge, especially vfork. And as much as we bonded over nakli hackathons, assignments, and computer sciency discussions, something felt ... distant.
Mai kaafi baar Snehal ko pucha, "How do I get him to open up?" 
And eventually, I found it - books and Harry Potter <3
What followed were many many heartwarming nerdy discussions that are super special because very few can appreciate how awesome they are. The only thing I regret is not being able to have these discussions in person.
Yeh bolne ka jarurat nahi how intelligent and hardworking you are. But one thing I love about you is your humility. Thank you for being in my 'inner circle.' Thank you for always pushing me to do better and be better. And thank you for changing my life.

text:
Hello Yashika!
Sabse pehle toh you are the best roommate and neighbour I ever had. You introduced me to the world's best alarm tune :P From the beginning, I always admired you for your friendly nature and motivated attitude. And above that, we had so much fun together in the first year. One of my best memories of college is that EDM in which we danced like crazy. And then we became roommates. And although our schedules didn't usually match up, the small chit-chat or gossip sessions were the best. I remember waking up to the smell of delicious soup in the middle of the night when you came after your dance practice. Also, thanks for taking me to the HC in the middle of the night when I had an ant in my ear (which I actually thought to be a bat in the beginning ._.). And next time se kisi achi movie ke saath year shuru karenge :)

From being neighbours to roommates to neighbours again, you were an actual constant in my college life.

I hope you have a beautiful life ahead with a lot less annoying alarm and a better sleep schedule :P Hope we meet again and dance it out again.

text:
CRINGE ALERT!!
It started with scaring other couples on the skywalk and ended with, NO, it never ended :). You can never imagine how much you meant to me at the time we met. You still have no idea how precious those late-night walks were, how beautiful the sun looked at 5 am with you, how you just understood what I meant, how you just knew what to say at every fucking time, how you always kept my priorities at top, how you never really complained about anything, how you made me laugh even if it wasnâ€™t necessary. I know everything you did required patience and dedication, I know it wasnâ€™t easy for you to get out of your comfort zone but there wasnâ€™t even one single time when you backed out. You are the most rational boyfriend one could expect. Even when we were fighting, you were there for me. Many of the things can not be written here but I know you'll always feel them while reading this. I do and always will appreciate those little things, our walks on "footpaths" both inside and outside campus, our first date in bazooka, sneaking through moti jheel barricades, the gatecrash in Kanpur, binging tv series, our spot(wink) and infinite other things. I know I can get too competitive and sometimes it can be difficult but you never uttered a word. I am extremely happy for us to have crossed many challenges that came in our relationship. It was as close to ideal as WE could get. We had our quirks and weirdness. I like having really conversations with you, I love sharing the "we could go to jail for this" humor with you. I love that you typed my pet name exactly 69 times in my memoir. I love a million things about you and I can fill pages but can not. You'll know them. I just want to say one thing, there may be a thousand ways in which a relationship MAY or may NOT go, but I know we'll choose what will work best for us. LOVE YOU MOTU (chubby guys cuddle better) ğŸ–¤

PS: Even if we decide to break up, I REALLY hope our friendship stays this magical. :)

text: Shut the fuck up. I'm so tired of being disrespected on this goddamn website. All I wanted to do was post my opinion. MY OPINION. But no, you little bastards think it's "hilarious" to mock those with good opinions. My opinion. while not absolute, is definitely worth the respect to formulate an ACTUAL FUCKING RESPONSE AND NOT JUST A SHORT MEME OF A REPLY. I've been on this site for 6 months: 6 MONTHS and I have never felt this wronged. It boils me up that I could spend so much time thinking and putting effort into things while you shits sit around (probably jerking off to cats or whatever gay shit you like) and make fun of the intellectuals of this world. I've bored you? Good for fucking you. Literally no one cares that your little brain is to underdeveloped and rotted to comprehend my idea...MY GREAT GREAT IDEA. I could sit here all day whining, but I won't. I'm NOT a whiner. I'm a realist and an intellectual. I know when to call it quits and to leave the babybrains to themselves. I'm done with this goddamn site and you goddamn immature children. I have lived my life up until this point having to deal with memesters and idiots like you. I know how you work. I know that you all think you're "epik trolls" but you're not. You think you baited me? NAH. I've never taken any bait. This is my 100% real opinion divorced from anger. I'm calm, I'm serene. I LAUGH when people imply I'm intellectually low enough to take bait. I always choose to reply just to spite you. I won. I've always won. Losing is not in my skillset. So you're probably gonna reply "lol epik trolled" or "u mad bro" but once you've done that you've shown me I've won. I've tricked the trickster and conquered memery. I live everyday growing stronger to fight you plebs and low level trolls who are probably 11 (baby, you gotta be 13 to use Leftbook). But whatever, I digress. It's just fucking annoying that I'm never taken serious on this site, goddamn.

Aur bhai u have the unique distinction of being the first in the group jiski bandi ho to bahut badhaiyan ğŸ˜.
Pandit yaar tere room me aake lagta tha ki organised way me kaise rehte hai , dekh ke inspiration milti thi lekin apne room tk jaate jaate sab gayab ho jaati thi aur phir tujhe mere room ka one hand rule to maalum hi tha, dustbin se lekar , extension tk sab ek haath ki doori pe. Baaki tu to kamre pe rehta kam hi tha , to phir mai tere bed pe hi fael ke dayal ke saath pubg khelta rehta tha. Bhai HSS me tu tha islie accha bhi lagta tha, shayd usi se first year me apni bonding achhi ho gyi thi, har din raat me 9-4 bc pel ke HSS ki practice karo aur phir baad me Gupchup khelo, bhai usme bhi avinash ki lene me bahut mazaa aata tha ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚.
Apan dono ka hi plan tha 2nd year me ki foreign research intern me chalenge, tune to surge ka form bhar dia tha as a step toward this aur mai bc form bharna hi bhool gaya, pubg khelta raha ğŸ˜›. Tujhe bhai mil bhi gyi foreign intern lekin ab chill hai corona hai hi itna chutiap bc. Baaki jahan abhi intern pe jaa rahe ho wahan chaapna mast ekdm.
Bhai tere li bhi kitni hai maine , be it tera breakfast me pel ke dosa dabana yaa mess me bday treat pe pastry khilana ğŸ˜‚, mazaa aata tha bhai, apan ki ek trip to ho gyi abhi kuch aur baaki hai wo to pakka karenge.
Jldi se bhai apni degree khatm kar , mote ki help kar dio economics me , job pakad aur phir apan saare bhai mast trip pe chalenge. ALL the best bhai, aise hi acche insaan aur dost bane raho.
author: Harshit  Rao

text:
chuddo saali randi maadarchod, bhn ki lodi, kutia; bhai this is how I mostly called you all our college life but Bhai let me tell you I shared the most unique bond in IITK with you. I harassed you, abused you, cursed you, have beaten you, stolen your food but bhai I also profoundly cared about you, I knew when you were tensed be it with intern or assignment submission or midsem/endsem but ig the photos captured by Naman just shows the former part ğŸ˜›ğŸ˜›. 
Bhai I had the most enjoying conversations/fight ğŸ˜ with you on such wide-ranging topics, one incident i remember is that we debated continuously for one complete hour and in the end had to stop because our throat dried up and we got thirsty ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚. Baaki to bhai we all know how berserk you used to go whenever some item of yours went missing ( except those headphones where u were totally calm ğŸ˜’ğŸ˜’). Also bhai thank you for being my constant companion in quizzing where sometimes we used to have total bloodbath and sometimes scored pretty high.
Placement times shows everyone who their real friends are and I can't thank you enough for all the help, you used to be there on zoom call for the whole time. I have sent you tons of questions from hacker rank and you used to try your best to help me understand them and find the solution to them. I even gave CAT because of you and u mofo chickened out in the end ğŸ”.
Your room were always next to mine and most of the time It was me who was in your bed, using your laptop to watch web series ( Oh I even forgot how many of those we have watched together). It was so fortunate that my interview was in Delhi and I was able to meet to you , that was a unique experience in its own right , exploring Old delhi, getting life lesson of not trusting food vloggers , going round and round in CP and those long talks on Rajpath and realising how single we are ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£.
Bro I feel that you have always thought that we were not  very good bhais from your level of competency and ambitiousness but bhai we have always thought about your best, u were kind of little brother to us.
Okk bro i think  I should leave now , I'm brimming with nostalgia. Now you have shifted to delhi so obvio we'll meet frequently and have fun as always.
All the best bro , may both of our careers eventually converge as civil servants ğŸ˜ğŸ˜.

And regarding the baseless question of me forgetting you, bro even if I alzheimers , your memory will clearly be remembered.

Till that Ciao.

Thank You,

text:
Tu hi ek esa banda hai jisse agar main "kalua" bolun to mujhe pata hai ki pakka offend nahi hoga. Kitni memories hain bhai tere saath. Humanoid se start hua, batti mein ghusa rehta tha, sab aata tha tujhe arduino chalana, smps chalana, R-pi chalana, . Humanoid ka hacker. Banda dil ka accha hai, honest hai, frank hai, par jo banda ration card ki website se bandi ki profile nikaal le, main usspe kabhi trust nahi kar sakta.
Bhai humanoid mein jo time spend kiya wo to kabhi na bhulne wala. Testing team mein apan ne pata ni kitne ni8 out maare honge saath mein, raat mein tera gyaan pelna start ho jaata tha, mera bhi dimag ghumne lagta tha. Dosa wala chutiyapa bhi yaad hoga, hindi mein hi shuru ho gya tha, bhai dosa ko hi emotional kar diya. 
Bhai Korea ki trip kabhi nahi bhulegi, yaad hai airport pe "ee nigga" wala incident, Raat ko main aur tu photo le rhe the road ke beech mein khade hoke, aur chote chote bacche bakchodi karre the, Korea ki party mein apan ne jaake gaana band karwa diya tha aur khud chad gye the stage pe, jab tu aur harsh aa rhe the to usski fati padi thi teri wajah se. 

Chalo abhi atleast saath to hain startup ke bahaane hi sahi. Yaad rakhna, agar contact na mile to rashan card ki website se detail nikaal lena. lol.

text:
Yaad hai, 10 baje aaye the ki code karde 12 baje deadline hai ğŸ˜‚. Yahi se start hui thi baate. Uss din ke baad se Mishra movie dekhta tha aur hum baate karte the.Tera Mishra ko bolna ki â€œMishra earphones laga leâ€ jab bhi Mishra bolta tha humko bhi bataye ğŸ˜‚. Apni high-level committee yaad hai- Tum, Rishu, Shashank aur mai. Lockdown mein to kitne video calls kare honge. Sayad hi koi din hoga jab video call na hua ho. Life ki 1-1 chiz discuss kar chuke the. Messenger group ka naam hamesha yaad rahega ğŸ˜›. Uss group ka content to kya hi bole. Dekho kabhi kabhi jab tum cooler mein so rahe hote ho to sardi lag jati hai achanak se bhi, usko kuch aur samajh liye the tum ğŸ˜¡. Patna wali trip ke to alag maze the. 2 din ka hi tha par maze aaye paidal ghumne mein (Thanks to Mukesh jiske liye har location bagal mein hi hota tha). GK Quiz yaad rahega. Mountbaten ki dusri shadi kab hui thi- 14 May 1935. Saale uske reception mein gaye the kya tum dono? ğŸ˜‚ Aur jo Mukesh ne artificial baarish karayi thi, train hi chutt jati. Last ke 50 din college ke kya hi the bhai. Sab kuch kiya padhai ke alawa. ğŸ¶Wo din bhi kya din the. ğŸ¶ 4  baje uthte hi Mishra ke room, fir H-13 mein khana, uske baad raat mein ghumna, raat bhar Mafia/patte/carrom. D-Mid wali chatt par ghumte hue gaane sun na, badminton, football, ek ek moment yaad rahega ğŸ˜‡. Jindagi mein nayi chize try karte rehni chaiye kyuki â€œAb to acche log bhi peene lage haiâ€ ğŸ˜›. Omegle pe tum jab â€œHey, Hiâ€ bolte the, uss accent mein tab ka to kya hi bole. Video call to chalu rahega hi even after tumlog Hyderabad chale jao.
P.S. Maggi aur chai to apan world-class banate hi hai I know. 
P.P.S Baki IPL chalta to jeet MI ki hi hoti. Udhar tera luck nahi chalega, samjha.

text:

Assignment, labs kabhi khud se nahi kiye. MATLAB to aaj tak install bhi nahi kiye, jane kitne course nikal gaye (special mention: Rohit Saini). Aur apna glider ko udane ka jugaad yaad hai na? 

Baki koi bhi advise ho, tumse jarur lete theğŸ˜‚. Itna gyaan bhandaar jo hai. Chemical bonding ka asli concept to tum hi sikhaya. Hall 12 ki saari parties mein tumhari shayri pe waah waah karna, saath mein besuro jaisa gaana, kutto ki tarah nachna ğŸ˜‚. Favorite shayri meri "Kaash" hai. Lockdown mein har 2-3 din mein shayri bhejte rehte the. Collect karke rakhe hai sab. Aage Bangalore mein kaam aayega ğŸ˜›. Patna trip ka to ek ek moment yaad rahega (special mention: GK quiz, baarish, aur chai-). Agar humko aage kabhi cancer hua to uske jimmedaar tum hoge ğŸ˜‚. Aadha kaam kharab mera to teri shayri aur playlist ne kari thi ğŸ˜›. Baki 15 July ko dekhte hai apni 10k wali shart ka result. 

P.S. Swaha ka sapna to swaha ho gaya! ğŸ˜‚
P.P.S. T-shirt sambhal ke rakhna meri. Wapas chaiye!

text:
â€œKabir to my Aditiâ€ 
I know how special I am in your life and its evidence is dated back to the day when I had my name on your lock screen xD. I have been promoted from your mental support in Robowars to your mental support in real life. Meri tareef kaafi hui chalo ab thodi tareef teri bhi kr deti hu â€” my first memory of yours is of ART105 â€” â€œ Faizan bht achchi photography krta and uske group ki videos bhi kaafi achchi hainâ€ I was like aakhir hai kaun ye and jab mili to Jee result milne ke baad bhi itna disaapointment ni hua jitna tujhse milkar hua.  Vo manhoos ghadi Antaragni ki thi jab hame dono mile. Uske saal ye 4 chaal tujhe kaise jhela, ye to mai hi jaanti hu. 
Biggest perk of being your friend was aunty ke haath ka khana and unka pyaar ( and she loves me more than she loves you ) plus jo tera hai vo mera hai :P
OAT rooftop pr nightout, vo takneek ke time pr NH91 jana, vo unlimited masti â€” memory loss hone ke baad bhi yaad rakhungi. Thanks for all your gifts and aage bhi aese hi dete rahiyo. 
You will always be the antivirus to my system and no one can take your place. Thanks for always being there for me and fighting for me when I was most vulnerable. Thanks for making me realise my weaknesses and what truly matters in life. I am glad I met you. At last, thoda sa gyan â€” start treating yourself better. You have been through a lot and deserve a lot of happiness. So stay happy and love you bht jyada <3. Anyway apne ko toh saath hi marna hai so jab tak zinda hain tab tak aese hi tang krti rahungi mai xD

I also remember, during my soap box, when people were asking ridiculous questions from me. Though you were supporting someone else and I have no hard feelings about that but what I really appreciated was you were not like those people. Even though you were on the other side, you did what was right. I truly believe you are a man with principles. Be like that always and keep progressing. 

And yes we'll have that deep conversation kabhi na kabhi. Hope we meet again soon.

Okay. Less go!! First and foremost congratulations. Finally CL trophy ke itna kareeb aa gye hain aap. text:
Mera Babu...
First of all...agr koi baba ko nhi jaanta, aur yeh memoir padh rha hai, toh tum 'duniya ka sabse perfect friend that a human can possibly get' miss krre ho. Baba is the only person jiska marte damm tk koi hater ni hoga. baba actually koi tera bura kr hi ni skta. chorr bhi tere ghar aayega, toh tu usko bhi enlighten krke vapas bhejega. baba you are like an open book to me...I kept on looking more and more phases of you...and keeps on liking you more and more. I remember 1st mein i've liked your witty comments always. poora group kahin baitha hua hai...toh usmein bakchod se comments maar ke sabki gaand maarne vaala, maze dilwane vaala was you. 2nd year mein..wing mein kisiko koi bhi dikkat honi, usko pyaar se sunna aur smjhane vaala was you. Apne saath saath wing ko bhi bhagwan se jodne vaala(chahe thoda bhot hi sahi) was you. harr ek bande ka go-to guy was you. 1st year se leke end tk wing ko jode rakhne vaala was you. hagge ke uss taraf vaale pakistani logon ko mujhse milwane ka credit bhi mein aapko hi dena chahunga. Selflessness baba mene sach mein terese seekhi. itna self-less kaie ho skta hai insaan.

Abhi mein tujhe bhagwan ka avatar bolne vaala tha...pr fir teri kamiyian yaad aayin. itni badi kuch ni hai...bss choti choti 2 cheezein. tu apni diet aur fitness ki bilkul ekdum maa chodke rakhta hai. agr yeh dono sahi krle na tu...bhai 'perfect human being' banne se koi ni rokk skta tujhe. smart, hardworking, good looking, cool etc. etc. sab hai...bss what you lack is discipline and control on your body. iska dhyaan rakha kr yr...poore wing ki jaan hai tu <3. 

Aur milne toh aata rhunga mein terese...kbhi kangaal vgera hokr.. sabki thokerein khaake...mein jb darwaza dhundhta hua aaunga toh mujhe pata hai sirf tu hi rakhega mujhe :) I'm so lucky that I met you babu :) I love you a lot :* :* take care apna aur apni body ka :)

text: Abhay. Tere liye ek adjective ki image hai dimaag mein but canâ€™t describe ki. Tu mera sabse ___ dost tha. Apan late bond kiye kaafi I guess par apni convos kaafi endless hoti thi be. Bas yaa to tu chale jaata tha ya bhaga deta tha. And exam time aane nahi deta :p. Vaise jo tune first year ke baad comeback kiya hai kaafi bakchod tha. Not just CPI but image, interaction and bakchodi. Now when I think bakchod to tu first year se tha. I think apne beech mein kabhi bhi clubs nahi aaye. Likhne ko to kaafi hai be. Kitna bhulla kaata apan ne legit. And apni to branch bhi alag thi. Vaise to mein sochta hun branch vagarh se thoda distance aa jaata hai kyonki cheezen kam common ho jaati hai but apne topics to kabhi khatam hi nahi hue. Ab to yaad bhi nahi aa raha aisi kya baaten karte the etni. Vo adjective abhi bhi nahi aa raha words mein. Tere saath vaise kaafi similar sa feel hota tha. Apne hi type ka banda hai. I was the funny,good looking,smart one :p but you were the jigri one. ** tere karan hi campus mein 26 tak ruka tha. Nikal gaya saala. Bhai jab tu campus se gaya tha to legit esa hota tha either mein ghoomte ghoomte tere room mein almost ghus jaata ya apne room mein kaam karte karte bahar is purpose se jaane lagta. Chill hai chal, mil liye yaar fir se and photos bhi ho gayi saath mein. Bangalore kabhi aaya to sabse pehle tujhe hi call karunga. Sorry modi :). And since tu to poochega nahi, trip pe chalte hai bhai secoond wave ke baad. Bas plan ho to usko just ticket book karne se pehle cancel mat karna :p.

text:
Bahubali. Mein year book portal par pehle bahubali search kiya xd. The first nickname anyone got in our wing.Tere mein to takkat dikhti bhi thi varna to chidhane vaala naam ban jaata. Vaise I think apne first month mein hi I knew ki tu sabse reliable person hai IIT Kanpur mein and I think sab esse agree karte honge. Esa kuch khass incident yaad nahi hai but teri vibe hi aise hai. Mein sochta tha agar kabhi kuch major panga ho gaya kisi se campus mein to pehla call esi ko karunga. Vaise 3rd year mein apna hangout karna kaafi kam ho gaya tha dono busy the but I guess abhi jab campus aaye to first year ki vibe se mile the. 
And Bhai tujhe vo bed vaali cheez yaad hai bhai. First year mein tumhare room mein hi to pada rehta tha apne room se bhi jyada. And fir neend aa hi jaati thi xd. Aniket to utha deta tha â€œjay uth uthâ€ karke. Uski awaz mein imagine kar. But tu bhola bhaala ensaan kaafi der dekhta rehta tha. Kaafi bahar to tu nahar kar aa raha hota tha fir tayyar hote hote aane jaane vaalo ko â€œmere bed pe jay soya hua haiâ€ kehta rehta tha. Man agar yeh line tere memoir mein nahi milti to I would be kind of offended ki tujhe yaad nahi hai. And fraud to nahi maara bhai batti club mein :)  bhale hi etna chaapa na ho. But seriously kehna chahunga and itâ€™s not only me, Tumhara aero club mein kaam dekh kar respect badh gayi thi bhai tere, kevlin ke liye kaafi. Baad mein laga shayad motivation alag raha ho :p but in the end to kaam matters.  Also Techmeet vaale ka chill hai bhai. Infact tu nahi tha to ofcourse mein tujhse expect nahi kar sakta na ki tujhe pata ho es baar kisne kya kiya. But I would say saamne se es baar jaan laga di thi bro. Tu 3-4 baar bol diya ese bata raha bro. Savage joke kharab kar diya tune baar baar bol kar. Bhai tu gurgaon aa jaa bas apartment ko hostel bana kar usi vibe mein rahenge.

Ab tere bhai ke paas to kaafi kuch hai bolne ke liye agar vo IIT Kanpur aaya to. Vo to shayad 1 saal tak bolta rahega. Vaise inspite of all these dasse, tu maggu nahi hai. text: Brooo. Obviously, mera pehla kaafi acha dost at IIT Kanpur. And ofc mein HSS first year esliye hi itna jaata tha because of apna group and log. Baaki aata to mujhe kuch nahi tha. Likhne ko to bohot kuch hai yaar. Apna common love for OAT. And now when I think eska reason HSS hi ho probably. Vaise first year baad thoda interaction kam ho gaya comparatively ek to branch ke karan doosra tere vo wing vaale kaand ke karan. 1-2 mahine to mein esi mood mein tha bhai esko saath mein rehna hi nahi to kon upar jaaye faltu ke. Fir aalsi to mein hui hi obviously. And thode mood swings kam kara kar aur koi jhelenge nahi man. ofc sabse jyada baar tere se hi lada hoonga. Well mein to sirf leta tha ladta to tu hi tha. Vaise tujhe pata nahi hoga but aadhi baar mera motive yeh hota tha ki tu apni thodi harkaton ko public mein sudhar le. I had a friend in Kota usko bhi aise harkton se pehle farak nahi padta tha and kehta tha log kuch bhi kahe kya farak padta hai but later he thanked me ki tu sahi kehta tha and usse improve karna chayie. Aise koi particular cheezen nahi hai but I think you know what I am talking about and tu sudhar to gaya mostly. Publicly esa to ab shayad nahi karta jisse log tujhe judge karen. Shayad kaafi choti si baat ke baare mein kaafi likh diya kyonki pehle kabhi bataya nahi. Bro vaise mein kaafi baar aise hi kaam karte karte so jaata tha. Us vakt aa kar dhang se sulane ke liye thanks man. And I never thought I would say this but un sab pareshaan karni vaali gandi photos ke liye bhi thanks. Bhej dena bas. Aur bhai tu jealous taunts mat pass kara kar bhai dosti pe. Mein introspect karne lag jaata hun. Inhi taunts ke karan aaj apni kaafi acchi photo nahi hai saath mein. Jis din bola tha us din khicha lete. Chill hai ab band karte hai likhna hai to kaafi kuch. Thoda memories se hat ke gyan ki side ho gaya xd. - Your investor number 1

text: Man tera memoir likhna sabse tough hai. Infinite cheezen hai. Firstly thanks campus bulane ke liye varna mil nahi paate. Yeh point tu gina sakta hai abse jab bhi bolen tera presi banna kya kaam aaya. Vaise apan dost shayad first sem midsem ke time bane the. Fir shayad apan winters mein roz OAT jaate the na? Abe vaise apan first year winters mein roommate bhi the. I literally have no memory of that time. Haan bas yahi ki us time tak apan same level par the :p. And ofcourse you are the only person I envy at IITK. Kaafi maje kiye be apan ne yaar. Apan to us stage mein pahuch gaye the ki kuch bhi ulta-seedha ho to apan situation par haste rehte the. Kaafi exams ka saath mein padha be. Kaafi fun hota tha. Undoubtedly the most fun person at IITK tabhi tere se etne log obssesed the. Vaise tu sabse bada reason hoga ki meri college life single nikal gayi. (Not writing this as an accusation) Tere liye first year mein sahi mein respect aayi thi jab etne saare options ke bawjood bhi tu kisi ka kaat ta nahi tha (yaa thoda sa hi kaat ta tha:)). Also teri us party mein I was not sure ki it was water but since tu presi banne se jyada es baat se khush tha, I went with it. So, meri galti nahi thi. Vaise apan kabhi nahi lade be. Halke se bhi nahi. Debates hui kaafi random topics pe ofcourse. May be because hamesha galti tu hi karta tha :) fir tu directly/indirectly sorry bol deta tha fir khatam. This was the best part. Mein hamesha like 0 filter mode mein hota tha tere saath. Jo man mein aa raha, nahi bhi aa raha vo bhi bol do. Esliye hi techmeet vaali night ko tujhe koi content nahi mila xd. Thanks man for chossing IITK inspite of all the options. Campus ki best memories tere saath hi hai.

Endsem ke time tumhara cycle kharab ho gaya tha to tum mera cycle leke ek exam dene chala gya tha aur mere pas mere cycle ki do chabhi thi jisme se ek tumhe di thi. Phir agle exam me tum pooche the ki cycle le jaye to maine bola tha ki mera v exam hai to mat leke jao but you being you, tum le gaye. Mujhe gussa aaya to mai devendra ke cycle ke peeche baith ke apna cycle L16 ke neeche se le kar ke library chala gya. Phir tum jab exam deke nikle aur cycle nahi milne pe mujhe call kiye, to pehle maine bola ki maine nhi li cycle aur jab maine baad me bola ki chill mar mere pas hi hai to tu ye bina sune hi phone cut kar diya. Phir thode der ke baad jab mera xam tha L16 me to tum wapas aaye aur wahan cycle dekh ke le gaye hall. Phir devendra tumhe mila aur bola ki cycle to krishna le liya tha. Phir tumhe laga ki tum kisi aur ka cycle utha liye ho aur cycle sis guard ke pas jama kar aaye with application. Phir baad me mere xam ke baad jab mujhe cycle nhi dikhi to maine tumhe call kiya aur tumne bataya saari baat, phir mai sis guard se cycle maangne gaya to phir ek application likh kar ke diya aur saari baat batayi. Phir ye kahani sis guard ke is line se khatam hui,- "bhaiya aapka dost alag chutiya hai lekin".

text: I don't know how to recall about the ultimate person in IITK. You are the epitome of perfection for me. Almost 3.5 saal inferiority complex m raha, but when I met you, I found an awesome friend in you jo party dene m nahi darta. I'm proud that I met a person like you as even today I brag about you in front of people that you are such a nice personality. I hope korea m tumhe artificial ki jagah original maal milega. Ghar par R***iputram ki parampara ko aage badhaya hoga tumne. Apni dosti kam time k liye thi ye matter nahi karta, but ye pichhle 3 saal se bhi jyada bakchod thi ye matter karta hai, aur aage bhi hmesha hi rahegi, Those perfect shots in moonlight at the top of helicopter building, that illegal breach in environmental building, that IPL match, library k peeche ki wo forcefully bnayi gayi candid photo(ye shailab to kitna bada ......... hai), airstrip tak pahuchne ki nakam kosis and of course your choice of songs, how can I ever forget that and pretty much sure I will never get those moments back. I gave you some fever and cough as a parting gift as you followed me to quarantine in those last moments, no need to thank me for that. I I wanna see you in living a balanced life to jaldi se kisi ko pata le aur milwana zaroor. I'll be one of the first persons to buy your novel and go through it. I miss you brother..... Milte rhna jab bhi moka mile.... I'll always be there for you for anything for any sort of bakchodi....

author: Kuldeep  Singh

text:
I wish I could write a book on you over a period of few months as every second I spent with you were exhilarating for me. I saw you on your Birthday for the first time and tried to gift you that pink foam balloon and passed out while looking at you as you were always such a beauty. Just your name is enough to fill me with enthusiasm that was the reason that I was able to get up from my bed and went to 8am class  to write down your name on the board. HSS to bhana tha, mera motivation to tumse hi tha wahan aane ka. Then came Tauu project, I can recall that you made our door opener a success when all of us gave up on that, even that lab was never tiring for me becuase of you. I used to ask people(nitesh, shrey...) about you and always tried to figure out some possibilities to steal some moments with you. You were one of the inpiration for me that I came back to that campus in those last months of my final year. Starting with chai samosa in canteen till almost daily nightouts, daily nayi nayi building dhoondhna, naye naye raston par jaakar sis guard k bolne par wapas aana, OAT m KK ka concert dekhna, ya Holi k din illegel tareeke se bahar ghoomkar aana, wapas aakr hall 13 ki canteen m khakar fir se ghoomne nikal jaana, Hall 2 se NCL ki taraf waali road par alag alag ped k naam par ladai karna,then NCL m paani peene k bhane sis guard ka ch***ya kaatna, wahan se nikalkar Helicoptor building ki chhat par jaakar uss breez ko feel karna, beech m yahi kahin IME building m poster k peeche deshbhakti dikhana, aur bahar nikalkar alag alag flowers par gyaan jhadna, Environmental bulding m fountain k paani par stone ko jump karana, RM k top floor se kanpur ko taadna, aur late raat bhootiya feeling m "Mere dholna sun" bjana, fir auditorium waale raste par pedo m alag alga insaano ki sakal dhoondhna, aage illegal tareeke se Park 67 m entry maarna,  wapas aate hue director waali road par pandey aur shrey ko race lgane k liye majboor karna, beech m tumahra hostel zaroor aayega par ye ghoomne ka silsila abhi thode hi khatam hoga, abhi to chawpati par dahi kawab bhi to khana hai, fir daaru ki planning bhi to karni hai (I really miss ki m tum logo k saath mahi pi paaya, but this isn't the ending) all centered around you and you only, ye sab to ek din ka chhota sa hissa hai, aise kitne hi din ham log saath m bakchodi kiye hai. How can I ever forget that sweet girl who came to meet me in my deadly quarantine(though again illegal :) ) and put a smile on my face. You are an epitome of inspiration for me. I have braged about you infront of almost everone I had known. I wanna live that life again... You made my days worthy to remember in the campus...You are the sweetest, cutest, enthusiatic, fantastic, heartful, adventuress, damn beautiful, girl I have ever met. I miss you and will always...Milte rhna, abhi to trip karna hai, daru pini hai, alumni banke wapas se campus ghoomna hai... even a lifespan will be less itni masti karni hai and what not. I'm eager to see you again, again kanpur wapas ka aane ka motivation degree se jyada tum hi ho....I'll always be there for you for anything, any sort of bakchodi.... 
see you soon
"My College crush"
author: Kuldeep  Singh

text: Bhai ab to btade campus m kon pasand hai...I can't remember a single moment jab ham ek doosre ko dekhkar na hase ho, bc itni bhi joker jaisi sakal nahi hai, par hasi to aa hi jaati, I was never even a percent of you but always tried to catch up to you, Bhai tu hai chapu maan le, Bahut RR machata hai, fir hmi ko chhorkar aage badh jaata hai, ham ussi bakchodi m fase rah jaate, Lucknow shaandar tha but usse bhi shaandaar thi wo raat, How can I forget our "Aishwrya rai" dancing on "Kajra re" and then that stud guy dancing in hall 8 on the ocassion of diwali, sab log bas group m circle bnakar tujhe hi taad rahe the. I always figured out a part of me in you, I never missed a chance to brag about you infront of people, I'm blesses to have a brother like you. Dhyaan se dekhiye iss masoom se chehre k peeche chipe stud launde ko, jispar ladkiyaan marti hai, but bhai sahab bhaav nahi dete, Bhai Badminton m jo maarta tha tu hmesha yaad rahega. Apna pushup challenege to barkarar rahega, though looking at you right now, I accept my defeat even before competing with you. I'll miss you brother.... Milna hai bhai, ye thode hi ending hai....I'll always be ready for any sort of bakchodi with you, just ping me once...

text: I remember the first walk I had in IITK, it was with you, figuring out the way to the airstrip. Tabhi se feel aa gayi thi ki bohot genuine banda hai, and this is the kind of people I want to meet here. It's been a long journey since, one that I've had the privilege to share with you. We've shared goals, dreams and ambitions, but the thing I'll remember the most is being able to share the truth with you. You may not think of it as much, but genuinely bohot kam log milte hai jinnke sath you can actually be yourself. I believe in you bhai, you just need to build the same confidence in you about yourself. Math ka RR to hum dono hi bhoolna chahte hai, so I won't recollect that here. What I want to cherish is our shared aspirations, our countless efforts chasing it and our shared dreams which we're going to achieve sooner rather than later.
author: Kushagra  Gupta

text: Bhai! Can't even begin, or hope to capture the moments I've shared with you, yearbook mei itni capacity hi nahi hai. College ki pehli daru se leke akhri tak (I made it a point not to drink after you left), canteen ke kebab parantha se leke Goa ke kaju tak, first year ke kattapa se leke...kattapa to tu abhi bhi hai XD, college ke some of the best experiences I've had the privilege of living with you. I'm terribly poor at first impressions, but thank god I was right about you, you bright bundle of positive energy. Even though NN was making us laugh, you've been the one to make me smile. In some of my darkest times in IITK, teri koi faltu bakchodi ya impossible plan was enough to remind me what's good in life, a random visit to your room was enough to remind me ki jitna bhi haggu I'll always have the best place to return to. Honestly, you've been the glue to our group, wo fevicol ka jod jo dosti jodta chala gaya. If I use the IITK lingo of bhai in it's truest sense, you shine as the best example of it. If ever you need me, if ever you make a plan, count me in, cause it's not about the place, it's about the people ( ;) ). This is not goodbye!
author: Kushagra  Gupta

text: Smartest person on campus, hands down (I include the profs too XD)! With that out of the way, thanks for all the memories and support man! I really appreciate it. I can't think of any other person to share the coordiship of Pclub with, and if it wasn't for times when we had to just grind thorugh it, the club would've failed. You've been the best coordinator the club has seen, atleast in my eyes (and that's a big compliment given the history). But you go way beyond that, I've always been in awe whenever I've worked with you, be it competing in Inter IIT, discussing topics people will understand only after 150 years, working through making problems or lectures, designing a Tshirt or even simply playing board games. I've always felt a certain ease when hanging out with you, and maybe that's why it was special for me. I'll cherish our talks cycling to and fro to RM, movie screening and board games in astro club, our discussions (literally everywhere), our 'trip' to Bombay, shared lunches and dinners (pizzas have never tasted the same outside Sandy's room) and most importantly, everything I've learnt from you. See you soon in Cali mate, we've yet to conquer Disneyland!
author: Kushagra  Gupta

text: Bsdk! Sorry, couldn't start your memoir without this. Let me start this memoir with an apology you deserve, tu humara personal punching bag tha but you stood strong through all of it. Can't think of a more fun or interesting person I've ever met, or imagine college life being what is was without you! And honestly speaking, you're one of the few people I cherish the most meeting here, so definitely US to leke jaa raha hu tujhe bhale hi bag mei bharke leke jana pade...can't imagine life being fun without you being in it. We all know tu bohot hi zyada smart hai, but what I want to talk about is how supportive and good-hearted you've been. Thode matlabi to sab hote hai XD, but the effort I've seen you putting for others (man it goes way beyond giving coding tests for others) is astonishing. Although life ki practicality mei kafi hagga hai tune (kabhi bag cinema hall mei bhoolna, kabhi phone, and wallet and ID card to bhagwan jane kaha hai)...but the way you've conducted your four years here, from your ideology towards it to your logic for living it, are closest to perfection. Your strength of character is astounding, jitne mazze humne tere liye I can't think of anyone else who could have faced it with a smile, and still be the buzzing, brilliant happy-feet. Know this for a fact mate that jitna devotion and dedication tune apni friendship mei dikhaya hai for all of us, utna hi hum bhi reciprocate karte hai tere liye. 'Aap -aap' karte hue 4 saal to nikal hi liye tune, ab Google bhi jaa raha hai..you're well on track on your plan to be the next CEO xd. Even after all our first year debates, fight club brawls and fifa el clasico's, you're the first person I would stand up for on campus. Although first year mei humne tujhe duniyadari sikhane ka try kiya ho, I will say this..never change. You're one in a googol, and the world is your oyster.
author: Kushagra  Gupta

text: Maybe we didn't start on the right foot (absolutely no idea why that's the case), but I'm so glad we corrected it (bonding over maal ka perfect example!). You're one of the most fun people to have a conversation with and a really cool person to hang out with (even the sober me agrees). We've shared loads of stuff, from our branch, halls, debates and Vox to bongs, our love for beef, hijacking trains, sutte and drunkard dance steps. Convocation in Goa was extremely fun minister! And I'm thrilled to have had you as my Hobbes. It sometimes feels like you're one of the most wrongly judged people in hall 2, but I feel like I know you much better now, having shared a convocation at Goa and a very tipsy return to college.

author: Mahajan Dipak Anil

text:
Yo Dhawal!! 
Bhai bahot si memories judi hai yaar tumhare saath!! Regarding the night when the third yearites caught us, I too felt the same way lol!! I was shit scared what would happen and shayad mere chehre se dikh bhi rha hoga but still it was a fun night. Do know that I was looking forward to dance to rocky/disco song and certainly not a slow arijit singh song ğŸ˜›. I had spent two years of my life in kota away from my home but somehow in the initial days i was still feeling a bit homesick. This was in the very beginning of the orientation and I didn't know kaise logon se milunga and kya hoga aage. But you did a very good job on distracting me from these thoughts of homesickness and making me focus on the fun part of college life instead. I will never forget the roasts of the people( mostly tamonud and divyanshu ). Tum kaafi mazedaar insaan ho bhai!! Gaana gaa lete ho, poems likh lete ho, bakchod writing skills, mathematics strong hai, basketball khel lete jo itna bakchod, funny ho kaafi(ngl I still laugh at the story of 'kiski **** me kitne **** aaj ginega deepak **** sometimes). Thanks for all these memories!! I really cant keep a track but there are lots of memories and I thank you for that!! 
Thanks for being there bruh. I have always been admiring you and there were times when you just made me forget about the hard part of life with your hilarious joles and roasts. 
Thanks for teaching me how not to look like a creep when you're checking out girls in Antaragni ğŸ˜›!! 
I know there are some uncertainties in life as of now regarding the career choices and about persuing things that you're passionate about. But do know this - I believe in you!! I know you will do good in whateger field you choose to be in. Sure, there might have to struggke a bit in the beginning. But I know you will figure it out and bakiyo ka pata nai hai but you have my support ğŸ˜ƒ. All the best for your future!! Baki yaar tum Delhi me hi ho agar toh pakka milna hoga apna toh - pawri karte hai milke jaldi hi !! Love you man ğŸ’

text:
"Sone de yaar" 
- rathore, 2017,18,19. 
Aur Bhai Adi!! Hopefully abhi BT khatm ho gayi hogi zindagi ki kaafi had tk!! I was really happy the day I got to know youve sorted things out!! I know it had been hard for you for nearly a year but you made it through anyway!! I still remember the zumba in the orientation, when most of the people around us were not exactly interested in dancing and then there were us - OAT ke sabse last wali seedhi pe jo saath me naache the bakchodi me that was a very nice evening. I could enjoy that because of you man cause I know for sure akela toh nahi hi naachne wala tha mai kisibhi haalat me xD. Thanks for that!! I also remember that ome time you encouraged me to come to the tracks with you foe the runs and made me go for a run in the mornings too. I remember the countless times we turned the lights of our room in the night because seniors were in the wing. I remember those failed attempts at waking people up in the mornimg kust for breakfast. I remember that annoying samsung alarm which used to wake us up for the PE101 sessions. I remember the EDM nights that we attended together and had loads of fun. 
Thank you for all these memories!! All the best for your future!! Love you man!!

Love you!! You're one of the most awesome people I've met at IITk.

text:
Yo bro!! I donâ€™t remember when did we meet for the first time. I think it was the TA lab and I thought damn saare CSE walo ko group in kar Diya hai yaha toh sare maggu log honge. But there were us!! Bunch of nerds trying to seek fun in things that were not that intereseting and boy did that turn out well. I always admired you for the level of hardwork that you put into things and I really feel it is your best quality. There is one thing however that I think you should know and it is that you are an extra ordinary person bruh. You may not believe it at times and think that you are just an ordinary guy who would not be able to do much but I know you're not. You're awesome!! Itna sab kuch karke bhi FB stories me positivity failaate ho logon me. You surely lift up spirits too!! There were times when I was not feeling good but you were there - sharing wholesome memes, laughing at the silly jokes that I used to slip in between and yet helping me out in academics at the same time. Thanks for that, thanks for existing. I cant imagine what would have been my situation in some of the courses if you were not there. I love how you also have a similar taste in music and also the feel good memes and the literature as well!! Baki bro mai tumhe kya time management sikhau tum khud itni saari cheeze manage karte ho- you are really breathtaking. I was not really a nightout wala guy in the first year. But when I met you in 4th sem and saw you just flipping the side of the match just through nights -  i was really motivated ( lmao you did a DS assignment once throughout the night and I was really awestruck. I thought ye bande ka ye assignment toh gaya time hi nai bacha hai and there were you!! Damn it was the first time I saw someone do that tbh and later on tumhare saath reh reh ke mai wo bhi sikh gaya) . I do not have much words how to thank you and I can not yet imagine what would the journey look like without you in it., Because seriously, you were there with me in the darkest semester - I remember all the nightouts and countless deadlines and the scary nights of OS. You were there all the times and you helped me get through it. Thanks a lot. Baki bro, milte hai Noida me Party karenge saath me and bakchodiya karenge aur bhi!! All the best for your future - no doubt tum chaapoge aage bhi!! Cause I believe in you and you are enough!!

text:
To,
the Based Chairperson Gang,
Vrooooooooooooooo!!!!!
You're the wisest homie out of all the homies and ngl I really got to learn a lot from you. A wise man once said "you should not call someone your best friend because then you are comparing your friends and that is not good".  Ironically, the very first line of this memoir compares you with other people but okay. you are really a very awesome person and I am grateful that I got a chance to meet you in my life. I remember we met for the first time in first year summers lol. It was the phy103 AM thingy on which we worked together. I hate that we did not get to hang out in the last month of iitk. But hey, Gurgaon aur Noida ke beech kitna hi fasla hai lol. I really like how I could easily message you regarding how the Y18 is fucked up in ESC and we should do something and how easily we went on board and actually helped them. Thanks, for everything. All the best for the future endeavours. Love you <3.

text:
Hehe bro, 
ye memoir me kya hi likhu ab samajh nai aa rha. Jab bhi kuch kehna hota hai tumse mai toh seedha keh deta hu tumhe dont think aisa kuch hoga jo nahi keh paaya hounga. Thanks for giving me that space and trusting me at the same time. I remember that one time when you sensed that I might be overthinking things and might be in the guilt that I have messed up things. You knew I might be hurting myself just by overthinking on that and you sent me the most comforting text one could possibly send at that time. tbh I was really really scared at that time and you helped me. Life is weird no? Sometimes we help people and we think that it is a very small thing for us but it really means a lot to them. Thanks for that. Well this was just one incident, I think there a lot more incidents where you helped me when I wasn't doing okay, Even lockdown ke time me you were one of the very few people jinse meri har roz baat hoti thi and I think uska reason bhi obvious hai. You end up where you find most comfortable.  Thanks for existing. Thanks for everything. I will never forget the antaragni nights when we scrolled tinder together, the nights in sixth semester when we bonded and opened up to each other, that one whole night when we shared the gossips, the days when we planned out things together, the last night when you gave me that letter and other countless occasions. It was a very wonderful journey. A journey holistic journey in fact. I really enjoyed the journey and I hope you enjoyed it too!! Thanks for making it special. You are one of the few people I go to whenever I do not feel good and yet everytime you make me feel great about myself. Thanks for existing. I really hope we get to meet soon and complete all the pending pawris. All the best!! Also, I believe in you, no matter what other people say - I know you are a wonderful person and you  will achieve great things in life. Congratulations future Yashika for all the success!! Love you!!

text:
Hey!
I think I have not thanked you enough for everything you have been to me and done for me. Thanks for being my support for all these years, thanks for being there when even I didn't know I needed someone, Thanks for caring for me like a mom, teaching me like an elder sis, and always being there for me as my bestie. I have never expressed how grateful I am to have you, as I have always feared it'll jinx our relationship (not saying it friendship cause we are much more than that). But could not control it anymore with all the nostalgia trip xD. 
I think you are one of the very few people who has seen me crying my heart out, having a breakdown and not just been there for me but helped me recollect myself and stand strong again. 
Thanks for tolerating me all these years when at times I wondered how could someone bear with me. 
Love you a lot! 
P.S. I don't wanna jinx it by saying any forever wala stuff ğŸ˜¬

Hello Madam! 
It's actually been 5 years! I vividly remember the day I met you in Dakshana, and I still can't believe that our fantasy of going to the same college came true. I was so happy ( even more shocked) when I saw you in front of the hall office on my first day at IITK. It's been one hell of a ride, and you've always been my saviour throughout. And yes, our random 2 AM conversations about literally everything, including friends, food, fashion, crushes, have made it so much more tolerable and entertaining. Ice cream and Meggie sessions were icing on the cake XD ( I'll always miss this). 
You have my heart for being the most dramatic and self-obsessed ( in a good way) BFF I could ever have. And yeah, I'll keep advising you on your relationship issues ( you know kitni pro hu m isme LOL) 
Thanks a lot for making me grow so much as a person and as a friend during these 5 years. I'm going to brag about having this " Smart-Gorgeous-Badass Bestie" for the rest of my life XD. Ig itni tareef kaafi h, Baaki tareef milegi tb karungi.
Let's always be there for each other. Aur Haan, Love you <3
PS: Don't roast me for writing those cheesy lines; you made me do this :P

text:
I know you are everyone's Sontu but IDK why I think I have spent more time calling you Chotu, just for the irony of it. 
Yaar first year would have been impossible without you. Sab saath mein kiya - padhai, ELS, TA, aero, and of course A-603 ki mastiya.  "Medha tumhare room mein bois hai" always cracks me up, but it was so true; tu hota toh that hamesha. Thanks for getting me through ESC101; you know all about my syntax errors. You'll be glad to know woh abhi bhi hai. SC-II ki labs mein same harkate karti thi :P
I'll miss those Antaragini nights, random NH-91 dinners, and of course OAT hangouts. Those two years wouldn't have been fun without you.

I know we grew very much apart after the second year. To an extent, ki jab campus mein the toh samajh nahi aa raha that ki kya hi bolu. I am sorry for the distance. If I could go back in time, maybe I'll try to fix some mistakes. I knew you as the guy jo MTH mere se padhke, mere se zyada number lata ha and look what you have achieved now. Just keep paddling upwards like this. Kya yaar, I recall Goa mein apna drunk heart to heart interrupt ho gaya that. Koi nahi, another time!

I hope we meet again and relive those fun "boondi ke laddu wali ice cream" nights in Bangalore again.
author: Medha  Agarwal

text:
Yo God! 
Yaar to this day I can't stop laughing at how much you resemble the Monkey King. I remember the first time Sonthalia introduced us, I took him away and whispered "yaar yeh toh ekdum monkey king jaisa hai." I remember how I crashed your and GJ's initial library date (when you weren't dating :P) and told her the monkey king thing. Thankfully, she didn't mind the similarity warna kya hi hota tera! :-)

I love how happy you always are and tend to dissipate that thing in every group. I have come out of our every conversation thoroughly amused and in complete awe of you. It was fun organizing GJ's birthday with you while you were fretting about doing the decorations all wrong. Chal I got a sick fire hazard story in return. Mujhe toh bohot maza aaya. 

I wish we could have interacted more on campus but jab bhi mile it was one memorable experience. Teri respect bhi bohot hai and tujhe dhamki bhi de rhi hoon - khayal rakhna meri bestie ka, bohot pitega warna. I really wish we meet again sometime. At least Singapore ghuma toh dena hi whenever I visit.
author: Medha  Agarwal

text:
BC! Sabne sab kuchh to likh diya. Me kya likhu?

Branch se hi contact me aaya tha even after being a wingie. I wish jaldi aaya hota. Bc kitni galtiya na karta zindagi me me. Aur yaar! Samaj hi nahi aa raha kya likhu. Apne saath me jitni memories hai woh koi aisi bakchodi wali nahi hai. Sukoon wali hai bhai. Saath me terrace pe jana, saath me campus ghumna, saath me shopping karna, saath me resturant jana. BC aisa lag raha hai dating ke baare me likh raha kisi bandi se ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚

Anyways! Mere saare mood swings sambhalne ke liye thank you bhai. Tu nahi hota to chize karne me confidence nahi aata. You are & will always be that "Validation wala Filter" for every major thing that I will do. Tuje niche jaate bhi dekha hai, chaapte hue bhi dekha hai, naachte, gaate, acting karte bhi dekha hai.

Koi chaapu nahi hai tu. Woh to meri kripadrashti ka kamaal hai. I can't even imagine ki yeh banda abhi bhi bas 20 saal ka hai. I have seen your desperation for acads, girls & even me coming to Bangalore. Tere to maze hai. ğŸ˜‚ğŸ¤¦ğŸ»â€â™‚ï¸

Goa trip tere bina imagine bhi nahi kar sakta bhai. Tere darr, tere chochle, teri balchodiya - sab mast hai bhai. Externally koi banda dekhega to apan ko c*** kahega but we all know ki Modi Varshney ki yaari bhai alag level pe hai. Jay to aise hi bolta rehta hai ki bulla karta tha woh and all. Uski vastavikta hi chhoti hai to ab kya kare. 

Mere saare mood swings jaante hi ho tum, sambhale bhi hai kaafi tune, aage bhi sambhalte rehna. Me tereko positive approach deta rahega. Bhai! Startup saath me to nahi par ek time pe shuru kara hai to saath me aage bachenge, grow karenge, parties & trips marenge aur bohot memories banayenge.

Bhai! Iski word limit kya hoti hai? Chhod. Ab khatam karta. Baaki to tuje sab pata hi hai XD

I mean it needs a lot of effort to maintain any type of relationship, and I respect you a lot for all your efforts to keep our friendship going. 
This whole memoir would be like green trees but with no fruits if I donâ€™t talk about our college life. You made these whole four years of college life really awesome by showing us your writing skill. Bhai mera SHAYAR..kasam se yar...kya likhte ho bhai..ekdum gaddar...I had only listend earlier ki â€œPYAR ME LOG SHAYAR BN JATE HAIâ€, but you made me believe it. Here is a two-liner that came in my mind spontaneously, hope u like it:
Ek tum aur tera adhoora pyar, i wish ki it happens bar bar;
You might not want it to happen again, but trust me, this will be the reason for your name and fame!
I just canâ€™t wait to see you on youtube and your book to be a bestseller in India...macha dena bhai! 
And yes, thank you for being there whenever I needed someone. Whenever I was in a confusion for choosing or doing something or not, you were the first person who I went to. And, ofc how can we both forget that traumatic period of my lifeğŸ˜¢...man i just canâ€™t tell how i would have been if u were not there. I am really really thankful to you bhai. And thanks to you for making me start all the nashe thingsğŸ˜œ...it really feels amazing. Kuchh nashe bache hai, but i know ki tu uski bhi aadat lgwa dega. But, how could I forget that Nainital trip man. Bhai, mai maut ko takk se choo k wapas aa gya tha...it was scary..but i really enjoyed it man. The funniest trip was our regular Patna trip. Sutta fukna at every Patna trip. Jb bhi tum patna aate the, ek lambi list hoti thi tumhare pas, of all the street-food and their locations.Jha bhi jao, â€˜paisa wasoolâ€™ ki responsibility tum lete the. Bhai, to ek din bhukha aata tha, paisa wasool krne k liye. and ghar jakar pta chlta tha ki you have gained 5 kgs of weight...i mean are you for real??? And itne khane wale bnde ko achanak se diet follow krna, i canâ€™t believe my eyes. Jo bhi ho, you are following it strictly, and yes huge respect for this. Aur bhai, wo 85 kg wali bet ko jyada serious mt le yar, gareeb aadmi ko jeene nhi doge kyağŸ˜‚. The most hilarious and memorable trip to Patna was of course Janâ€™21. First of all, you should thank me for making you lose your weights, and saving your auto ka kirayağŸ˜œ. We did so much kand bhai...you know that! 
Last but not the least, I wish you very very good luck for your great journey ahead. I hope you fulfill all your dreams, and most importantly follow your diet, cause the â€˜BETâ€™ is still ON.
Love you 3000xğŸ’“ğŸ’“
