text:
I really don't think ki mujhe kaisa bhi memoir likhne ki jarurat hai. Apni yaado ko mai memoir nhi banaunga. Memoir toh ek kitaab mei band ho jayga, par mujhe umid hai ki hamari dosti us kitab mei band nhi ho sakti.

Isliye, is memoir mei aisa tujhe kuch nhi milega jo tu dhoondna chah raha hai. Ham hamesha connected toh hai hi.

Par haan agar kabhi hamara connection fail ho gya ho toh, toh here is my 5-point plan. Ye hai toh tumhare 19-22 saal ke safar ko dekhte hue. Umid karte hain, aage bhi kaam aayega-  

1) Itna yaad rakhna ki duniya ke har kone tak koi "connection" nhi pahunchta hai. agar tu mountain peak par jaata hai toh vaha mobile signal toh NHI milega kabhi, ofcourse. Toh agar peak par jaana hai toh, apne "network" ke comfort zone se bahar toh nikalna HI padega. Safar AKELE hi karna hoga upar tak.

2) Tum ek khuli kitaab toh ho hi. Koi na bhi padhna chahe toh bhi dikh hi jaata hai. Tumhari is khuli kitab ko tumhare colleagues bahut fayda uthaenge, aur tum fas bhi jaaoge. Reason batane ki jarurat nhi.
Isliye koshish karna ki is kitab ko band rakhna. Band karna matlab, jo bhi tumhare anadar chal rha ho, use bahar mat aane do. You need to practice on acting for that. Infront of the mirror, try to make facial expressions, and postures and judge yourself.
Agar itna karne par bhi nhi ho rhi kitab band, toh koshish karna ki "cover" chadha lo. Cover can be used so that your feelings can be covered under it. You can tell a different story. Don't tell your real feelings to everyone. Remember, to tell outsiders ON A NEED TO KNOW BASIS (google it). Seperate your personal and professional life. Tumhari poori mixed up hai. Colleagues ko personal life mei jyada mat ghusne dena. Kuch kaam nhi aayege, kamzor bana denge.
Aur haan, diary likhne se kuch farq nhi padhta hai, ulta negative effects hi hote hai. Isliye diary likhna band hi karo.

3) Ab chalte hai, ek aur related topic par. Self-introspect vs overthink. Self introspect sab ko karna chahiye, it is necessary but overthink nhi. Jab bhi aisa lage ki jyada soch raha hai, then change your thought process. Focus somewhere else. For example, read any interesting topic, preferably in HINDI. (watching videos and listening music don't help, because you need to use your brain.). If you think you always overthink on a certain topic, then dont introspect. Dont think yourself as you. Think about the whole scenario with respect to a 3rd person in the room. Then judge the situation. Think about bigger goals. Or take others' perspective. Lighten your mood.

4) And, "Lighten your mood" ka mtlb bas ek nhi hota hai. Acha laga dekh ke ki tumne apne hostel ke aakhri dino mei control kara. It proved you can DO if you WANT. You can overcome FOMO easily. You cannot ever justify drinking unless it is a medical condition (that to beer). Kabhi iske lat mei mat doobna.

5) Doobte toh tum "friends" mei bhi ho. lol. Maine tumhe in 4 saalo mei kai baar alag-alag "samudra" doobte dekha hai. Tumhe "samudra" ki "gahraiyon" ko explore karne ka badha shaok hai. Par yaad rkhna, utna hi gahrai mei jaana, jahan se tum bahar aa sako. Kisi mei itna mat doob jaana ki fir uski gahrai tumhe apne andar kheechne lage. Ache ache divers bhi doob jaate hain, jyada gaharaiyon mei. Agar samudra see bahar an aa paao toh "tairna" seekh lo. Swimming mei bhi bahar nikalne ke liye, "samudra" ke "pani" ko peeche dhakelna padhta hai. Samudra ko toh kuch nhi hota, vo vishaal hai. Par tum jaroor baahar aa jaoge, khuli hava mei saans le paaoge. Tum apna socho, sumdra ka nhi. Ghut ke nhi jeena hota hai.

Last mei,
"ZINDAGI NA MILEGI DOBARA" - is phrase ka real meaning dekhna. Zindgai sirf ghoomne firne se nhi banti. Zindagi har pal hai. JEETE TUM HAR PAL HO, MARTE EK BAAR HO.

Agar pahle pata chala hota toh, saath mei kaafi padh liye hote. Khair chodo, umid hai sab apne goals ko achieve kar le.
Aur haan, tumhe kuch jyada hi hasne ki aadat hai :D. Achi baat hai, bas serious bhi ho jaaya karna beech beech mei. Age seriousness aur dedication hi le jaayegi.

text:
Bhai. tere baare mei jab bhi yaad aata hai, sabse pahle vo TA ka solidworks yaad aata hai. us samay meri poore 4 saalo mei sabse jyada fati rahti thi, and you r a life saver. Ab tak maine 6 cities ke 8 schools mei padha hoon. Kai dost peeche choot jaate hai. Bachpan mei bahut mushkil hua karta tha. Ab aadat padh chuki hai. Aaj tak mera koi dost mujhe fir nhi mila. Tujhse mai pahli baar neemuch mei mila tha. Mera 6B aur 7A tha. vahan se jaane ke baad socha nahi tha maine fir milna hoga. Par us din tujhe lift mei dekhne par, mera dimag confusiya gya. Ye kya ho gya. Kya ye vahi hai. Yahi soch raha tha.

Uske baad apna safar badhiya hi guzra. Umid hai, tum aage success prapt karoge. Best of luck priy mitr!

text:

Bahut doubts solve kiye hai tune, afsos hum eco201 mei return nhi kar paaye, lol. MTH101 se lekar yahan aa gye aaj, time badhi jaldi beet gya. Kuch kaam na hone par ek doosre ke room par aa jaate the, kaafi maza aata tha. :D

Tumhari fitness bhi gazab hai, bahu garmi lagti hai aur trips par tumhare "dost" aa jaate hai. 2 baar back2back covid ho gya. Iske bavjood bhi tumhara sports mei javab nhi. Baminton mei toh nhi jeet paate mujhse, ofcourse :P, but kaafi versatile ho. TT, Baddy, Cricket, aur pata nhi.

Tum bhale hi wing ke last days at hostel mei nhi aa paaye, koi baat nhi, video calling ki tech ne kami nhi hone di. Isi tech ko aur aage lekar jaana, best of luck. :)

author: Naman Agrawal (M Agrawal)

text:
I really hope you didn't forget me if you are reading this after a long time. agar yaad na aaye toh apne memoir padhna jo tune mere liye likha tha. Kaafi descriptive hai. :)

Mile ham mutual friend Priyanshu ki vajah se the (PSY151A ke group ke liye), par vaise bhi milna ho hi jaata department se. Par 1st year se hi milne ki vajah se hamara bond kaafi acha ban gya. Apne college mei within-batch acads ke alava jyadatar log baat nhi karte, par hum kaafi kiye.

College mei kam hi log hote hain jo apne subjects ko interest se padhte hain, tum bhi unme se hi the. Is vajah se hamara acads mei kaafi banti thi aur saare groups bhi ek hi saath banaye. Kai baar hum class ke baad cycle par hi sab doubts discuss kar lete the. Is vajah se eco padhne ki jarurat nhi padhi. lol

Par acads ke alava bhi hamare kaafi similar interests the. Tera simple aur decent nature kaafi sahi hai. Aur tujhe hasne ki bahut aadat hai, bhale hi baat faltu ho. Isko change mat hone dena. Sab problems aasan ho jaati hai.

Hamne kaafi extra time saath mei bhi kaata hai jaise, mera room (D6, Hall 12), library, ccd, aur ek din yaad ho toh hum ghumte ghumte akele L20 bhi gye the jab sem khatm ho gya tha. Hum dono ko nature aur silence kaafi acha lagta hai.

In short, you made my life at IITK SIMPLE (simple like a home). Jab bhi mood kharab ho toh tujhse baat karke acha hi lagta tha. Par mujhe tera TV series ka taste acha nhi laga, lol. koi nhi.
Kuch samay pahle tu IES ki taiyaari kar raha tha, abhi pata nhi kya update hai. Plans change hote hai, koi nhi. Par tera jo bhi plan bane, best of luck. Umid karte hai, jab bhi kabhi tu ise fir se padh raha ho, tu kaafi succesful ho gya hoga.
author: Naman Agrawal (M Agrawal)

text: Hello bhai, toast hone ke baad ab kuch likhne ki zarurat toh nhi, par tab bhi to save the memories in this book. You have always been very dedicated to anything you do. Bas ek baat hai. Koshish ke baavjood bhi kuch na milne par confidence mat khoya kar. Result = HardWork (80%) + Luck (20%). You do hard work but luck is not always in favour of everyone. It is the truth. We should keep trying. It is the best. Wish you a happy journey.

author: Nitesh

text:
1. Hi Betty,
Let's start with Google :P
Though we were only two seats away, it took us two semesters to finally cross paths (condition, both of us being aware, C-Mid out of reach :P). Oh, I wish now I should have been more courageous, bas 2 kadam hi to chalna tha. Life me probably har cheez end me ki, har kaam me late hua, but oh I swear, agar kismat-e-khuda fir mauke ne dastak di, is baar time pe a jaunga, is baar nahi aalas karunga. 

Kya me ye kehke flirt kar sakta hu, ki "T.T. to bas ek bahana tha, apse milne ka irada tha :P", theeke, might not work, but tujhse bura T.T. shayad hi koi khelta tha. But ngl, that summer camp changed my campus life a big swing, not to forget orientation lol, bacho ki ragging nahi leni ati tujhe. 
Post that, mostly hi hello aur apke thermo ke quiz mere dwara likhe jane tak, itna hi interaction ho gaya tha mostly. But, Diwali's have always been eventful for us, haina ;). From that to numerous trip plans, cancellation, boredom, Naman ke maze lena, late-night random texts, time flew. But I am glad we went to Offline on the Roof that day; that broke the ice (both literally and metaphorically), didn't it. 

I still can't believe I ignored you for a complete sem :P, I am still ashamed for that. But, now that I remember, that led us to our first time alone in C.C.D., with me being caught by the very prof I bunked class of X.D. Sorry for the messed up intern call, I wish I could go back, need to make few blocks fall in place. But, post that, the reunion was bound to happen with me in my worst state, at the best possible location, for the worst possible topic (oh, we know what moment are we talking off, I'll save myself the embarrassment of making it public here). They say everything happens for a purpose, I might now have figured it back then (yes, I am slow, especially in your case, remember hall 12 se 6 takes me 30 mins :P), but now that I look back at that moment, I indeed find my best friend bearing me at my worst (again, metaphorically and literally :P).

From that to Hall 4 wala gyan, to "duniya hi badal do me to pyara sa chamatkar hu", and then to that unplanned Antaragni night, I think our lives finally started to obey the laws of thermo. What a living manifestation of the butterfly effect that event was. Not every day I miss flights, not every day we bilk 3k worth of drinks :P. So these events officially mark your presence in 2/3 impactful events of my college life. Needless to say, you have always been this special, right :P. Sorry for messing up your birthday really bad. I was never good with birthdays :(. Next time pakka better.
 

Spring brought about spring in our lives too, haina? Chalo firse waise hi rehte h? Probably the best time we had, things sailing like the titanic, but little did we knew that CoVID ka iceberg was closer than it appeared. I am so glad we went to Manali, agar wo kat gaya hota to kise hi pata tha age ka. And I regret missing that opportunity, and then our "8 Jan" happened X.D. I still regret not running behind your cab at hotel samrat :(. 

Post that, to numerous cheeze hui. I messed up big (read every) time; kudos to my bad social (read virtually social) skills. But I can't really justify on text how supportive you were. Love you 3000 for that. We saw through every thick and thin, so much so that now we might as well qualify as living proof of the 3rd law of thermodynamics ;). The entropy of our system decreased, and for good :)

Sorry for Goa, but my first visit to Jaipur involved my two best friends couldn't have been better. I wanted to come back sahi me that day, but you knew my halat. Though, 8 Jan will always be special. And then that tiny but beautiful period on the campus. Literally everything falling apart in terms of rules at campus, kuch cheeze reh gai, bahot moments choot gaye, but it was soooooo gooooooood till it lasted. I promise I am the same milestone, just that it needs some polishing. I will be the same :)

Songs have always been special to us. (we didn't choose our yet, the onus on you now) 
But, so quickly life went from "There for You" ---> "Perfect" ---> "The Middle" ---> "Stay". Let's take it to "Love Story" now? :P 

This marks the end of this long pending memoir, but mark my words if nothing else. We still have lots of time, my list of movies, sorry cards and education to catch up on, hopefully (like really) together <3

P.S. I know I am late again..., nth time after the deadline, but I kept my promise, I managed to get things in place. Hopefully, this is the last time I'll use this superpower :P. Also, that "1" has significance X.D.

P.P.S. Here's the answer to some recent question/s posed to me: 
From "Back to You" Lyrics: 2nd para first two lines + 3rd para last four lines.

Yours,
Jug with
Googly, Boogly, Bush, Piglet, Hamster and Baby Yoda
author: Nitik  Jain

text:
Hi Anirudh,

I came in touch with you through Eclub. I recall our time together in InterIIT tech meet 2018 at IIT B.  We had participated together in the Engineers conclave.  That day spent with you and Jay was really fun.  I was expecting you to continue in Eclub as a coordinator from Hall 5.   In 4th sem, we did our TA202 project and ESO203 lab together.  We did not connect much in 6th and 7th sem though. I am glad that I could connect with you again in 8th sem while collaborating on AML course project.  Hope that you will stay in touch. All the best for your future endeavors.
author: Nitish Vikas Deshpande

text:
Hi Ankit,

I was fortunate to have you as my roommate in first year.  I remember that our room 324 and Ashok's bed in the middle was mostly occupied by Apurv who used to bring all the electronics stuff in our room.  We went through the ups and downs in our first-year courses together. I remember that your 1st sem endsem exams had got over before mine and I had two papers left but with a gap of 3-4 days.  You, me, and Ashok had watched around 7 movies together that night before my exam.   Some of them which I remember well are "Fantastic Beasts and where to find them", "The Arrival", "Lucy". I became so engrossed in having fun that night, I did not do any practice for TA101 lab exam and ended up with the only B grade in my first sem.  

We lost contact after our first year when both of us decided to change roommates.  Even our rooms were on the two extremes of 4 mid wing. I hope that you did well after your first year. Hope that we might connect sometime in the future. All the best for your future endeavors.
author: Nitish Vikas Deshpande

text:
Hi Jay,

Although we were a part of Eclub since our first year, I really felt connected to you during the period before coordi interviews.  I recall that we were given several tasks like club cleaning and bringing in new furniture. These were the first tasks that we did together as prospective coordinators (All thanks to Abhigyan who made us collectively do these tasks to build our bonding). 

You are the most creative person in our club. You were the face of Eclub managing the important role of publicity. Your poster designing skills are amazing.  I recall you taking a lot of effort to create the poster for the E4U initiative. Almost all posters and website designing were managed by you.  Your name will go down in history for redesigning the club website (https://students.iitk.ac.in/eclub/).   

Although our last meet was before covid pandemic started, we have been connecting virtually on various occasions. The last time we connected was for the Eclub coordi interview for Y19 batch. Hope that we will reunite some time in the near future. All the best for your future endeavors.
author: Nitish Vikas Deshpande

text:
Hi Kanishka, 

Thanks for being a part of my journey here.
We met first time in the E club winter camp. I recall that our first project together was creating an egg basket game in processing software where the basket was controlled using Arduino and ultrasonic sensors. We also made an application using Android Studio. 

I am amazed by your knowledge of places to visit on the campus. Before I met you, I was not aware of sites like the oxidation pond behind OAT and the IIT K nursery at the end of the road to the auditorium. 

I was glad that you continued in the E club after the summer project on Skin Track. We jointly conducted many events for the club. Even after your tenure as a secy was over, you remained in touch with club activities. I recall that you had borrowed the LED strip from the club to celebrate your friend's birthday. You are really good at organizing surprise birthday celebrations for your friends. I recall that you had planned my birthday celebration in the Lecture Hall complex in my third year (However, it was not a surprise for me since you had invited Apurv, who leaked the info about your planning)


Although we didn't do many courses together, the one course we did together was the ENG course by Prof Ravichandran on "Literature and the Individual." I recall that we had rehearsed the debate of Kafka's " The metamorphosis." The debate was supposed to be on the spot, but prof never realized that we had decided our points-counterpoints beforehand! 

It is great that you, too, have plans to pursue graduate studies in the US. I hope that we will meet sometime soon. I will be happy to help you with your grad school applications.
All the best for your thesis work here and all future endeavors.
author: Nitish Vikas Deshpande

text:

Anyways, I hope that you were able to devote time to pursue your other interests and I hope that you did not regret quitting ERA. 

Our areas of interest are quite different now.  I hope that you will keep in touch.  All the best for your future endeavors.
author: Nitish Vikas Deshpande

text:
Hi Mudit, 

Our interaction started with collaborating on the problem statement by BARC in our first Techmeet at IIT B. Remember those nights that we spent together in Hall 12 sitting in front of PIR sensor. Some funny events that I recall during our presentation at IIT B was the cup of tea spilling on the judge which led to our team getting extra time for the presentation.  The best part was our chat on the messenger group with Suraj, Abhigyan, Ashok. Might go through the chat to relive the experience of Techmeet once again !

The next memorable part was our second trip to Mumbai for presenting the prototype to BARC. We were fortunate to have connected with our alumni Sumit Chowdhury who later met us in Hall 12 canteen during his visit to IIT K.

We were really hoping to get a gold medal for the Roorkee edition by BARC/ Alphonso.
Unfortunately, this event was a closed-door event and we missed all the fun that we had in Mumbai. 

We have been through ups and downs together in our Eclub journey. Thanks for always supporting me in my crazy visions for club. One last thing that we missed was our project on Crazyflie which had to be discontinued due to covid. Our batch will be remembered as the one which revolutionized the club. Not only did we bring in new initiatives, we also renovated the club and redesigned the club website. 

Your tenure as Gensec will also go down in history for bringing back the title of Techmeet winners. Hope that all four of us will have a chance of reunion some time in the future.
author: Nitish Vikas Deshpande

text:

text:

One of the funniest parts was recording the video for the challenge. If you still have the video saved in your drive, please DM me the video. 

I recall the night before the E club coordi interview when we were brainstorming over the million dollar question of "How to keep track of the components in E club?"  Even after completing my tenure as coordinator, I haven't figured out a solution yet!   

During my tenure as coordi, many of my decisions were influenced by you in terms of deciding a project for club or purchasing any new component. Thanks for your ideas and support for Eclub.  Hope that our paths will cross in the future!  All the best for your future endeavors.

I specifically recall EE370 and our interaction with Prof. Iyer.  You always had your lab sessions in EE381 before my labs. I used to call you every week before my lab to get the pre-lab sheet done.

Another reason I felt connected with you was that you lived in room 234 in your third year which also happens to be the room that I had lived in my second year.  Technically, I happen to be your bed-baap!

Although our areas of interest have diverged since 6th semester, I hope to stay in touch with you in the future. All the best for your future endeavors.

text:

Remember the cab that we took from campus to the airport when we were going home for vacations in March 2020.   You had asked me whether we need to worry if our internships in the US will be affected because of covid.   At that time, covid had just reached India and we were still traveling without any mask.  Many things changed after that week.  We had received the mail from TAMU that our internships had been rescinded.  All our plans of spending time together at TAMU were ruined. If not for covid, I am sure that we would have connected really well.   Anyways, keep in touch. Our paths will definitely cross in the future.  All the best for your future endeavors.

Do you remember that I used to approach you every year after midsem exams to borrow your harddisk which had a great collection of movies. I had copied the movies from your drive. I even have a folder named "Movies from Shivam" saved in my PC. I will remember you the most whenever I watch movies from your collection.

Anyways, hope that we will connect again soon.

text:

text:

text: Hey Captain! Sorry for leaving the team. For the little time I was in the team, I enjoyed a lot only because of you. You pushed me to come to all the treats with you and socialise with the team members. You introduced me to the people who'll be my friends for life just like you. You are a really good friend, and IMO the best captain. You were the initial motivation for me to get out of my shell and do something notable. I wish that I could be there for you as much as you were there for me. Thank you for everything!

text: Yo! We finally made the door opener, be it for a garage or a barrage. I had fun distributing all the work to other group members and doing the negligible work with you. Thanks for introducing me to the "you're a wizard Harry" video and reviving the "chithi chithi Robot" song a night before the scariest exam of my life. Now that I'm looking back at our moments together, I feel like we were together in so many moments at IITK ( TA group, surge, eng123, philosophy, cult meet, and many more courses) and I never realised that we spent a lot of time together. The coincidences of the "coincidental trio" never actually stopped. Looking forward to more such coincidences!

author: Nupur  Mehra

text:
Hey brother!
Do you remember advising me to do my homework regularly in Reso? I did follow your advice for some time, and then we came to IITK and I never did my homework by myself again.
You were so serious in Reso, me and Disha Bhatia we're too scared of sitting with you. Then we met on the Audi stage and that was a completely different you! You are as cool as you are hard-working.
All the best for your future and I hope to see you with your clothes inside out again!
author: Nupur  Mehra

text:
You're a wizard Manisha!
What kind of magic did you use to become the sweetest person in the world?
There are only a few people who can make me talk about my problems and you are one of them. You should note it down under your big achievements list. Thank you for listening to me, supporting me and decorating my bed with so many rose petals and toffees! No other roommate could have been so artistic with my bed.
I'll always be here to listen to you and support you and make you cook something for me. I hope all of your problems vanish and you have a great life ahead.
author: Nupur  Mehra

text:
Got to bond with you in the last few months of IITK only. It was fun to make those bum prints on the wall. You are a really good choreographer, you made that weird leg kicking step look so easy.
Why didn't we met sooner??????
Let's continue the drunk talk we started on the terrace!
author: Nupur  Mehra

text: Naman Roshan, you can never be trusted for taking care of a person in a bad hangover. You can also not be trusted for taking good photographs. But you can be trusted for being a good friend! You always came to hang out with me whenever I called you. You were always there, never too busy for me, and never ghosted me. Also, if I have played TT 100 times, then the 99 times was with you. I love to make fun of you, but you should know that I'll never intentionally hurt you. Also, you should know that you're one of my best friends. Will meet you soon!
author: Nupur  Mehra

text:
Hey Jug,
If I could start over these four years again, the only thing I'll change is to meet you sooner. Right from the first day of orientation, I'll get two seats closer to you. Then, we could have had more trips to jail and a hell lot of Friday nights. You turned me from a beast to a princess without me capturing you into my Castle. You're the most selfless, loving, caring and warmest ( literally warmer than our hot water bag) guy I've met. Still, I had my chilliest kiss with you. It will always come to my mind whenever I'll smell snow. Even your roses never had the thorns but only the sweetest fragrance of blueberries. Thank you for all the beautiful moments you curated for me, for being so selfless and loving, and for being in my life forever.
This is the end of my college but not the end of us. I'm never letting you get away from me.
Yours,
Betty.
author: Nupur  Mehra

text:
I remember we had to make a group for TRC's course. I showed the list of the students enrolled in the course to Nitik and asked him to recommend someone. He recommended you, saying that you're too hardworking (no doubt about it). Hence, I asked you out for the group and I'm so glad that we did it together. Our group meetings were more of a laughter session! 
I had no contribution to the project except finding the book and calling the meetings, my write-up work was done by the "senior member" of our group himself. 
I really enjoyed making fun of TRC's habits for the first "off" of the course with you guys! I hope that you achieve the highest level of happiness in your life and also gain high spiritual capital!
Also, were you invisible in the orientation? The seat beside me always looked empty to me.

text:

Remember how we started stealing the clay from the ESO lab just to pass those 3 long hours? And how we used to find different shapes on the surface of those metals which we had to draw? That was in a way just like finding shapes in the clouds. I was able to be my childish self again with you.
We have done so many stupid things in the labs together, like playing with the rubber gloves in the UOP lab, drilling in pencils and chalks in the TA lab. 
I wish to do such stupid things with you on a larger scale in the future. Let's level up this cool stuff we do next time we meet!

text:
High 5?
This was probably the first thing we bonded on. I have always enjoyed wandering with the camera and you. The time in Bombay was probably the peak of our friendship till now. Watching the sunset quietly next to you, I think that we were talking with each other at that time without speaking anything. Do you think the same? That moment was a really special moment for me. All our trips and photo walks were memorable, especially the Banaras one. Although I used to get mad at you at times when you would ghost us during the club work. But those were temporary things. I hope that our friendship stays forever.
Also, we should go on a trip together soon!

Baaki mtlb itne ache se summarise kiya hai naa tune mere memoir pe, icha kr rhi wahi copy-paste maar du (doosre memoir me krti hu). Bas yrr koi photo nhi hai saath me uss time ki, regret rahega wo hamesha. Kisi bhi participant ki koi dikkat hoti thi, I was like thike naa yrr koi ni dekh lenge, but tu poori headache apne sur leke kaam krta tha. Day3 nhi bhool sakte kabhi bhi, BC mote ne kya confuse krke rakha hua tha, 3 baar scheduling krwayi thi, fir bhi chod hue the agle din. Baaki Ratnesh ki lene me aaj bhi utna hi fun aata hai, or ye topic hamesha common rhega jab bhi milenge (sorry Ratnesh, agar tu ye pad raha hai to). Best decision tha Shivam ka jo tjhe Nationals ka manager nhi banaya tha, warna itni bakchodi shayad naa ho paati, hehe. Anyway, aise hi humesha bakchod or bindass rehna. Kabhi milte hai wapas. I don't think I have ever told you this, but I admire your strength. Maybe I haven't helped you a lot in your elections (sahi me door rehna tha yrr mjhe unn sabse), but I always respected you for being so brave and fearless, and for always standing up for what you believed. Respect man.

text:
PR calling Festi!!
Yaar teri first memory naa 1st year ki hai, jab tu Katiyar ke liye birthday card banane GH ayaa tha, lol (Am I allowed to openly say this?). Hamesha ye discussion kaafi hota tha humara ki kaafi similar ho tum dono, literal bhai lagte ho.
Anyway, uske baad Antaragni'19 ke baad ig diwali ke baad call aata hai tera, bro milna hai kuch gadbad ho gyi. BC bhand hoke chhoti ko bata diya tha tune, meri fati nhi thi, but jis tareeke se tu express kr rha tha, aisa lag rha tha ki fatni chahiye. Uske baad to yrr fir CORE TEAM, alag feels, alag expectations, or kaafi jyada enthu. Enthu to ussi se yaad aata hai jo "KAIROS" naam pe kitna jyada discussion hua tha, lol. But, ek point aane ke baad, enthu kaafi down ho gaya tha. Tune or Shrey ne hi milke sambhala tha poora, placements ke baad sbko jinda kiya, or fir karali BC (wo feel nhi hai, but apni Antargni thi yrr). Bohot jyada miss kiya maine, jo hall-12 me saath milke kaam or bakchodi ki hai tum logo ne (photos or videos aa rhi thi mere paas regularly), or jo final night bhand hue ho tum log. Goa trip jldi plan karo yrr, saath me bhand hona hai BC (OAT ki tarah nhi hopefully). Dukh kaafi raehga on-ground Antaragni naa hone ka, jitna expected tha utni bond nhi ho paayi me team me, but at the end kya hi kar sakte hai. Khair kaafi BT hai meri udhar. Anyways, umeed hai Goa me jld hi milenge. Tab tak Take Care, or apna enthu or feel humesha aisi hi rakhna!!

Me pehle kaafi sad thi D dekhke, lekin tere aate hi saara dukh khatam ho gya, kyuki kuch jyada hi bura hua tha tere saath, hahaha!!
Doosri memory obviously econometrics ki. Tune, maine or Kiran ne 1 ghanta pehle library me milke jo midsem me chaapa tha. Wo kaale, takle, mote ko to kabhi bhool hi nhi sakte, endsem me badla nikaal liya tha usne. But thike grade acha lag gaya tha uss course me, lol. 
Bhai tere saath Somesh ko galiyaane me kaafi jyada majjaa aata hai, dil se nikalti hai uske liye to gaaliyan. Manali trip to kaise hi bhool sakte hai. Kaafi sexy trip thi wo. Bas ye corona hate, next trip pakka Ladakh ki hai. Guide se setting krke aaye hi the hall-13 me aane se pehle. Jald hi milte hai. Tab tak apne HR ko jyada mat tang krna, BC nikaal dega, lol. Chal Take Care!!
author: Palak  Agrawal

text:
Yo Maitreyee!!
Sbse pehle, I want to say a very very big THANK YOU to you, for forcing me to become the pool captain in 2nd year galaxy. For me, that was a lifetime experience, and I would not have known what I would have missed if I have not actually done that. Kaafi majja aaya that yrr uss time tere saath kaam krke. Sahi me pyaar aa jata that kabhi kabhi to ekdum hi (for reasons I guess you might be very well aware of, lol). 
Uske alawa I don't think we share a lot of memories, but I do respect you as a person. 
Hope you will rock the same way in your future as well.  Take Care!!

P.S.: I think the most we bonded was on the word "SHAURYAS", and the zeel to always protect it!! <3 <3

author: Palak  Agrawal

text:
Dekha aaj hi daanta tune, or aaj hi memoir aa gya, lol. But yrr, kya karu jab tak deadline ekdum sur pe nhi aa jaati naa kuch kaam ho nhi paata hai. Lekin chalo aapke liye aaj ache se mood banake likh dete hai.
Yaar terese jo sbse badi shikayat hai wo ye hai ki tu bohot jyada patli hai. Tere saath sahi me photo khichana acha nhi lagta mjhe, bc complex ho jaata hai, hehe. Baaki yrr kuch bhi chahiye ho pata hota hai Manisha ke room pe milega. Kaafi kum baar hi aisa hua hoga ki tere room pe paani peene aao, kuch khaane aao, yaa kuch bhi lene aao naa mila ho. Room pe to chhodo, hall-13 ki canteen me bhi kuch chahiye ho to inn madam ke paas sab milega. Baaki poori wing me savage to bas ek tu or me hi the, hahahaha. Bhai hapan dono ek team me ho jaayein to fir, koi ni aa sakta saamne, especially Chitranshi, hehe. Baaki sab kr rhe to room ki bhi tareef kr hi deti hu teri. Wo wall yrr, itni jyada sexy, mtlb jab paint kr rhi thi naa tabhi majja aa gya tha dekhke. Baaki yrr kaafi mehnati hai tu, mtlb meri sahi me dil se icha hai ki tu creative field me kuch kar. Kaafi jyada hi chaapti ho dost tum uss field me. Haan, ek baat or tera wo class ke time laash ke jaise sona hamesha yaad rhega. Mtlb madam raat ko bolke so rhi ki please yrr subah bohot important class hai, koi jage to please jaga dena. Subah room pe jao, gala phat jaaye insaan ka chillate chillate, isko bed se uthake neeche phenkdo, chaahe kuch krlo, majaal hai jo agar madam ki icha nhi hai to uth jaaye wo, lolololol (laptop me emoji nhi aa rhe, to aise hi expressions dikhaane pad rhe, hehe). 
Kaafi jyada lamba ho gaya yrr, chalo kuch yaad aaya or to ek or me likh denge. Teri Udaipur ki trip baaki hai ek, aana kabhi. Baaki milte rehna, or haan bina mask ke bahar mat nikalna, lol (kuch nhi bas yuhi bakchodi). Take care!! <3
P.S.: mere room pe wo Antaragni ka symbol reh gaya :(
P.P.S.: Tu humare wing ki Godmother thi hai or humesha rahegi
P.P.P.S.: Tjhe pata nhi hai par tu hai
Special mention: WHITE SAUCE PASTAAA, kyuki uske bina tera memoir poora ho hi nhi sakta <3
author: Palak  Agrawal

text:
Yo Neha!!
First sem with you and Yashika was fun. We were not much in touch after that, but thanks for being one of the greatest behen for me. Man, you play amazing volleyball, abhi last ke dino me hi dekha maine to, lol. Anyway, all the best for your future, I am sure you will do great. Take care!!
author: Palak  Agrawal

text:
Yo Nikita!!
Yaar kaafi fun loving insaan hai tu!!
Hall-1 me majja aaya tha tere saath, but teri wo placement waali story, how you coped up with everything was real inspiring. Baaki be the same fun loving person that you are, not caring about what anyone thinks. Baat krke fun aata hai tere saath. Haan kabhi Bangalore aao to treat le lena dost, hum to ready hai dene ke liye. Hoping that our paths might cross some day again, tab tak Take Care!!
P.s.: please reconsider Thanya's suggestion.
author: Palak  Agrawal

text: Yo Nilay! You were obviously the worst lab partner one could ask for, but yrr tere saath bohot sahi vibe match hoti thi. First year ke baad we lost much contact, obviously I was so busy, and tu hamesha ki tarah khaali hi hoga I know. But first sem me kaafi majje kiye the, from making everyone jealous in PHY lab (bcz of apni alag bakchodi), to missing that coke studio in Antaragni, and to me escaping every treat you have ever asked for (hehe), I enjoyed your company (aisa bolna padta hai). Hopefully ab flirt krna seekh gaya hoga tu, bandi to nhi hi banne waali hai terese, to flirting ka hi sahara hai, lol. Wishing you a great future babe. Also Rajasathan me bohot paani hai (iykwim). Take Care!!
author: Palak  Agrawal

text:
Yo Nipun!!
Yaar literally online sems dono teri wajah se nikale hai, warna kya hi hota hum saare namuno ka, hehe. Pehla nasha tune hi karaya tha, with that 10 rs waali bhaang ki goli. Chadhi nhi mjhe though, but pehla try ussi din tha. Baaki yrr kabhi bhi kuch bhi chahiye ho, DS ke solutions se lekar Somesh lodu ke assignments tak or bhang ki goli tak, sabme hamesha teri yaad hi aati hai sbse pehle. Baaki yrr drameve1, summer workshop sab was kaafi fun. Hopefully wo case interviews iss saal kaam aayenge. Trip pe chalte hai kabhi ECO waalo ke saath. Always be the hard-working and helping person that you are. Placements me please tang kr lena. Milte hai kabhi. Take Care!! 

P.S.: Anarkali kon hai??

Yo Nupur!!
Yaar tere saath meri best memory is arranging 3rd year diwali at FMC room. Kaafi majja aaya tha uss time, wahan jhaadoo nikalne me, lights lagane me, chhota sa mandir (well, sort of) banane me. Yaar 2nd year galaxy me tjhe nhi pata, alag pressure tha yrr mjhpe. Isiliye agar kuch ulta seedha bola ho to gile shikwe maaf karein. Baaki majja aaya tha uss galaxy me tere saath kaam krne me, especially FMC room me wo apple waale shoot me, bhai alag shit thi yrr wo, bohot mushkil se shot aaya tha wo. Rest, it was fun sharing FMC room with you for that year, wo jo tune Parth ko room se bhaga diya tha jab wo match dekh raha tha, epic bhai epic, lol. Uske baad se darr lag gaya tha ki FMC me kuch ulti seedhi harkat nhi krni bilkul bhi. Rest, it was fun interacting with you. Stay happy, stay sexy. Take Care!! <3
author: Palak  Agrawal

text:
Nanaaaaa!!
Haan sahi baat hai tune kabhi 'moti' nahi bola, but tune naa kuch naya naam invent kiya tha mera. Yaad hai, nhi yaad to me dilaati hu: "HIDIMBAAAA". Kyu mtlb kyu tha wo??
First year ki DoAA visits to alag hi special thi. But yaad hai 1st year ki DE. Dono ko krna tha, par himmat nhi ho rhi thi. Ek doosre ke aupport se hi pahuche the. And then wo epic DE ki treat. Seniors sabko puch rhe continue karoge yaa nhi, sab haa haa kr rhe, sirf tu or me muh pe mana kr diye the unko, hehe. Baaki chuhiya ke bhai ki shaadi, first year summer ki dance workshop, kaafi fun bhai. Bohot bakchodi ki thi yrr saath me, but fir kaafi serious sa ho gaya tha tu, lol. Anyway, milte hai yrr kabhi. Tere bhand hone ke baad ki harkaton ke kisse kaafi sune hai, kabhi live dekhne hai. Aise hi chaapte or naachte rehna. Take Care!!
author: Palak  Agrawal

text:
Yo Pooja!!
Bhai kaafi shaant ladki. Saari beheno me to thi hi, but I guess poore Y17 me sbse jyada shaant tu hi rehti thi. Anyway, tere saath majja aaya yrr basketball khelke. Or wo kuch random cheezein, jaise ki water park waali trip, all that was fun too. Hopefully thoda bolna seekh jaaye tu, and all the best for your future. Take care!!
author: Palak  Agrawal

text: Yo Katiyar!! Yrr tu pata hai bohot pyaara insaan hai. Ek baar tjhe thanks bolna tha, uss din jo tune peene se roka tha naa, shakal yaad hai teri mjhe aaj bhi. Khud nashe shuru kr diye the tune thode time me hi, but koi naa maaf kiya. But pehli baar bhand hui thi me to wahi yaad kar rhi thi. First year ki summers me kaafi majje kiye the, especially wo "isse kehte hip hop hip hop" dance waali worshop. Also wo church yaad hai, jo legit katwaya tha wahan jaake xD, kaafi fun time tha yrr wo. Wahi baatein yaad aa rhi hai ab. Chalo koi naa, hopefully waise majje krenge fir, or iss baar saath me baithkar peeyenge, lol. Take Care!!<3
author: Palak  Agrawal

text: Yo Ramola! Probably one of the most helping and passionate guy I have met in the campus. Baaki interests kaafi similar se the apne: dramatics, basketball, Antaragni, galaxy and film club. It was fun to interact with you on various occasions. Hopefully ab Axis Bank ke vlogs jald hi dekhne ko milenge, XD. Haan ek baat or, Aakanksha di se jab bhi baat hoti hai, ek baar teri yaad jaroor aati hai, hehe. All the best for your future, hope you achieve great heights in your career. Take care!!
author: Palak  Agrawal

text:
Yo Ritika!!
Bhai sbse pehli memory apni Manali Trip. I guess tabhi se apni bonding start hui thi, usse pehle tak just jaante the ek doosre ko. But that trip is something I will cherish forever. Uske baad bhi 2nd year me we bonded over courses and some random Eco waalon ke saath treats. Bohot jyada touch me nhi the always, but fir jab bhi baat hoti thi to wo hamesha kaafi jyada lambi khichti thi, and it was always fun. 
But bhai, I respect you for doing all those khatarnak waale courses, to which people like me always stayed away from, lol. And the good part is you are such a hard working person that tu unn courses me bhi somehow kaafi chaap leti hai. Anyway, kabhi Bangalore aana to jaroor milna, job lagwali agar waha to or bhi badiya, hehe. All the very best for your future. I am sure you will do great. Take care!!
author: Palak  Agrawal

text:
Hello Shamra ji!!
Aapko kaise bhool sakte hai, aap to zindiagi bhar dil me rakhne waali cheez ho. Academics ke alwa yrr jyada kuch common tha nhi apna, to isliye humesha jab bhi assignment chahiye, notes chahiye, exams or quizzes me answer chahiye, sbse pehla text tere paas jaata tha mera. Naatak to me bas aise hi bakchodi me krti rehti thi, lol. Deep down, I knew ki tu kabhi mana nhi krega. A very BIG THANK YOU for that. Also yrr Udaipur aane ka plan tha hi to thoda pehle batadeta, dates adjust kr lete hapan. Koi naa, agar Geetanjali College waala tera kaam ho gaya hoga to aate rhenge aap to fir ;). Humko jaroor yaad kr lena jab bhi aao. Rest chaapu to tu hai hi, umeed hai aage bhi aise hi chaapte rahoge. Chaapu ke alawa, you have a very big and beautiful heart, don't ever change that. Hopefully jald hi milenge. Take care!!

Yaar Antaragni'19 me kaafi kaam kiya tha saath me abithke, but terese wo epic all team meet hi yaad aati hai, literal "BE LIKE SHIBALIK" feels. Anyway, all the very best for your future, I am sure you touch great heights. Hopefully, fir milenge kabhi. Take Care!!
Over and Out!!

text:
Aaishi yaar kya likhu ab mai tere baare mein. Chalo purani baate yaad karte hai. Pehli baar tu mila tha 3-top pe tab mujhe yaad hai tu jo bolta tha bohot logo ko samaz nahi aata tha par mujhe aata tha. Tujhe dekh kar hi laga ki yaar ye aadmi apna aaacha dost ban sakta hai. Baate karte rahe tab ek din dhoni related fact share kiya tune wing wale group pe tab pata chala ki tu dhoni fan hai tab toh saare taar jud gaye aur kya hi chahiye tha firğŸ˜‚. Mujhe yaad hai usi din class k bahar mila aur maine tujhe pucha tha tu bhi dhoni fan hai aur tune bola haan fir apan mast baate karte karte hall gye the Sath mein CSK ki matches dekhte the wo toh nhi bhulunge kabhi. Fir toh sabse accha time aaya apna sath mein jab galaxy mein dance karne k liye gye. pehle din se mujhe yaad hai har chiz mein sath rehte the... streching ,warm-up, running sab mein sath me rehte the. sath mein sikhe sab. yaad hai wo pehla din jab bohot dance kar liye fir chalna mushkil ho gya tha stairs chadne mein kya haalat ho rhi thi. fir jab galaxy jeete tab kitne maze kiye sath mein uske baad aur achhe dost ban gye apan. But sadly every good time has an end. Apne raaste alag ho gye q ki tu gaya SAE mein aur mai reh gya dance mein. Mujhe hamesha lagta tha dance karte waqt ki mai akela hu koi sath nhi(jab tak sashwat nhi aaya lekin wo bhi saala late aaya kaafi). Mujhe bhi le jaata yaar SAEğŸ˜¥ğŸ˜¥ sath mein kaam karte. Fir toh 2 saal milna kam ho gya kaafi bas wing mein kabhi kabhi milte theğŸ˜­ğŸ˜­. Fir abhi time mila hai sath mein jab dono dual kar rhe. One of the best friendships developed at IITK. One person whom I can really really trust. You are more like an elder brother to me. 
Some of our memories together - 
Hmare thane (E512) m tm Pandey, hm Bajirao aur Nipun havaldaar hua krta thağŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚. 
Waise to hm nahi darte h, par us din you got me. (#Bloodyà¤®à¥‡à¤°à¥€). btw, BKL b dr gaya thağŸ˜‚
E512 (7-RCR) m kabutar ka romance. 
Nipun k sath prankğŸ˜‚. Pehle hm msg kiye fir tm kiye fir hm kiye aur tmne BKL s pucha kaa be muskura rhe ho? Nipun be like- bhai koi h. Us be like - Ohhh bhaaai Ohhh bhaaai Chaapa. CongratsğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚
First year m Shivam ko maggie party s block krne k liye Saavan Gang ka gathan kia tha.
Kitni baar hm aur Nipun class k liye nikal gaye room lock krke aur baad m pata chalta tm naha rhe the.
Wing m sbhi room k baahar swastik bana kr bure saaye ko bhagana ğŸ˜‚
Wo Loco party @ CCD
Mujhe GPL s bachane wala contract.
Tmhara wo chal be Canteen/ Canteen chalega. Hm to hmesha aate the ğŸ˜‚
Second year ki bakchodi. One thing I regret is that I couldn't make your CAD for TA. Gaadi banane m lg gaye the. Proper birthday parties to second year s shuru hui thi. @CCD or @Dominos or @MacD. Time kaise nikal gaya pata hi nahi chala. Third year aaya, bahut bakchodi ki. Tmhari intern party, fir PPO wali party.  Fir Covid aa gaya. Ghr pr mn nahi laga to aagaye tm se milne Lucknow.
Itne kisse h ki likh nhi paa rhe. Sach m bahut bakchodi ki h. Wo jignad ki roasting. Some Commonly used slangs - tum to badi tez ho be, aur be, chaapa, ohhh bhaaai.
At IITK, far from my home, I never felt homesick. I knew I have two brothers here who are always there for me. Although this is not a parting away story just a beginning to a lifelong friendship.
Covid khtm hote hi trip pr milte h.
Hmesha yaad karte rhenge, 
Tmhare Partho

text:
Bhai Mohit, tm yaar bade bakchod mitr ho hmare. ğŸ˜‚. Tm hm sb log k chotu ho. Bade seedhe aadmi bhi ho. IC s ladne k liye sada tat pr rhte ho. Hm jb bhi bor hote h, tmlog ka ldai bada enjoy krte h. Kabhi tmhari side lekr IC ki maarna. Kabhi vice versa."Bhag Panda teri to" bol diye honge ab tk to.
Goa m jo tm bed k liye roye the. Aaj bhi yaad h hmko. Usse bada r rona nhi dekha kabhi ğŸ˜‚. Koi ni hm badhappan dikha kr tmko wo bed dediye the. Goa ki bakchodi kya hi ginaye. Bahut bakchodi ki h workshop pr bhi. Ab zyada kch yaad to nhi itna samay ho gaya h. Tm hamesha s IC k sath magte the. rarely(shayd ek baar hi) hm tm log k sath chalte the, but ab sochte h jaana chahiye tha aur memories bn jati. Koi ni. wo workshop pr bakchodi krna. Central workshop pr kaam krna, Late night DoAA canteen, CCD pr treats, Airstrip pr gaadi daudana, bahut maza kiya h sath m. Log maan jaate to possibly hm log ek aur trip pr jaate. Hm to poora tayyari kr liye the but last m sb saanp log kat liye to hm kya hi krte, itna door s aana rhta aur koi nhi aa rha tha. Pr koi nhi. Covid khtm hote hi ek trip pr chalenge.koi nhi aaye to hm dono hi chal lenge. Suna h tm bade heavy trekker ho. Best of luck for future. Waqt sudharte hi milenge.

Aur be mitr - bhai - roomie - Aloevera - meri fake ID ka diwana/victim - mess wala - marwadi bhaisa (Not buffalo) - TAuaa wale (Ye hm nahi maante kyunki hm 2 saal drafter chalaye h)ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚. Aise to badi memories h pr kch likh hi dete h - 
Chaar saal pehle mile the, saath m classes jaana(Room lock krke when Pandey bathğŸ˜‚). L20 k middle section k peeche wale block m 4thi 5vi seedhi pr line s poora wing soya krta thağŸ˜‚. 
Tmko Taekwondo jaata dekh badi daya aati thi hmko. Hmare thane(E512) k tm hawaldaar jo the. Bada kaata h tmhara fake ID sğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ 
Bhai hm to dare the us din, Lekin tum zyada dare the. Bs tm uchal nahi paaye kyunki tmhara weight (us samay) mujhse zyada tha aur tm pnkhe k neeche the to air resistance bhi rha hoga. Jo bhi tha tm zyada dare the.ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚

Us waqt tmhari GK subhanallah. Bada maza aata tha jb Pandey tmko roast krta tha.

Tmhari campaigning kiye the. Tmko pata nahi ek baat ab batate h - Tmhari jb HEC dvara li jaa rhi thi, tb hm hmari ek fake id s election officer ko inform krke waha bhej diye the. Although wo kch nahi kia jo kehna h kaho, bachaye the tmko.
bahut memories h kya batayein
Roomie bhai. I have got the best ever roomies. Kabhi tm log s koi shikayat nahi hui. Koi duvidha aai to tm log s batiya lo. Cooler liye the. But yaad h summers m hm uske aage duct laga kr khud hawa lete theğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚. 
Mess secy roomie k faayde kya hi bataye. Rhne dete h galat prabhav padega. But bhai eternal thanks for dal baati. Dal baati is lub. Taste hi sahi khilaye the tm second year m.

Ek baat h tmko gariyane ki, hmko jo tm Chitral k poster banane m fasaye the. bc raat raat jagaya gaya tha mujhe. Wo treat bhi nahi diye hmko. (raaz ki baat - hm vote bhi nahi diyeğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ mazaak kr rhe h). pr koi ni seh liya thoda

After family, agr koi h to wo hmare mitr log h. You guys (You, Abhyuday) hold a very important role in my life. 4 saal ki memories ye yearbook h, but our friendship is everlasting. 
Yaad krte rahenge.

Priy draams wale mitr,
Hmara draaams k prati rukh sada s hi kathor raha h. pehla kaaran to BKL h. Tm log bhai mehnati hote ho, lab reports banwana ho to bana dete ho. baaki yaad nahi aa rhe.  Vaise to Mech m sath m hase aur roye h dono. Kayi labs m lab partners bhi rahe h. Heat Transfer wali lab yaad h. Lab ko jaldi s khtm karke. Canteen s chips aur samosa chai le kr agli class jaate the. 
TAuaa lab m bc FLYING DRAGON banaye theğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚. badi mehnat krke weld aur brazing ki thi chote parts ki. Last m check krte waqt bc chal hi nahi rha tha. Fati padi thi. side m tel ki bottle was a God's miracle. bc tel daalte hi makhkhan ki trh chal rha.
Yaad ho to check krne k baad usko full speed se chalakr check bhi kiye the nahi toota tha.
8th sem almost saare courses same the hm logo k. Pehle to wo course ki baat krenge jo hm dono n drop kiyağŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚. jo weekly r rona tha usme. Achcha h drop kr diye. Best wishes for future....

text:
Priy Priyakhee!
Tmse hm inspiration lete the kaam karne ka aur class attend karne kağŸ˜‚. Hamari gaadi to nahi bn paayi pr bahut maza kiya h designing m. Sabse pehle to chassis designing tk hm masti krte the sb kaam karte the, kyunki uske baad hi hmara bodyworks ka kaam shuru ho skta tha. Bhale Shukla ya Ritik ki bitching krni ho. ya fir kisi k sath prank krna ho. Bada maza kiya h tmhare sath. Chassis ki meshing krne ka dard hm samajh sakte hğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚. Fir tm log n final krdi Chassis. Hmne ek week m bodyworks design final krdi. Material selection aur Manufacturing process dekhne m alag dhandhali thi.ğŸ˜‚ Tm honeycomb selection wala kaam kr rhi thi, aur m CF vendors ko laalach dikha rha tha (Laalach kyunki 30m^2 CF bahut paisa hota h). Bahut chill maara h sath me. Hall 5 TV room, Reading room, Central Workshop, Library. Bahut brainstorming ki h sath m. Hm tum aur Shahid dimaag ghum jaata tha, Aluminium chassis aur CF bodypanels m.
Mostly saari classes m hm sae wale log sath m bethte the. JRK wali class to epic. jaldi aa jate the thoda to JRK k sath discussion krne beth jaate the kbhi kbhi.ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ Assignments ho ya lab reports hamesha madad ki h tumne. 
Wo small scale carbon fiber ka prototype yaad h, jo m, tm aur Shahid banaye the. First hands on experience tha carbon fiber k sath tm log ka.  Bs chakka lagane ki deri thi and voila, ek bachche ka khilona ban jaatağŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ Strong and expensive toy. 
Hm sb bahut treats pr gaye h. DoAA canteen, hall canteen, CCD, ramaiiya, farewell pr jaha chale the(Naam bhool gaye hm us jagah ka). Un sb m best to hmko wo lagti h jb M, Shahid aur tm room pr chana chor bana kr khaye the aur Jitesh ko photo bhej kr jalaye theğŸ˜‚ Alag s mess m jaakr vegies laye the. Mess worker bhi soch rhe the aaj bhaiya ko kya ho gya.ğŸ˜‚ Central workshop ka AC summer stay ko 5star kr deta tha. Jaldi aao aur late jaao. Aur waha beth kr ek taraf netflix dusre taraf solidworks/ansys. ğŸ˜‚ Bahut miss karte h un dino ko - tm sab ko. Bahut memories banayi h sath m. Wo yaad h CCD se wapas aate waqt ek puppy peeche pd gaya tha. Jaha jaate waha aa rha tha. Fir hm log strategically usko dusre dogs k area m le gaye aur wo bhaag gayağŸ˜‚ Whether it be SAE, Mech Labs or courses, or treats or market m material lene jaana(Ye hmko bilkul pasand nahi tha) bahut bakchodi ki h sath m. tmhare bio m ek baat pdh kr thoda dukh hua. Koi aisa vyakti ho jo aisa bolta ho to humko batana, dekh lenge usko. Lockdown m vaise bhi bahut pehelwan ho gaye h. You Shahid and me (Saini bhi tha) will always make a team. My journey at IITK is incomplete without you. We saw a dream and worked together to make our car, pragun. You were going to be our lightest driver. (For that you needed to gain some weight ). Best of luck.
-Parth

text:
Badal Bhai! 
You are one of the most trustworthy person, I met at IITK. A best friend indeed. Some memories down our lane -
First year k shuruaat m hm aur Pandey bade confused rhte the tm me aur Arihant m. ğŸ˜‚. Tm log ko baad m jaise jaise jaanne lage. waise waise samajhte gaye differences. Saath m Lecture hall jaate the. Wo L20 k mid section ki last wali stairs yaad rahengi.Hm hamesha tmhare pass betha karte the taki tm jaga do hmko biometric aane prğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ Hm log ka PE bhi sath hota tha. dukh dard k sathi hğŸ˜‚ ğŸ˜‚ ğŸ˜‚ 
Udghosh wali trip yaad h. Trip kyunki ghum kr hi to aaye the green park stadium (M,tm,Nipun,Shivam) ğŸ˜‚ koi kaam to nahi tha. 
Hm bhai bada special feel karte the jo tm hmko kuch raaz ki baat batate rhte the. Ab raaz ki baat yaha kaha daaleğŸ˜‚. Tmhari first year s bandi k kisse pure wing m prakhyat the. Although hm vegetarian h, tmhara chicken ka tyaag was appreciating. Mtlb kon hi dekhta tha but fir bhi. (bhabhi ji ko virtual pranam!) Tmhare Haryanvi roomie ki kya baat kare.  Hm regret krte hğŸ˜, First year Antaragni m usko uchal kr catch nhi kr paaye. Khair apne part ka gpl samajh liye hm vaise bhi nahi lete.

text:
Chalo hum bhi mention kar hi dete hai ki bhai ki DP me dusre hum hai aur hamara naam likha hai hamari cap pe  'N' for NANA. Aishwarya bhaaaii, the 'DEB' specialist. Bhai tu ek hi baar bolta tha aur wo bhi to the point bc. udta teer bhi nhi, teer nikla aishwarya ki kaman se aur ghus gaya jahan ghusana tha. teri chhavi to dimaag me wahi hai, sala thand me bhi half pant pehn kar aur shawl odkar ghumta hua aadmi. club ka koi bhi kaam ho, hum saare bc khush ho ya dukhi ho, tera sath to har jagah raha hi hai.

Meri maari to hai hi tune bahut, lekin IIT roorkey me jo pakadwaya bc, tera call nhi aata to logo ko kaano kaan khabar nhi hoti. tab to laga aishwarya bc mc harami, but abhi lagta hai  ki tune hi to kaam asaaan kiya <3. jab bhi koi problem janmi, koi na koi solution to aishwarya ne diya samjho. koi kaam karne ke liye mujhe chadhaya bhi tune hi hai ki "abe nana tum chapu ho, 15 ke pass tum jaaoge". convince to karhi leta tha kisi bhi baat pe. 

Ostwal ke room me chicken ki party, shukla ka chicken khana, mime madhu ki workshop aur use wapas bhejne ka locha, antaragnii ki BTyaan, senior-junior ke masle, hall12 ki bakchodiyaan (haa haan DJ khalid bhi), volleyball (main bhi khela hu bahut bar bhai), inn saari yaadonn ke liye thanks bhaiii <3. Bas college ke akhiri dino me bhi jud jaata to gham na hota ki last bye bolna reh gaya. 
all the best bhai aage aane wali har chunauti ke liye.

- Y17 Fakr hai ! (iska shrey to tera hi hai)

Aur thake haare tere wing me aake tere hi bed pe sona sahi lagta tha mujhe, rajai bakchod thi bc. apna jyada sa samay to 1st year ka beeta hai sath me, bc chhota sa baccha bade aadmi ke peeche chappal leke gaaliyaan bakte hue bhaag raha hai, wo to bhai yaad kar karke hasi aati hai. antaragni kari sath me aur mehengi kitabo ka chuna lagwa liya, abhi tak matter solve hua ya nhi pata nhi. chota packet bada dhamaka hai tu bhai!. galaxy me tera "ECS me G**d phategi, F lagega sabka bc" kehke darata rehta tha bc. aur orientation ka tera wo dialogue "hey dude, whats your problem man?" bhai tere se sahi to koi nhi karta x). saale chote se sharir me kitta ghussa bhar ke rakhta hai, yaad hai drameve 1 me 2ndyear me bc tune 1 bacche ko bhaga diya tha, wo aaj tak tujhe kosta hoga. 

chal jo bhi hai, bada accha banda hai tu lekin MC to tu bhi hai. choti umar me bade karname kar kar ke tum aise hi naam kamate raho. aur ummid hai fir mulakat hogi, tab tak ke liye alvida mitra
<3

text:

Aage jake kabhi bhi agar main college ke baare me yaad karunga, to pehla tu hi yaad aayega. Bhai har saaal room mate. Bade bhai ki tarah hai yaar tu. Meri kisi bhi baat pe comment to karta hi tha. Kuch galat karu to tokta bhi tha. Darwaza khula reh gaya to tu galiyayega, pankha shuru reh gaya to tu galiyaega, kuch samaan nhi milraha to tu galiyayega ğŸ˜‚, tere se behes karne me lekin maza bahut aata tha.

1st year me sabse pehle Rahul aur terese mila, tujhe dekhke ke to laga hi tha ki bada chaapu aur talented roommate mila per bc ESC aate aate pata chala, are ye to apna hi bhai haiğŸ˜‚. A ne B ko de diya to A khali ho gayaağŸ¤£ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£, bhai kitta hase the yaar ispeeğŸ˜‚ abhi bhi yaad karke hasi aati hai. 
Ek din aise hi ghumne nikal gaye, kya karna hai to garden ghumke aate, waha kheeche photos pata nhi kaha chale gaye. 1st year aisehi haste khelte nikal gaya. 2nd year tak tere hariyanvi aur punjabi gaano ki aadat lag gayi. Bahut sahi hai bhai tu, apni dhun me jeene wala, thoda selfish thoda determined, aur bahut sara humor ğŸ˜‚. Ummid hai ki fir milenge kahi to aur jaroor milenge. Stay happy as you are. Love you bhai â¤

text:
Loki man, bhai bada hi gajab aadmi hai yaar tu. Teri acting styles ke to bhai sabhi deewane hai aur improptu ke to alag se. ''Aur Chapu nana''  keh kehke lagta hai nana ke saamne chapu tune hi lagwaya.

pehli mulakat bhai apni 1st year galaxy, kya kya rap aur gaane ka remix banake laata tha (kuch kuch original bhi the, mana nhi kar raha) tab laga tha ki haan ye banda hall2 dramatics to bulandiyo tak pahuchayega. teri acting aur imprompts ka ek example yaad aaraha hai bhai, summer me apne ko judiciary pe nukkad banane bola tha. tu sutradhar bana tha, tera wo beech beechme 'suneil shety', nikal aana, wo thanos ke snap wala idea bhi tera hi tha. katai cringe bhai. fir play me to tumne acting ke jalwe dikyae hi "yaseen, ye tumhara hi kaam tha na". waise to play maine kam hi kiye hai, but ye accha hai ki 'cheema' (I guess chit-pinjar me yahi naam tha tera) ke sath me stage share karne ka mauka mila.

Apart from dramatics, terese gyaan ki baate bhi bahut mili. bc tu aur shukla milke pehle flow mere ko hi to samjhate the (dindor ko bracket me daal leta hu). mere sath aisa to kabhi hi hua ki kuch samajh nhi aaya to tere se 10 baar poocha aur tune politely nhi bataya ho. badi acchi acchi yaadein hai tere sath. aur unhi me ek hai bhai tera birthdayyyyyy yaaar. wo to special meri aur shukla ki hi treat thi samajhne me koi harz nhi. wo moments to bhule se nhi bhulunga. baaki to 3rd year galaxy wale din bhi bade majedaar the (loki man captain america bc :)))) 

khub aage badho bhai, jahan bhi jaaoge dhoom machaoge ye to sure hai. baaki milenge to sahi, aur milne ki jagah bambai ho too aur jyada accha hai. All the best bhaii <3.

text:
Ostwal bhaaaiiii.... tere sath ahi to waise bahut saari yaadein hai, per mujhe sabse accha lagta tha tere sath medly khadi karna, kya naye naye ideas laata tha bhai tu, " ye step itta hard kyu raknha hai?" aur tu "easy wala karne me kya maza". matlab sasti cheezo ka shouk to pehle se hi nhi tha, karna hai to bada karo. waise to shuru sehi chalu karna chaiye, per bc jangle java wala choreo karne me fati bhi thi lekin maja bhi bahut aaya tha, aur tune kaha tha "ye to nhi kat raha nana apna, kyunki apne siwa karne wala hi koinhi hai".

Antaragni se shuru karte. "na tere ghar me bijli hai na mere ghar me paani, raining cham cham ho rahi hai hum pe ye pareshani" x) xD ohhhhh bhaaaai tha to ye katai zeherrr, usi antargni ke dauran doaa pe bakchodi, chaukhat pe padhna, tera doaa pe ronaa bhaaiiiii "koi kuch karne bolta hai, koi kuch, ek jaisa bolo to sba kardu" aur laga ronee. wo rone se lekar abhi rulane tak ka tera safar bhai Salute. wo NSS ka nukkad bc bio ke exam ke beech me kar diya, usme bhi "oohohoh" ka choreoo, bc abhi hasi aati hai, but as you said "apna batch hi raste pe karke aaya hai bc", feeling proud! yaad hai wwahi bc tu end ki shayri bhul gaya aur mujhe nagada bajate bajate pooch raha hai, bhai moment tha yaar wo bhi x) .

orientation ki to baat hi alag hai. jitni marawayi, kabhi nhi bhulenge. Antargni ke apne choreo bhaaii, "hum 2no hai alag alag" sale original step hi wo vulgar tha. waha se to bhai play me chala gaya, aur uske baad jo tune Anand se leke Ramdas tak ki progress ki bhai usko to 21 topo ki salaami. 
galaxy me bhi bade maje kiye yaar. saifi ka play, fir apan ka 3rd year wala to bakchood. 3 run through me hi chaap diya. (director ko jyada mehnat nhi karwaai xp). Coordi tenure ki to kya hi baat kare, jab sabse bada kaand hua, tab to apan 2no hi so rahe the (IITB). lekin saaare utaar chadhav dekh liye, aur kuch majak mastiyon ke sath jeet bhi gaye. 

ye saari to bas dramatics ki baate hui, yaadein tobahut saari hai. lekin iske alawa bhi to mech ke courses nikalne me kitna waqt bitaye hai bhai. aur har baar ek chiiz common thi. "ostwal hai, sab kuch ho jaayega". wo first year me NCL me sath jaake padhna, 2nd year tak library aur 3rd year to wing me hi chata tha sab kuch. 

Golden ka to pata nhi, but you are a man of good heart. log izzat nhi kama paate, waha tune logo ka bharosa kama liya. Apna branch, hall,dramatics, to same hai hi but apni shuruwaat bhi same thi, fir wo club interest ho ya CPI. lekin yahaan aate aate raaste alag ho gaye. fir main kabhi iss baare me sochta hu ki kya reasons rahe honge, to bas wahi moments yaad aate. tera na gaali dene se lekar gaali diye bina na bolne ka safar, ki kaise sabse alag opinion hone ke bawajood bhi tu apne opinion pe khada rehta tha, kuch alag karne ki chah rakhta tha aur uske parinaamo se ladne ki himmat bhi, mehnat to teri badi hai hi, lekin teri will power usse bhi badi. aur abhi teri inhi sab baato ko atmasssat karne ki koshish karunga, aur ummid karunga ki aage aur acchi acchi chheeze tere se seekhne mile

Aage ke liye all the best bhai!
Love you <3

text:
"Nana bhai chal scene banate na", "bc nana tu kitta fraud maarta hai bhai", "aaja chal aaj chicken khate","oo nana yaar chud gaye yaar","9 baj gaye kya ğŸ˜‚", "hello nana, haan uthja bsdk class nhi aana kya", aur bhi kitte sare dialogues hai bhai, bas ab bolne wala tu nhi hoga. 2nd sem me to main khud hi gayab tha, LEKIN "UPSC nikal lenge naaaaaa" ye nukkad me dialogue sunke judge to kar liya tha ki bc ye dindor bada hawasi haiğŸ¤£. Galaxy to uss saal ki bhaisaahab. Dubey ka wo gaana "samay ke pahiyo ki pagdandi" ise sahi se gaane ka bhar tune apne sir liya aur khud hi hag diya bcğŸ˜‘.

Ab aate hai Summer play pe. Bhai practice me maje bahut kiye. Tera dance dekhke to abhi bhi hasta hu ğŸ˜‚, bhadda nachta hai bsdk, 2-4 acche steps seekhle. Uske baad wo exercises, bc jyadatar skits me tu hi sath raha hai. Aur play se bedhalat me bhi sath hi. Chalo ye bhi theek tha.

Fir 2nd year antaragni bhaii, bc saare log play me cast apan dono hall se nikalte samay sochte ki aaj katiyaar exercise me gandi na phade ğŸ¤£, but katiyaar to apna kaam bakhubi nibha leta. Aur tu hisaab rakhta tha ki nana ne aaj kitta fraud maara ğŸ˜…. Aur bhai acads ki baat kare to wo apne to sath hi me uthte aur ghatte the.

Galaxy ka zeher yaad hai "sapna toota to hai dil yunhi jalta hai" ye bhi tere room pe banaye the, munna, circuit aur anand bhaiğŸ˜‚. Usi galaxy me apan jhagad bhi liye, thodi mukka laat bhi ho hi jaani chahiye thi, dher sari yadon me ek ye bhi shamil ho jaati. 

Aur sirf dramatics se related nhi yaar, tere sath to baaki pal bhi maje me hi gujre hai. Bc wo shukla tu aur main wo venky ka subject padhte hue bakchodi kar rhe, kyunki pata tha ostwal sab sambhal lega. Wo loki k badday pe asmaani sair aur wo DJ khalid wala moment bhai avismarniya.

Aur bhi bahut hai bhai, agar jaane se ek din pehle bhi bata deta na, poora 4 saal recap karlete hall 12 me. Chill hai, but bada dariyadil insaan hai tuâ¤, aise hi udarta banaye rakh aur gyaan dete na main accha lagta na tu, to bas jahan jaaye waha swag aur mahol banate rehna.
Love you bhai â¤

text:
Varun "dominating" Jain, jabse main janta hu tabse to mere mann me teri poori image ye shabd bol deta hai. Teri gaaliyaan ho ya satire, shikar to jyadatar main hi bana hu. Kabhi teri sarcsatic baato pe hasa hu to kabhi ghussa bhi aaya hai, lekin ab baato se tera mukablato karne se raha, to gaali de kar hi mann halka karliya. Waise ek baar to awaaz uthayi thi (IITB me dance competetion se pehle), tu bina kuch bole chala gaya, tab maine socha ki play ke liye ostwal ko manaya jaaye ya sorry ke liye Varun ko, choodo yaar Dance pe focus karte hai :)) . 

NSS me dekha tha pehli baar, aur ye shant sa dikhne wala banda 3 saal me itna keher dhayega iska andaza bhi lagana mushkil. Dram eve 1 me hi pata chala ki bhai sabko sath leke chalne walo me se hai, fir chahe gaiyanke hi kyu naho. aur to aur bhai gaana bhi gaate hai, bhai scene bhi banate hai, bhai gaana bhi likhte hai, bhai instrument bhi baja lete hai, aur bhai ka sense of humor to gazab ka. Itna Multifaced chaapu character hai tu <3

Antaragni, InterIIT, coordinators jahan bhi tere sath gaya, khud bulli hone ke alawa ;] jo jo choti moti bakchodiyan ki  mast thi. jitni bhi parties hui hai, log bhand hoke bhi maje nhi kar paate, kyunki waha bhi initiate karne wala tu hi. hall 2 me dindor ka room aur hall 12 me tera, bas yahi hai jahaan phir kabhi mauka mile na, to saare yaar milkar ek baar fir DJ khalid ban jaau :)). Coordi wale tenure me kitne bhi utaar chadhav hasi majac dukh dard hue sabme tu sthir tha, strong tha, calm tha. Aur ye acchi cheez hai to seekhne ki koshish kar rahahu. 

Tera BT wala chehra jyada nhi dekha lekin jab dekha to fatt jaati thi. IITB se laut ke baad aur abhi college chhodne ke wo moments unhi me shamil hai. upar se bhale hi kathor hai lekin mann me koi baat nhi rakhta. 

Inter IIT ki wo baat to kaise bhul sakta hu, maine kurta nhi laaya, to tu galiyaya "nana bc tune kurta nhi laaya to tune laaya kya hai" ----"shoooooeeeeessss" :). Aise hi saare khushi aur dukhi wale palo ka hissa tu in 4salo me mere sath bana, uske liye thanksss bhai <3. 

college ke akhiri dino me bhi aur maje karne the, but kya kare kismat me nhi the, aur haa ksi pe taunt maarna aur maze lena ye hall 12 me rehne ka parinaam hi hai shayad, aur pata nhi kyu ye main dindor pe hi azma ke dekh leta hu. wo akhri raat me photoshoot ha idea bhaai. jaate jaate apan sab bas yaadein sametne ki koshish kar rhe the. bas fir kabhi milne ka mauka mile, to tera roomm ho, saare yaar ho, tu dabbe pe gaana chalaye aur sab bas aise hi kho jaaye....

Alvida bhai <3, All the besttt

text:
You have been a constant support and pain in the ass for the past 4 years. IITK had pre-destined that these two guys would end up being close friends - we shared - wing, â€˜baapâ€™ ( should we call him that ?!), department, coursework home-city, the same crush...and many more.

It was a hell lot of fun cheating with you (Mr. fattu) in exams - Really OMG!. But I knew for a fact if Mukesh has solved it on his own - it has to be correct. 

Apart from all the nicknames, I have called you, the occasional gyaan session and the frequent gang bangsâ€¦I truly admire your helpfulness, hard work and â€˜coolnessâ€™ (You finally made it ) to name a few. The best thing about you is - you help others profoundly and you never ever make them feel so.

Just be punctual (You better know why!) and take the leap (wrt Rishikesh trip, those who know, know) - and everything would fall in the right place, If not, I have got your back now and always. Cheers to the past 4 years and a life-long friendship. THANK YOU!

text:
Itâ€™s really hard to express your simplicity and sweetness in words - easily one of the nicest person I know o:)Have seen you inside out (You know what I mean :P)..shouldnâ€™t go into details on public records. Some things about you really intrigue me - how can someone play all day long (you should be the poster boy of Glucon-D) and have so much organised hostel room (Dude, really WTF!, they are not supposed to be organised in the first place :-)). 
It was a pleasure being your script-writer from Nishika in fresher to Minki in senior year...chutiya tmhara kata...but dukh hmko bhi hua ;)...I guess they didnâ€™t know you have 6-pack abs, a good job and a kind soul (Khud so jaayenge uskoâ€¦..)..oh that qualifies you for marriage (already late by Rajasthani standards xD).. can wait to share your rangeen hostel kisse with bhabhi-sa (itâ€™s time to forget Kristen Stewart).
Your room has always been our backchodi adda...your Gurgaon flat will be one too :) You are better than a bank when it comes to safeguarding money but you used to steal my roomie and his shipment..very bad! ;) Just a friendly reminder - I play better badminton and mini-militia than you. Period. Most probably you would agree, if not, I do have ice cream.
I have got your back just like that Antaragni night dare. Have roamed around a lot together, still, a lot left to explore.  It would be near impossible for someone to know you and not like you for the person you are. Thanks for always being there except PHY103 endsem...hahaha!!. Love you, bro! M just a call away! All the best! A very bright future awaits!
P.S - Is sem to firse dassa aarha hoga !?

text:

text:
2 guys having serious discussions for hours about random desh/duniya topics...yeah, thats us!... Hopefully doing our bit for a few of them in future together. I donâ€™t remember how we became such good friends but thatâ€™s the point, good things just happen! We have our footprints from Nepal to Rajpath, Naini lake to Lal Tibba, Chandigarh to Triund top and many more. Wishing to scale some more mountains, driving some more miles and doing some more adventure sports together in India and Abroad. 
You are a guy with high ideals and more or less I have seen you stand by them. The whole senator episode was fun...jokingly proposing your candidature in the last hour of nomination in mess...and boom the third-highest votes count! You are generally calm, composed and confident - the gyaani â€˜yodaâ€™ of our group.
You constantly cheered me up whether it be jumping off the hills while paragliding, rafting through personal hardships or doing my first 3km run. A huge fan of driving skillschahe bike ho ya car...kya cut maarte ho bhai xD. Had a great stay at IITK.. thanks to amazing friends like you who inspired, comforted and taught a lot at the same time. 

Our friendship has aged like red wine and I know the future holds better.  Just read the autobiography of a yogi, you have been sitting over it for ages. You do good Shayariâ€™s...last day during the storytelling session, I thought she was the...the source of pain in your Shayariâ€™s..but I was wrong..so ultimately *turns out* you have good storytelling skills also. You laugh hard and say â€˜fuckâ€™ even harder (Virginityâ€™s hurting, uh?) Happy Exploring...I hope you find something worth settling for. Just a call away!
Aajao... **Awkard hugs**...Chalo Badhia!
PS - Keeping laughing randomly without reasons as you always do!

author: Prabhat Kumar Singh

text:
Ah...those days of romance. 
July 22, 2017.
First day in IIT Kanpur, first time in hostel. I entered my allotted room: 320, 2-top, Hall 3. The only thing I see is a jeans hung on a crooked nail on the wall, dumped on it is a green checkered shirt with rolled up sleeves. Delhi guy. I knew.
The next thing I remember is comparing our Motos with the feeling of a certain brotherhood that two guys with same phone share. The next thing I remember is discussing our expectations and our favorite movie stars ;).
I never felt how happening a single room could become, when we built our own door closing system, when you kept sleeping till 10 on PHY101 lab exam and when the pole dancers and poles came together XD.
Stealing hotspots, playing tennis on Tauaa tables, snoring off while the room's door got replaced, wandering in bhoot bangla looking for a broken hockey stick during treasure hunt....
Bogged down by so many memories, the floods never seem to end. But this is a flood I do want to drown into.
Hell of a great things we did in that damn room. Never to forget the bromance ;-)
Who knows when our lives cross paths again, but surely when it does, I'm sure it'll be a Kodak moment.
So long, friend.
Btw, I still couldn't understand Maeri.
author: Prabhat Kumar Singh

text:
Itihaas gawah hai ki hostel me do bros jab mile hain to final year me alag hona hi pda. Shayad ye kudrat ka karishma tha ki college me entry bhi ek room me hui aur exit bhi ek hi room se.
Khair, kaafi philosophy pel di.
Konsa vichitra kaam nahi kiya ?Watercooler se cooler me paani bharkar bisleri ki bottle ko uske upar mujra karwaya. Shayad ye jaadu koi aur na jaanta ho.
Room ke andar sutli bomb aur kon fod sakta hai ? First year me HEC se chhupkar OAT ke piche garden me letkar wifi chalana, aur us excited kutte ka excitement control karna; Utsav ki bidai par vilaap karna; gaming karna aur last room ko theatre banane ka plan; Suman ka mms banana; Arun ka sleeping makeup karna....itna sab hai ki yaad nahi.
Phir milenge, tab yehi chizen to baad me yaad ayengi XD. 'interaction' ki vo raat jis din saari chitrakala baahar aayi thi chacha log ke saamne, jis din pole ka talent aur debate karne ki kalaa nikli thi hum logon me, aur jab Abhit ka chhipkali prem saamne aaya tha, vo din kabhi nahi bhulne waala. 
Milte hain dost, phir kuch kissa lekar, bakaiti ke naye kaarnaame lekar.
Bas ek hi ichhaa adhuri reh gayi, agar paani ki vo saari bottles bech di hoti to aaj 500 ke note se bane gadde ke upar baith ke ye likh raha hota :'-(
author: Prabhat Kumar Singh

text:
"Jo hota hai acche ke liye hota hai."
I think of this when I remember that you missed the first quiz of the first semester of your college life. Painful, yes. But destiny.....
Whatsapp numbers exchanged, emergency contact method established, just to make sure none of us missed the next D-Day. That's where the formal friendship started.
I could say our friendship was like the apes starting to interact in order to start a new age of civilization. Ye le mere ghar ki mithai. Ye kachori rakh, Jodhpur special XD.
The real spark started with us buying Haralambos, mugging up shitty sociological theories and cursing the course with each term memorised.
I can't remember when you became the photographer of our group, always coming up with dazzling ones. Two OTC trips and an all cycle trip to the Barrage brought out the adventurer in us, knowing each other better, struggling and still finding the fun in that. Never losing the cool even in the greatest of pressures is something I borrowed from IITK, with you at the centre. 
After so many travels, there's one thing I know: the thirst for more adventure isn't over yet. 
Won't be long hopefully, when we'll be pulling our bags together, sneaking into one of the locals without a ticket, yet for another adventure....
Till then, adios friend, philosopher and guide'ish'
author: Prabhat Kumar Singh

text:
Helllooooo ghunchuu (;P) !!!!!
As I sit down to write this...I donâ€™t even know where to begin. There is so much that I am grateful for and so many things to be proud of! You are the coolest and the warmest person I have ever met and as I write this, tears come rolling down my eyes :â€™) I canâ€™t be grateful enough to have met you and the way tables have turned around between us!  You are the first person I share everything with whenever anything happens, doesnâ€™t matter if itâ€™s connected to you or not! (I canâ€™t believe I just confessed this) You amaze me every time! Thank youuu sooo muchhh for making my life no less than a fairy tale. Whatever be the situation (good or bad), we have always managed to turn it into a golden memory, to be cherished forever!

Thank you for helping me become a better person (in progress though ;P), come out of my comfort zone, try new things, make new friends and the list goes on and on and on! You are the most amazingest (;P) person I have everrrrr met.

IITK will always hold a special place in my heart for it has been a great host and helped me meet you in the most uncertain of times. You have been with me through thick and thin and I expect this to continue in the coming years! Thank you for tolerating me!!

Call me as soon as you read this, or, you know the consequences! Also, donâ€™t ever forget to be proud of yourself as the â€˜almightyâ€™ Prashansa Dadu loves you <3 !! Cheers to all the mad things we did together! Letâ€™s meet as soon as the pandemic is over. Until then, no byes!

text:
Mere Bhai, 
Pichhle janam me mene puny kiye honge tabhi mujhe Arnav jaisa baapu aur tere jaisa bhai mila. Hum toh asli wale bhai hai, ek-ek baat likhunga toh word limit exceed ho jaayegi. Apn toh shuru se hi contact me the. Tu wing me age-wise sabse chhota hoga, par tumse mature puri wing me koi nahi hai. Tumne mere har kand me mujhe guide kiya, aur meri low time me mujhe sambhala. Tum nahi hote toh me puri tarah se fucked-up ho jata. Fir mere liye shayad sambhlna bahot muskil hota. Bandi wali meri irritating baato ko bahot saha tune, par time pe sahi rasta dikha diya. Tumhari itni importance hai ki, agar jab bhi koi kand hota tha mere sath sabse phle tum dimag me aate the. Tumne sare bhaiyon ki bahot help ki hai. 
Tum khub tarakki karo, taki hum proud se bol sake yah mera bhai tha clg me. Banglore jaa hi rahe apn, mulakatein rukni nahi chahiye.

text:
Hi Mote!
Ab bhakt kya hi likhe bhagwan ke baare me. Sabse playful insaan ho tum puri wing me. Tum mote bhle hi ho, par dil se ekdm chhote se bachhe ho. Jab koi kaam kar rahe hote ho tab super-serious and baki time ekdm childish behaviour. Tumhara dil bahot saaf hai. Tumne meri bahot help ki hai. Profs ko RR wale mail tumse behtar koi likh hi nahi sakta xd. Interview tips, coding bugs/silly mistakes, company life, bandi ke baare me, etc kaafi sari helpful discussions mei bhul nahi sakta. You are the person that everyone wants to be with, no matter wherever you go. 
Jis tarah se tum sabki care karte ho, I wish mei tumhara chhota bhai hota, par I am sure chhote bhai se kam bhi nahi hun. Tumhe irritate karne se alag hi satisfaction milta hai mujhe.
Sach batau, tumse jagda karke bahot jyada bura laga tha. Roj man karta tha ki tumse baat karke sorry bol dun. Abhi apn kabhi ladai nahi karenge, thik hai?
Bhulna mat tumhe mess me kadak roti/paratha/dosa lena mene sikhaya xD. Aur bhi bahot sari chhoti moti yaadgar baatein hai. Aur han, badminton sikh raha hun, apn team banate rahenge, aur sabko hara denge.
Jeevan me humari care karte rahna. Yaad rakhne me tumhe efforts lagne nahi wale hai, kyuki mei bhulne nahi dene wala. <3

text:
Hey best friend, I am wondering where to start. You are undoubtedly the person whom I conveyed the most number of lines in terms of conversation at IITK. I can hardly remember any conversation between us in the first half. But when I get to know you personally, I became an admirer of your simplicity, brilliancy, lowliness, generosity, and sense of humor. You have a big brain and a big kind heart at the same time, which is very rare.
I am damn sure that you know me better than any other person does. We had many Bakchodis together. Listing them down would require a whole book in itself. You motivated me in every possible way. You shared some of your not-so-dark secrets with me, and I could not find any secret element in them xD.
You canceled your Goa trip because some of your close friends, including me, were not going. I was so overwhelmed knowing this. We have completed almost two years of friendship without turning the back on, no more than zero times, which is very infrequent in my case.
We always believe deep inside our heart (or brain) that it happens exactly opposite to whatever you say. And that was the reason you always underestimated yourself. Bro, You are nailing everything.
You are such a helpful person that, despite your PPO, we were preparing every day for (my) placements. Thanks for everything.
I saw you closely pine for someone in love. It proves that you would be a great lover if given a chance. Tu ladkiyon se baat kar toh sahi.
I hope we will keep creating the PRs together on GitHub for every bug we see in life (whether open-source or not)  ğŸ˜‚
author: Prashant  Chouhan
