author: Prateek  Varshney

text:
Yo Roomie! 

Yep the term is still valid after second year given the fact that I used to spend much more time in your room than I did in mine :P. Agar apne wing ka koi HR Kadim kehlaya jaa sakta hai toh voh tum ho. Kitne saare sports khelna (voh bhi dhang se aur kadr se khelna, unlike us buffoons :")), dance, acads, coding, event management, bandi patana aur pata nhi kya kya tum ek saath sambhal lete ho. And knowing where exactly you come from, it never ceases to amaze how you manage to keep such a cool head every time and have an optimisitc outlook on things irrespective of the situation at hand. The constant efforts you put in to reach greater and greater heights are an unceasing source of inspiration for me.

Thanks for being at the receiving end of my rants during the SPO drives, exams, assignment deadlines and just simply every day rr. Thank you for not just listening to my rants but doing so with a broad and calming smile across your face.  Thanks for patiently tolerating me as your badminton teammate :). But I won't thank for you for the cool music playlists always being played in your room. Vanced ka credit tumko nhi milega :P.

Bas thoda khulke baat karna seekh le. Ain't no point in hiding "secrets" for 2 years when everyone else almost surely knows it :). And yes, start asserting yourself. Better to be a driver than to be a passive passenger in the ride called life. Also, College ke baad bhi room ki heirarchy maintained rehni chahiye :P.

College mein ek trip banti thi saath mein but nhi ho paayi... :(. Chalo ab college ke bahar hi sahi :). Aage bhi aise hi chaapta reh. Wishing you all the best for your life ahead, both personal and professional. And do stay in touch. Baaki milte hai lockdown ke baad. Cheers! :D
author: Prateek  Varshney

text: Yo Karan. You're one of the most level headed guys with an all-in-all personality I have come across during my stay here. Adventurism, sports, dance, acads, coding, placement and what not, you excel in almost everything. Bas thoda khulke baat kara kar varna them girls ain't gonna be impressed soon :P. And haa, stop sneaking into other people's phones. The JPMC HR may not be as lenient as we have been XD. All the very best for you life ahead bhai! Aise hi chaapte raho. And let's go on another trip soon :)
author: Prateek  Varshney

text:
Hey Deepak. Roz tera yearbook page kholke baith jaata hu kyuki samajh hi nhi aata kab aur kaha se shuru karu mai. Socha aaj pehla attempt maar hi lu. Toh first draft samajh ke baksh dena :P.

Thanks for being at the receiving end of rants, cribs and everyday rr. Tune naa sirf har baar sunaa (voh bhi itni dheeraj ke saath), par apna valuable feedback diya and har bar mujhe calm down kiya. And most importantly, you were always there as a rock for me to fall and rely on. Tere bina toh mai DE courses katai clear nhi kar paata. Raat bhar padna aur phir exam se pehle mujhe padana aur mere doubts clear karna. You even took the blame for me for some of my fuckups in courses! I can't express how grateful I am to have you as a friend during my stay here :D.

You're the guy who made me fall into love with memes, wholesomeness, shayari, gazal, music and literature. Bhai maine tujhe kitni baar kaha hai, apni kavitao ko publish kar par tu sunta hi nhi -_-. Pata nhi kyu khud ki talent ki kadr nhi karta. Thank you for the daily dose of dopamine and serotonin via the memes and music you send my way on a daily basis. Sometimes that is all one needs to drag through their mundane day and life :). 

Keep on spreading happiness man. And ab jaate jaate apne time management ke raaz bhi batate jaa :P. Counselling, HSS, acads, memes aur pata nhi kya kay ek saath sambhal leta hai XO. Bas jald se noida aa phir chill karte apan saath mein :P. Wishing you all the best for your life ahead. And once again, Thank you simply existing! ^_^
author: Prateek  Varshney

text: Asslam u alikum Khan Sahab! The First President to change the political culture of Hall-2 who won the election by getting the opposing candidate disqualified :P. But also the person to give his all for the Hall's sake.  Probably the best coder in our wing (jo 8th se coding kar raha hai :P), and the most diplomatic guy. Life seems fun when you get together with us for a movie session.  Bas thoda khulke interact karna seekh lo. Baaki toh mast insaan ho hi tum. Stay in touch! And best wishes to your South Indian wifey :)
author: Prateek  Varshney

text:
Hey Monika. Probably the most unique lingo wali girl in the campus that I know of. But then again how many girls do I know!? XD. Thanks for being a great friend throughout my stay at IITK. Funny how I got to know you first via my wingies (And yes! voh mail maine nhi likha thaa. Sacchi! :P) and sad how I did not get to meet you earlier :").  

Thanks for being at the receiving end of my rants during the SPO drives, intern ho yaa placement. Not just listening to my nagging complaints but also telling me exactly what I needed to hear, and most importantly, for just being there :) . And tum resourceful nhi hote toh SSP Psycho Lingo jaise courses mein mai kabhi pass nhi ho pata XD. Baaki chaapu toh tum ho hi, from you amazing artworks to your coding skills to your athletiscm and your jaw dropping yoga asans you manage to pull of (God! Dekh ke hi dard hone lagta mujhe toh :P). 

Sad how we don't have a single pic at all. I was looking forward to it during the last campus stay but tum toh aayi hi nhi -.-. Jaldi jaldi Google Gurgaon ya Bangalore join karo and Hyderabad ditch karo. Phir milte hai kabhi :). And haa, humne toh tumhare gender-neutral Hindi seh li but shayad office vale naa sahe. Toh graduation ke baad thik kar lena :P. All the very best for your life ahead, both personal and professional. And do stay in touch. Cheers! ^_^
author: Prateek  Varshney

text:
Hey baby girl! :P Still recall the mess table interaction we had right after orientation. Over the 4 years, you went straight from "Yaar tu gaali kyu deta hai. Bina gaali ke bhi toh sam baat bol sakta hai naa" to greeting people with "Aur bsdk (Â¬â€¿Â¬)" XD. 

Naa sirf Mech, but har cheez mein tune khola hai aur andha chaapa hai, be it drams coordinator banna, acads or corporate andha paisa. I am a great admirer of how you took on the challenge of stepping into the completely unknown domain of Data science, worked like hell through unpaid and paid internships, made all sorts of interesting tutorials and managed to bag a fat ass paying job in Data Science itself! All because tune ek baar thaan li toh ab karna hi hai ab bc.  You have potential to go from heights to heights. Never stop achieving greatness!

Thanks for introducing me to ecstasy :P. Kaafi mazaa aaya kyuki teri company jo saath mein thi. Bas ab jald hi phirse milke "chill" karna hai tere saath :). All the very best for your life baby girl! Aur touch mein rehna. Jald hi milte hai! :)

â€œO meri Janeman!â€
Met you 4 years ago, and one inferno/mid sem later, we were practically inseparable. oo bhosdike,
Bhai pahele yad dilata na ki aj last date hai isko likhne ka. Kya kya likhu bhai. Sab kuch toh nai likh sakta is memoir mai. 

Day 1 hostel mai, sab aise hi zada nai bol rahe aur ek tu... usi din se bakchodi shuru. aur us din se abhi tak level upar hi gaya hai bas. Tu proper depiction hai dilli ka launde ka. 

Phir toh kya hi tha, 4 sal aise hi khatam hue hai tere room aur uncle ji k room mai bhate bhate. Chaye woh 1st year wala bluff ka game ho ya last year wali kissi ki bitching.

Pure campus mai kya chal raha hai, kya raaz hai kaunsi bat kaise bat, sab ka khabar tere pas hai- chaye woh hall 3 ki bedsheet ki kahani ho ya kissi ka laptop chori (xDD). 

Bhai woh "Gupta Rice company" aur "kauua k ghosle mai humara koyal" ne kya bhosda kiya. Is idea ne maaza hi dila diya tha. Sala abhi tak hassi ati hai. 

"bhai lag gayi" iske bad jo khushi hui â¤ï¸â¤ï¸. Party toh pahele bhi chal rahi thi, lekin iske bad toh aur khushi k saath hui. XD. Lekin jald hi wapis jana pada. Jo bhi hai- woh kuch din ache se yad rahega- quarantine ho ya normal hall 12 ki zindagi.

Waise tu news anchor mat banna, debates mai samne wale ko kuch bolne hi nai dega. ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚

Bhai itna kabhi nai hasa honga, jitna tere saath hasa hu. (bc itna gussa bhi kissi ne nai dilaya)

Khush reh, aur tension kam liya kar, aur please bandi ki choices achi kar le.
Trip p chalo BCCC.

text:
"Room pe aaja"
Oh man, I am gonna miss this so much! Well writing this memoir is not easy simply because there is so much to say and express but most importantly how much I wish that I could tell you all of this face to face. You have been a big ( also tall :p ) and beautiful part of my IITK journey and there is nothing but gratitude to express. Thanks for helping me come out of my shell, for giving the best advice, for being my go-to friend, for teaching me some really cool dance moves, for being approachable always, and most importantly for making me understand my self-worth which had hit its all-time low during the second year. I am always gonna be grateful for being able to go to campus for one last time have so much fun with you. I so do not want to believe that this is the end of my IITK journey but hey let's call it the start of a new chapter of my life of which I would really love you to be a part of again and so pls pls pls let's meet soon and stay connected ( Tujhe set up bhi toh karvana hai ) In the end, I think I have only one thing left to say.....Are you lost babygirl? 
Love youuuuu

text:
Henloo Bholu/Bhola/Bhole/BhOPla/Dora the Whora bahut kuch
This is gonna be a long memoir. I know I have many friends here, many as close as you, but I can't simply ignore the fact that who I used to rush to first in times of distress, and who always used to help me out. A L W A Y S

If I start figuring out how the friendship started, it was probably when I started to came to meet tarish, and then dipuk added me to the spammer grp. But I had absolutely no idea how important you'll be for me in the upcoming 3 years, and beyond

To consistent bitching about everyone, to late night mamamios, to innumerable spamming, to almost many many of the memorable aspects of my life at IITK, you have played a central part. China ki mkb, uski wajah se kitni planned trips reh gyi, but ab jaldi hi hogi I believe so ğŸ˜¤

Thanks to specially you, and many others, 1st year me jis hall 12 ki mkb karte the, almost became my second home, and I had enormous fun and gossip time there, especially D3, I can never forget the wing

Also jitni baar canteen me tere naam se khaaya hai bhaiğŸ¤£, wapas maangne mt lag jaana kangaal ho jaunga, ya wait doge se jo kamai hogi usse de dunga, ameer to hone wale hain hum XD

Aree haan, another important part, Pubg, valorant, oh bhai kitna khele hain humlog, pubg me to tum log pro the ekdam lmao, ajeeb lagta tha but still khelne aa jaata tha, anyway maza bahut aaya usme, sab cheezon me kahi na kahi ek memory rahi hi hai tujhse related jo ki humesha humesha yaad rahegi mujhe

Aur bhi kai cheezein hain ig, but ab aur nahi likhunga. Waise bhi ye wholesome nature apna inbuilt nahi hai, so Bhola Chutiya likhte hue khatam karta hu.

Thankyou for everything, I can't and can never thank you enough but still thank you for everything. Chal jaa cycling time ho raha hoga terağŸ˜›

text:
Henlo,
Starting with "Laut aao 2nd year wali diksha"
We first met before the trip to delhi ig, and that time I had no clue how important role you'll play in my college life. Since then we had so many trips, so many up downs, and of course you have changed by miles, but still I believe we share a great bond :p
Since you know it is impossible to encapsulate all those memories we made, I'll leave this memoir with a few positive words. Since I can boast off the fact that I have known you the best all these years XD, you were really one of those sweet and simple girls everyone would admire. I was well there though to witness the third year transition to your "Angry Goddess" role, and the final year wala introvert mode bhi, but over all those years, your empathy and kindness for others didn't change, which I am extremely proud of.
You know I am very bad at expressing emotions, hence I would just like to thank you for the innumerous times you've helped me, and for those innumerous memories throughout the life at IITK.
And no, I won't kill you XD
Regards
Pull K Yeet

 "Dadu chal humdono hi one to one karte hai!! aaja isse pehle sir apne sath bula le humdono hi khelna shuru karte hai :')".  You were there for me when I was feeling all alone even when I had the whole of the team with me, and just you being there, not saying a word but understanding what I was going through is enough to tell everything there is about our friendship. Thank you for that! <3
Words are not enough to explain what you and our friendship mean to me (although I explained everything on that night remember?? :P) I can share literally anything with you (and maitreyee, taking her name so that she doesn't kill me when she reads this :P), and this is something I have never done till now, sharing everything with anyone. I miss having long talks with you about anything and everything. Those are one of the best memories I have of IITK. :')
Meet me soon!!! And yes let's live together forever once we all get a job!!!! Because you know, I'm the reason you survived college ğŸ˜ŒğŸ˜š Keep missing me (I know you do ğŸ¥°ğŸ˜‰)

text:
Yaar Dhawal kahah se shuru karu tumhare bare mai. Tumhare sath jo maze or masti kare sath kari thi wo to kabhi nahi bhul sakte. 
The first impression i had of you was of a rich spoilt pampered kid to top that with your round-faced- pahadi look. Always playing GTA-V and watching TV series. Or Randomly kabhi "OHH Godddd", "OHHH FKKKKKKK", "BC", "MC" Bhai poori wing ko pata chal jata that ki Aj Dhawal movie ya tv-series dekh raha hai. Kisko pata that ki tumhare andar ka bathroom singer itna grow kar jayega age jaake. 
Sociology mai exam se jyada to tumhari harkate dekh ke dar lagta tha, Sochta tha "kitna chill hai yaar yee"ğŸ˜‚. Mai apne ap se kehta tha "ruk jao end sem ane do sari coolness nikal jayegi" ğŸ˜…. 
Magar afsos aisa kuch nahi hua. Dhawal bhaiya to humare shuruwad se hi chapu the. Adi ye shayad tumse kabhi keh na saka ho but wo tum teeno ko(Tu,  Deepak, Shubham ) ko first year mai bahut gali deta tha. Roj rat ko mere room ke bahar ake "Mc kya randap macha rakha hai in teeno ne mere bed pe"
Aur fir summer camp maine sakshat logo ko roast karte hue dekha. Maja to bahut aya par Mujhe nahi pata tha tere ane wale sare shows mujhi par honge ğŸ˜…. 
And then it happened, I shifted with Hemant to another wing and jo tumhari bitching start hui kya batau. Magar had to tab ho jati thi jab tum mere hi room mai ake mere hi bed pe baith ke mujh pe hi show kar rahe hote the.  Kaise hi late night campus  walks or inhi sab bachodiyo mai samay beet gaya pata hi nahi chala. 
But the last months on the campus were the best, even the quarantine with you guys was awesome. Wo late night walks on hall 4 chat, or ninja banke shubham ka room dhundnağŸ˜‚. Listening your stories about your past your school life and your struggles, "belt se bhai-sahab dwara maar", wo 11 km daily run, wo ias -ips walo ki mast life, "wo ouija board wali kahani", "wo 6 thousand se 6 crore 6 thousand wali investment scheme" ğŸ¤‘ğŸ¤‘ğŸ¤‘. Kash real life mai bhi mere pas tere jaise credit card hota ğŸ˜.  But the promises we made on the hall 9 stairs top still remain unfulfilled. 
Jao yaar bahar and karo ji bhar ke jitne tour karne hai, and PERSONS nikalo yaar. Bas ji le apni jindgi and live a live to its fullest.
Thanks for being such a wonderful part of my life. 

P.S. - bas bada admi banke bhul mat jana or wo 70% -30% paise batne wala kuch nahi tha bas tum hi log chadaye ja rahe the.
author: Rajan  Singh

From being that shy introvert pahadi sa ladka, "3-bot à¤•à¥€ à¤²à¤¾à¤¶", yaar sare courses mai bas A lagte lagte reh gaya to becoming the fun-loving and vibrant person you are today.

text:
Aur bhai Phooking Mistry...... band ho gaya tera rona dhona. kitna rota tha yaar tu, poore last ke 2 mahine tune kuch nahi kiya and last mai phod ke ghar nikal liya.
Mujhe aj bhi yaad hai first year ke orientation tujhe fever tha and maine tere documents carry kare the and tu mujhpe hi gussa karne laga tha. Us time mujhe laga itne selfish and MC kaise ho sakte hai log. But wo kehte hai na dont judge a book by and aj char sal bad mujhe lagata hi you are perhaps the most kindhearted and sweet person I've ever met. 
In my entire 4 years, I couldn't think of a single day when we weren't together ğŸ˜…. Right from 3 bot to Athletics CPA to Group - B of 1st year. Machana to tumne ate hi start kar diya tha, 1st sem mai hi district mai gold and was offered to go to INTER IIT but bhai had other plans. 
From pulling an allnighter before the PHY 103A exam, or, keeping up with Ram Narain RIP workout ğŸ˜­, or, late night campus walks, or, hearing about your plans to make money ğŸ¤‘, or asking you for money in library and buying stocks with it, and dhawal making a story about - "Aditya ne ek bar Rajan ko paise diye - bas yahi take this story uske bad Aditya ko kabhi wo paise wapis nahi mile"ğŸ˜‚. 
But the best part was perhaps the summer camp with athletics team, waking up early in morning and cribbing about the workout, going to ganga barrage, Playing cards and hearing about the stories of seniors, Making stories about others, and going swimming,  and then the blue world trip Yaad hai jab hum hamari kitni fat rahi this uchi rides pe and jab hum us ride pai top see gir gaye the..... 
Magar fir tum bade ho gaye or humse jyada samay apne any freindsssss ke sath samay bitane lage the. Aur fir tumhari jindgi mai kusum ayi....
Hume to laga that Aditya humare liye campus aya hai but nahi..... Aditya ko to ghadi chaiye thi. 
But campus ke wo last months mai kitna maza kiya that yaar, wo photoshoot outs, wo tumhare walk pe na jane wale bahane, hall 4 and 9 ki chat pe gyan wali bate, and holi pe tumhara jalwari wala dance, long distance road running in the lockdown and, your future plans at the age of 25 ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£. 
Bahut yaad ayega yaar.  But touch mai rehna kabhi bhi man kare to call ya text kar dena.

text:
Hey Aamir ahmad makki- You asked "what is wrong" about others..WHAT IS WRONG WITH YOU????..If you ask me,  an order of magnitude worse than us decent folks - scientist/GoI/people of India who is doing positive things  rather than filthy reprehensible and above all unhelpful posts you are posting..For someone connected with IITK, this is beyond shameful I do hope your colleagues are taking note of that (as I have) .

Let me give some perspective:  I and *all* my kids/family have gotten vaccinations - some (those who were doctors) in December 2021 as soon as they were eligible. I live in US but do have a lot of friends in India - virtually *everyone* got vaccinated. 

Most of us scientists and decent people are  doing what we can to fight the pandemic.  Modi's government, and Indian People in general has lot of good will here in US - this is why our President, realizing the help India gave US in the beginning, and others are doing what we can.

And here you are - peddling trash and mis-information.  Unnat Bharat Abhiyan IITK deserves better.  Your colleagues and IITK deserves better.  If you can't add anything positive, please refrain from doing harm.

This is not fun and games, it is NOT 'freedom of speech' or evil government coming after your freedom to  peddle nonsense. It is serious. People like you have done enough harm. Please stop it. 

PS. If you are so incompetent that you can't use a simple web application, like coWin,  find someone who can - instead of blaming someone else. 

And do wear a mask (ranting about Kumb Mela is not helpful), get vaccinated (Ranting about "BJP vaccine is not helpful).

I know I got mad at you many times. Aur tune bahut manaya bhi h muhje. I am not letting you go easy, aage bhi ese hi manana padega. alwaysâ€¦ be it college, Gurugram, or even in the future. 
You were there in my most difficult times be it during internships, then lockdown, and then placements( har test ke baad randi rona krte the...xD). Because of you, I managed to get the offer from OYO. Raat ke 3 baje bhi tu mujhe guide kar rha tha placements me. I remember the happiness you and your whole family felt after hearing my job selection. I agree with you that this lockdown helped us to get rid of our lodu (yudh) habit. Otherwise internship ke time jese placement me bhi yudh karte rhte;) ğŸ¥²
The last 1.5 months of college were really awesome. But you always spoiled our movie screening plan. Donâ€™t forget the day when you laughed at my singingğŸ˜¤. 

Good bye to apna hoga nhi, abhi tujhe meri shaadi bhi karwani h. Chal milte haan jaldi hi. 

Thanks for being always there. M also a call away! 
Aajao... *Awkward hugs*...Chalo Badhia!
Love you, broâ€¦ğŸ˜ğŸ˜

P.S.- Ghyaan ki nadiya bahate rho..
author: Raman  Lamba

text:
Hi Vipin,
The quiet little boy in 1st year to a nice, soft-spoken, sincere, and wise counsel, ever ready with witty replies! The struggling boy of 1st year to a very brave man now. You really made it. You made me believe that a person can do anything if he desires. I used to feel like I am all alone in our department as there was no one in our wing from our department and I donâ€™t have many friends from our department too. But you were there always with me. 
You took all those crazy courses with me. We pulled through all those tough courses together. I think you were the reason why my grades started to improve from 2nd year. Looking at you I used to feel how could a person be this much determined to know about concepts. You always dig deep into the problem. The hard work and energy that you would put into everything were exceptional, you would just keep studying until you understand the concept. Never settle for less. Never tried to remember things, always wanted to know how things happened. 
I think because of me you developed the habit of watching all those tv shows. I used to watch movies, tv shows, and animes always. Sorry for giving you a bad habit of watching shows in middle of exams tooğŸ˜. But I am grateful to you as you taught me many good things. 
The friend who emerged as one of the important person in my life. I am not going to say goodbye as I am not letting you go for my life ever. Keep calling me and we will discuss all the ransom shit of life.ğŸ™‚

Thanks for always being there. Love you broğŸ˜â€¦ Always be calm and self-confident.

Yaad hai tujhe, first year ke end mein donon ke bhaiyon ne dhokha diya tha agle saal room share karne se. Aur phir uske baad hm donon mile the ğŸ˜…. Dukh mein ek dusre ke saathi!!! Phir uske baad first year summer, 2nd year, 3rd year, bas tu hin tha mujhe jhelne wala ek. ğŸ˜‚

Yo Apple boi!!!
Hm donon third year mein mile the. Tu tha dusre wing ka, par uss year mera neighbour ban gaya tha ğŸ˜œ.
Waise jab bhi woh phase yaar karta hun, ek hin baat dhyaan aati hai. Main tere room mein aata tha aur tu blanket ke andar leta/baitha rehta tha. Kabhi kabhi toh game ki aawaz aati thi Mobile se, baaki time pata nahin kya karta tha ğŸ¤£.
Then DBMS mein same team. Although project finalization ke alawa kuchh nahin kiye usme saath mein. All credit goes to the covid. 
Shukra hai Lucknow trip pe saath gaye the apan. Pure din idhar udhar ghuma tha. Baht maze kiye the maine, tune, aashish aur kg ne. Although dusra planned trip (Rajasthan one) ke liye tu itna excited tha, aur end mein aane se mana kar diya ğŸ˜•. 
Then Amazon internship together. Although we were in different teams. Amazon ke MacBook ka baht utilisation kiya tha tune ğŸ˜‚. Itna pasand aa gaya ki placement hin Apple mein lagwa li... ğŸ˜
Placement semester was very exhausting. Par har baar mera first point of discussion tu hin hota tha. Kitne discussions karte the be saath mein!!! 
Lekin placement ke day 1 slot 1 ki kahani nahin bhulunga main kabhi. Kitna RR kiya tha tune be ki kisi mein shortlist nahin ho raha. Aur bc day 1 slot 2 ki har company mein shortlisted tha. After the offer, you were like - "sab maze maze mein interview de diya bhai". Maze maze mein kitna chaap deta hai tu bhai ğŸ˜….
Then phase aaya campus mein last month ka. Raat ke woh campus walks aur sabke itne saare treats. Tera woh kg ke saath samosa fight ğŸ¤£. Tera kamar-dard, finger fracture, kya kya karwa liya tha tune ğŸ˜œ. 
Aur phir woh party, jab itna kuchh lene ke baad bhi bolta hai bhai kuchh nahin ho raha mujhe ğŸ¤£. Heave driver nikla re tu toh. Milo kabhi, capacity testing hogi teri...
Aur han, Randomised Algo!!! Bhai, tm aur Prajwal na hote toh kya hota uss course mein ğŸ˜…. Maze maze mein woh bhi saath mein nikal diya apan ne ğŸ˜Œ.

Aur even MG road, CTR, Mathikere, Delhi mess, Orion Mall, KFC, Nandi hills, ... The list is so long yaar!!! Bounce toh sabse pehle dhundhta tha tu ğŸ¤£. Aur han, tere ghar ke bane hue laddu. Baht yaad aayengi unki...
Phir hmlog wapas campus aaye and then kudos!!! Same hin wing mein aa gaye phir ğŸ˜…. Phir you and me became the common link to join this quarter of the wing to the next half part. 
Phir toh late night canteens aur night bullas... Still remembered ki tujhe kayi baar raat ke 1:55 pe bhi log uthate the aur tu canteen jaane ke liye neend se uth jata tha. Teri yeh aadat baht cute lagti thi mujhe.
Phir hmlogon ki Lucknow ki trip plan hui. Baht maze kiye maine, tune, Geetam ne aur Ashish ne. At that time I got to know ki yeh banda kitna selfie lover tha. Jahan mauka milta tha, bas selfies lene ruk jata tha ğŸ˜…. I loved that part of you my friend. Kaafi memorable raha tha woh trip.
Phir woh Antaragni mein Holi dance. Tera unique dance step ğŸ˜œ. Har kisi ko yaad hai woh toh.
Phir aaya Rajasthan trip. Tune aur Geetam ne hin convince kiya tha mujhe aane ke liye, although baad mein Geetam mukar gaya. But the trip yaar ğŸ’–ğŸ’–ğŸ’–. Aise hin plan karke chal diye the and then kaafi sahi ghum liya tha hmne 3 cities/towns. All thanks to Nishant for being our host. Wahan bhi you were indulged in selfies most of the time. Camel safari, bike ride in Jaisalmer, night bike tour in the open desert, all were very memorable. 
Waise han, petrol apna hamesha bach hin jata hai rented bikes/scooties mein ğŸ˜…. Chahe hm Bangalore mein ho, ya Rajasthan mein.
Last one month in the campus was also great. Pehla point hua karta tha tu - "KG, mess chalega?", "KG, canteen chalega?", "KG, Hall 9 chalega?" ğŸ˜‚. Saath mein holi, treats, night walks, OAT mein bulla, cards, special party, .... Baht maze aaye the tere aur baakiyon ke saath. Aur joint banana toh art hai, jo sikhna pada, taaki tu kuchh naya experience kar paaye ğŸ˜….
Waise tera woh dance Sachin ke room mein. The list is soooo long.

Par jo bhi ho bro, tu baht achchha aadmi hai. Aur chaapu toh hai hin (dassa boy!!!). Ek paper abhi publish ho gaya hai, aage bhi aise hin machate raho. All the best for you life ahead my friend! ğŸ™Œ Jald hin milenge apan.

Aur han, teri Taj mein treat due hai ğŸ˜…. Aa toh hm zaroor jayenge... Till then, take care.

PS: "List" yaad hai na!!! ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£

Late night badminton games, even during the exams, were the most relaxing period. 2nd year mein kitna PUBG khelte the be hmlog ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£. You, me, ashish, reithick, chanchal, nishant, shubham... Jahan utarte the, chicken dinner mil hin jata tha ğŸ™ŒğŸ»ğŸ˜.
Waise tujhse mere jhagde bhi kaafi hue. Har baar tu hyper hone lagta tha. But I think main situation sambhal liya karta tha ğŸ˜œ.
Waise kitne hair transitions kiye be tune... First year mein normal hair, then no hair, then very long hair, then different colors on the hair, then normal hair and back to no hair!!! Tera pata nahin, par tere baal baht rangeen the re baba ğŸ¤£.
Chalo, 1 saal aur baaki hai tmhara toh. Kuchh kaand karoge kahin toh call toh mujhe hin karoge sabse pehle ğŸ˜‚. Intezaar rahega unn calls ka.
Baaki, future ke liye all the best bro! ğŸ™ŒğŸ»
Although tu academically baht achchha nahin kar paya apne laziness ke kaaran, but you are a genius man. Life mein aage phodte rehna aur MACHATE rehna.

Kitne cheezein saath mein ki thi hmne!!!
Starting from first year astro events (although we were opponents ğŸ˜œ) --> First year ke summers ki 40 days ki conditioning by the Adventure club --> 5K, 8K, 10K --> shopping trip to Lucknow for buying trek items from Decathlon --> Hampta pass trek --> 2nd year mein donon Astro club ke secy --> conducting Mandakini in Techkriti...
Iske baad toh tm gaayab se hin ho gaye the ğŸ˜… (7 sem mein hin graduate hone mein)
Coming to the conditioning, yes it was very tough in the beginning. Bina ruke toh 2 rounds bhi mushkil se hote the ğŸ¤£. But then our dedication helped us through all that. At the end, we used to do 12 rounds (4 with stairs). Remembered Mahesh ji and Rahul!!! ğŸ˜…ğŸ˜…ğŸ˜… Jo bhi kaho, hm donon ne ek dusre ko baht support aur motivate kiya tha 5K, 8K aur 10K pura karne mein.
Now the Lucknow trip! You were damn excited for eating at Tunday Kababi ğŸ¤¤. We did lot of shopping from Decathlon and then we executed our plan of lunch at Tunday ğŸ˜ğŸ˜ğŸ˜….
Then the Hampta pass trek... Man, it was so adventurous, exciting and fun there. Aur tera woh experience at the park with that baba ğŸ¤£. I can still quote it in your words - "Aaj ka experience share karne laayak hai. Main ek forested park mein tha with the group and ek masale aur jaribooti waala hme follow karne laga and then aise hin baat karte hue bolta hai 'Bhaiya, shil*j**t le lijiye... Ek saath 3-3 ko thaka denge. Dandi bilkul aisi ho jaayegi...'. Main peechhe murkar yeh dekha nahin ki Dandi kaisi ho jaayegi. I was like... Kyaaaaa????" ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£ğŸ¤£
Par jo bhi kaho, those 5 days out there in the nature with you and others are one of the most memorable memories of my life. 
Phir Astro mein kaafi kuchh Kiya saath mein. Although, tmlog takneek jeet gaye the ğŸ˜•. But all of it was very memorable.
Baaki aage ke liye all the best dost! Jaldi se good news sunana UPSC ka. Tu achiever hai hin. Mujhe zyada bolne ki zaroorat nahin ğŸ˜….
Aage kabhi zaroor milenge bro. Till then, take care aur aise hin MACHATE RAHO!!!

text:
Hey Reithick da!!! ğŸ˜…
I knew you very less in the first year, except playing badminton with you and knowing that you were such a great bowler. I think it was the period just before the first year summer when we started knowing each other in a better way.
And after that, we stayed very close till the 4th year (all thanks to the hall change at the last moment after the quarantine period ğŸ˜…ğŸ¤©).
I still remember, you were the guy whom people used to say anything in hindi, even abusive words, and you didn't have any clue even as what they were saying ğŸ˜‚. Although later, your determination to learn some hindi helped you a lot man.
Waise how can I forget that summer incident. When we both went to buy something from z-square and you bought a dress for your present-ex, whose payment was done by me. And I had to wait for the next 2 years to get that back, that also in installments ğŸ˜….
We even remembered you HTC phone, the lightest in our grp, which you were proud of ğŸ˜œ.
You were a guy who went through many ups and downs in the life but was dedicated enough to convert that phase into a memorable opportunity. Dassa, cricket, ...
I liked your simplicity man and your thirst to strive for the best you can. 
How can I forget the TA202 end-sem exam ğŸ˜…. Hope you remembered ğŸ˜œ. Thanks for that yaar ğŸ˜.
Btw, everyone in our grp would agree on this that you were the most irresponsible person of the group ğŸ¤£. Still you used to manage the things. 
Playing late night badminton games, cards, going on trips with all (when you used to come late everytime ğŸ˜œ), long walks, your fundas, your random theories and discussion on them, ... (the list is very long). I will always remember all these yaar.
We made so many plans for Bangalore yaar!!! You, me, Ashish and Prajwal. The best was the go karting. All thanks to this covid situation that we haven't executed that ğŸ¤¦ğŸ»â€â™‚ï¸. But hope to meet soon there and execute each of our plans....
In the quarantine period, you were like an angel for me ğŸ¥º. Although you had to stay for one more week of quarantine which deprived you from playing holi with us ğŸ˜•.
On the last day in the campus, it was very tough to bid farewell to you. But jo bhi ho, you taught me to stay positive in the life ğŸ™ŒğŸ».

Now, I think it's getting very long ğŸ˜…. So, let me wrap it up.
All the best for your future bro!!! You are an achiever and a talented guys. This will remain with you for very long (maybe till the end). 
We will meet soon after this pandemic gets over. Till then, take care.

PS: I want a new goggles from you now for the one which you lost.

Aur bhaiya! 
I still remember my day in IITK jab sab tere room par baith k tujhe sunn rahe the aur tu branch change ka gyaan de raha tha. Maine kaha tha main toh sirf maze karne aaya hunn yahaan and you judged me so hard. Maine nahi socha tha ki after that we'll become such great friends. MSE se tu Civil aagya, Shashwat se bhaiya bann gaya aur Phir se Ud Chala bhi gaa dia xD 

Tujhe BT bahot zyada hoti hai shayad isiliye madam aur mujhe bheja hai taaki wo kamm karein. Main Norway wagerah jaane se pehle India ghoomna chaahunga fir chalenge :P

Aur logo k memoir mein toh kuch kuch memories common hain, yahaan toh poori college life hi common hai. But the best memories would be jab hum Civil ki labs mein assistants se ladd k aate the. Umpire se, ABN se aur main sirf tera saath dene k liye lad jata tha aur Matke humko dekh k shock hojate the ki kitni himmat hai in UGs mein. 

Teri wajh se kaafi kuch seekha maine -MATLAB, Photography, Cinematic Videography, Chess, Music, Papa Rap and thoda bahot Kanpur ka accent. 

Tune apne mann ki karte karte teen branches change karli aur kaafi marwaayi. Aage bhi apni pasand ki chize hi karna chaahe fir kitni bhi marwaani pade. Baaki Ranti Shukla toh aap ho hi bhaiya.

text: Bhai Maisam, koi jugad hai kya teri? Tu toh poore campus ko jaanta hai, kuch karwa yaar. One of the most Mast persons I met at IITK jo apna room Cards khelne ke liye hamesha available karwa deta tha :) . Jindagi mai mujhe Ladakh ghumne ek baar toh jaana hi hai pakka, tab please mera tour guide ban jana xD.
author: Rohin  Gupta

text: Hello mere chappu friend, from asking ki tujhe mai yaad hun ya nahi to becoming 2nd year roommates kaafi progress ho gayi apni. Umeed hai aap bhi Mota bhai jaise hi full taraaki karein apne jindagi mai and haan apni arranged marriage mai jaroor se bulana.
author: Rohin  Gupta

text:
Hey Nitish, you are one of the most hardworking and helpful people I have seen and met at IITK. I consider myself fortunate that I came to know you and could discuss Electrical Engineering courses with you, that really helped me a lot in these last four years. I feel that you are one of the few Electrical Engineers from our batch that had genuine interest in the subject and research. EE370, EE381, EE320, Vipul Sir ke Music Projects kya kya nahi discuss kiya tumhare saath. It was always fun and insightful interacting with you.
Same wing, Y18 orientation, extended CS family, Room 234 and much more, we had many things in common apart from studies. I believe that our bond grew with time as all good things should. Hopefully, our paths will cross sometime again in the future. Till then, Keep in touch. All the Best for your future.
author: Rohin  Gupta

text: Hello Piyush, hum dono ek doosre ko utna acche se toh nahi jaan paye kyunki internship ghar se hi ho gayi hamari :( , par phone mai jitni baar bhi baat hui tumse baat karke accha laga. PPO milne ki news bhi tumne pehle dedi thi, aage bhi aisi hi bhadiya khabrein dete rehna. Asha hai ki jaldi se Bangalore jaane mille aur tumse lambi lambi baatein kar paye.
author: Rohin  Gupta

text: Events Ground chal raha hai kya bro? Events Ground ka toh pata nahi par Goa jaroor gaye saath mai. Thanks for your constant companionship throughout these past years and hopefully for many more years to come.
author: Rohin  Gupta

text: Excellent Class Notes writer. TA201A mai tumne project kaise banwaya mujhe aaj tak samajh nahi aaya. EE381A ki lab mai fraud marne mai saath dene ke liye thanks. Kaafi intern interviews bhi saath mai baithke diye. You were one of the most genuine and intelligent persons I met at IITK. Never Change and Keep in Touch.
author: Rohin  Gupta

text:
Hello Bhai Shailabh, Shashank yaad rahega ya nahi pata nahi par Shailabh jaroor yaad rahega. Orientation mai pehli baar baat hui tumse but fir uske baad baton ka silsila ruka nahi. ESC201 ki lab mai bakchodiyon se lekar intern ke dukhon tak sabme tumne saath diya. 
Thanks for everything. Aage bhi cool boy banke aise hi chapte rehna aur yaad zaroor se rakhna. Hopefully, jaldi hi dobara milenge.
author: Rohin  Gupta

text: Nainital ki trip ko memorable banane ke liye thanks. Us trip pe jahan bhi gaye saath gaye, tumhare bina trip survive karna wouldn't have been possible. Hamesha aise hi khush rehna. Take Care.
author: Rohin  Gupta

text: Hey Reithick, you are the only person that made me speak English at IITK. One of the most tension-free and intelligent persons I met at IITK, it was nice to know you. Thanks for always sorting out my subject related doubts. Take Care.
author: Rohin  Gupta

text: Bhai yeh sabse itne asaani se dosti kaise kar lete ho, mujhe bhi sikhao apne yeh skills. Tumse utni baar baat nahi hui hogi, jitna corridor aur canteen mai Hello kiye honge ek doosre ko xD. Financial Economics mai pass karwane ke liye dhanyawad. Aage bhi milke ek doosre ko Hello karte rehna hai. Itne apna dhyaan rakhna. Ciao.
author: Rohin  Gupta

text: Patte khelne aa raha hai kya? Haan bhai chalo par sirf 2 round khelunga aur fir 2 ghante ke baad bhi uthne ka naam nahi lete the. Kaafi mazza aaya tumhare saath yeh 4 saal. Aage bhi aise hi chapte rehna apne jindagi mai. Wing Reunion karwane ke responsibilty tumhari xD. Take care and yaad jaroor rakhna.
author: Rohin  Gupta

text:
Matlab pehli ladki jiske saath comfortable, bina sharmaye, walk karte karte baat kar saku. Abhi bhi yaad hai woh techkriti ke food fest wali walk. Ladkiyo mai role model ho tum matlab. Situation ke hisab se mature n fun (EDM wala dance ğŸ˜). Tumne wo mera coffee wala cup leke, khud jo dustbin mai dala, I was like-ye bandi jyada hi sahi hai! Wo glowing band abhi bhi h mere paas tumhara diya hua. Ek baar eye ke corner se dekha ki tum muzhe bula rahi thi (dekha nahi kyuki koi aur laga). But mood ke dekha to tum smile kar rahi thi, even though maine galti se ignore kiya tha. Mannn, tu sahi mai alag hai (tum se tu pe aagaya na mai ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚). Tumhare family ke saath status dekh ke khushi milti hai sach mai. Aise hi haste raho please (atleast tumhe dekhe kabhi depression nahi ayega muzhe ğŸ˜¶). Milna hai tumse phir kabhi ek baar toh. Tumhare aage ke har status pe meri love reacts gurantteed hai aisa samjo ab. Saath to itna time nahi spend kiya, but dekh rahe ho na...ye memoir bhar gaya ussi se. Itna kahunga ki bas modo pe yaad karlena kabhi life ke, kabhi hum bhi hasane ki koshish karnege tumhe - agar kabhi udas ho to.  
With Love â¤ - Rohit
author: Rohit Baliram Landge

Par samaj lo ab feelings. Tuzhe dekha tha maine last yearites ke dance fest mai nachte. Katil moves hai re teri nana, acting toh chappar faad matlab. Sabhi tantotant thi apki involvements. kisi mai kuch kami nahi. tere ko yaad karke mai toh smile karta hu abhi bhi. Sad to hota hi nahi tu shayad kabhi. Mil lena bro abhi bhi hum ji rahe. text:
Kutte! Kitna kuch khilaya hai maine tereko. Bhulna mat. Kitna energetic hai bc tu. Kabhi bhi dekh lo, ful on enthu. Sports ke bare me nahi bolunga. Sab bol diye honge. Nisheeka ko bata de mai hi tha chat karne wala. Kitne logo se chat karwaye bc tune. Gharwalo ko bolkar shadi fix kara le. Mai ayega. AOT maine tereko dikhaya tha, uska thanks bol. Itna movies mat dekha kar bc, thoda chill bhi mar le. And one of the trait of yours- being melodramatic. Kuch bhi hoga, gussa kar ke baith jayega. Mahine-mahine to baat bhi nahi karta tha. But deep down, everyone knew it ki kuch time baad fir se khud baat karne ayega as if nothing had happened. I still donâ€™t understand ki tu itna magne kabse lag gaya? First year me apan saath me baithke chill karte the aur fir exam me hag dete the. Gurgaon me chill marna. Paisa hi paisa hoga. You are such an ambitious person. But remember, you earn money to spend it. Live life and fulfill your dreams. Nahi to paisa kama lega but jindagi piche reh jayegi. Milte rehna, tu to milega hi. Aa jayega merese treat lene. Whenever you read this, just remember Iâ€™ll be there for you.
Btw hagga is paar is the best!

text: You were the first guy I met at IITK. Initial impressions? Bahut bolta hai bc. But never even once I thought ki chup ho ja. Itni meethi meethi baate bolta hai tu ki sunte hi jaate hai sab. I even thought ki you may be a manipulator (kya karu? Duniya bahut buri hai. Dimag me sab negative hi aata tha). But wtf? Itna achha aadmi nikla tu. And yo, how tf do you store so much info in that little (jk) brain of yours? Iâ€™ll never forget those nightouts between Lamba and us where we convinced him that you wonâ€™t find a girl here and just get yourself married. Ragging me bhi to saath me the apan. And how tf do you take a bathe so frickin quickly? Literally 2-3 minute me khatam. Bc tere karan mai bina brush kiye breakfast karne lag gaya. Lucknow was class and Rishikesh was fun. Wouldn't have been without you. Yaar tu jab hasta hai, pure wing ko pata chalta hai. Dikkat ye bhi nahi hai. Dikkat ye hai ki tu hasta hi rehta hai lol. Never stop laughing. Milte rahenge nahi bolunga coz milna is compulsory. Fuck pademic, milna is necessary. Abhi Gurgaon ja rha hai. Waha se seedha Delhi jayega (IAS ke liye) I know. Signing off Mr. Senator. Btw hagga is paar is the best!

text:
You know how hard it is (TWSS) to write a memoir for you, right?
From praveen ki gaaliyan to coordis ki gaaliyan, from courses ki BT to life ki BT, from VH me paani laane jaana to FL shop me daaru laane jaana, from â€œHiâ€ to â€œaur bsdkâ€,  its been a great journey together. <3 Well, the ending is a bit hazy. But you know what? If you dont like the ending, it prolly isnt the ending at all.

Aajkal my morning dose of dopamine is the memes and reels you send me on insta. Please don't stop doing that. <3 

Love you . Miss you a lot.

author: Sagnik  Mukherjee

text: From "Ei tui bangali" to "bhai yearbook likhish". From first bengali friend to one of the best friends in college. It was a great journey pal. You have contributed so much to my growth. I hope I did something similar. We'll catch up soon. Coffee house -> Vibe to manna dey -> Hoppipola -> Terribly bhand -> rastai ghum. (#HokFok ?)
author: Sagnik  Mukherjee

text:
Adzoooooo (okay, dramebaazi yahin pe khatam)
Cant believe we're finally here. At each other's yearbook. Wish we could do this in person, but "it is what it is", right? From birthday pe mujhe cake na khilana to SOC me mujhe bachana, we sure have come a long way. And we both know it doesn't end here. Cause I really don't like the way we had to say our goodbyes. 
You've always been a bliss and I'm glad we got to know each other. PS: tere batch reels were gold XD 
And yeah we should pawriii soon. (AND WE WILLLLLL !!! <3 ) And next trip (yeah that's gonna happen) pe we should do that "scaring the shit out of priyal" thing again xDDD that was FUN :p 
Take care and stay safe madam :33
author: Sagnik  Mukherjee

text:
Siiiiiiiiir ,  (okay enough drama)
Every moment with you has been a bliss. If you remember, CS me pehla birthday tera celebrate hua tha. What a blast we had !! Then dheere dheere opening up, getting to know each other. Its been great honestly. You've always (ALWAYS) been a great inspiration and an amazing buddy. Intern ka experience same nahi hota tumhare alawa (MEAN IT !!!). Hope to see you soon and miss you a lot. Wish you all the best mere bhai <3 .

Saath me train kab kr rhe hai apan dono ?
author: Sagnik  Mukherjee

text:
aaii shuorer bachha !!!
jotoi gali dii, mon theke tomare ami bhaloi bashi. Merechho kolshir kana, tabole prem debona ? xDD
Okay enough dramebaazi, and fomo to anyone else reading this.
What a gem you are mama, one of the jolliest and craziest dudes i've met in campus. Physics-baaji theke maagi-baji, sob ii to korle xDD. Ektu gorib keo sekhao. (oops, bengali again lmao)
Yes, jokes aside, Love you bhai. It was more that just "our paths crossed" i guess. And Im proud and grateful for that. Touch e thakish. Parle call korish gorib take. Bhalo lage. 
-- iti tomar baba xD
author: Sagnik  Mukherjee

text:
Oh, you're finally here. <3 Lemme structure the thoughts. 3....2.....1..... okay it is gonna take time. I'll just start and spew everything that comes. 
Love you bro. Always loved how you could cheer up the entire room just with your presence. Undoubtedly one of the best peeps i've come across in campus. Dono WB me rehte hai bhai. We can catch up anytime. And we will do that soon. Call krte rehna. Bulla kaatne k liye i'm always up as you know xD. I still remember ek entire evening faaltu ki baato me bita dena tere saath (met at lunch and tu room tak aaya baat krte hue and we kept talking xDDD). We never had that beer-bulla session we planned (just before covid, we were supposed to do that just after the "small" vacation). We will do that as well.
Miss you buddy. Take care. Stay hydrated xDD.
author: Sagnik  Mukherjee

text:
Tu bro hai mera, Pta hai na tujhe ? <33 
â€œYou probably know me by all that Spamming on Facebook.â€ ? Nah bruh, I know you for reasons beyond that. Donâ€™t I?


One smart dude once told me â€œ10 saal baad sab koi ghis rhe honge, what will matter is tere paas baat krne kayak koi hai ki nahiâ€. And yeah within a second your name striked my mind. Thatâ€™s how much you mean to me. 

Thanks for making my campus life so wonderful. Thanks for being the person you are. And above all, thanks for existing. 

I miss you everyday. We vibed on day one. And weâ€™ll keep vibing till the last day. Baaki tu roomie to ban hi rha hai mera <3. Mast pawrii krenge :33 

Wish you all the luck bhai <3 . I miss you a lot.
author: Sagnik  Mukherjee

text:
Okay first things first Priyal Bhandari !! Why are our yearbook statuses so similar ? What evil sorcery is this ? (read in my voice ofc)

Thanks for not telling anyone ki kaise mujhe chhodne aana padhta tha hall 5 :â€( .
I will always remember â€œbure aadat chupane chahiye saaagnikâ€ and many other stuff you casually taught me. Whenever we say â€œsummersâ€, we mean â€œ2nd year summersâ€ by default. Ig the summer of â€˜19 deserves that much. 

Scaring the shit out of you with arzoo was FUN, â€œmaneer panchurianâ€ was FUN, Orientation â€˜19 was FUN. goa was FUN. The â€œahemâ€ session was FUN. And yeah hanging out with you was FUN (always). <3

Thanks for keeping me company while tum log pawrii kr rhe the (VC isnt half bad ig). Wish you all the luck and miss you a lot (The most cliched sentence in every memoir, cant skip this one :p, but yeah, I do miss you). :â€(( 
Reels bhejte rehna (khud ki nahi, FUN wale)
Okay, kaafi lamba ho gaya (also, TWSS). So baibai.
author: Sagnik  Mukherjee

text:
To one of the purest soul I've met in campus. 
Thanks bruh. We have interacted a lot, and I've learnt a lot from you. It was fun working with you and it was fun doing random bulla sessions as well. Keep in touch and take care <3 <3 .
author: Sagnik  Mukherjee

text:
Okay this is hard (ngl, and definitely not gonna be dramatic)
You prolly are the only FRIEND friend in campus, (or maybe in life) jar sathe I had fights eto frequently. And yet we eventually got back to where we were (back to basics basically lol).
Thanks for helping me go through many tough times, and making me listen to "new rules" , "levitating" and what not xDD (Guess Im fond of a little torture :pp)

Wish you all the luck (although you never needed it, neither you will) for your future. You're tough and strong. And you're doing enough to make everyone around you so proud of you. Just wanted you to know that. 
My college life wouldn't be the same without you, I hope you know that as well. Thanks for everything. Take care and stay safe. 

PS: I've kept that letter with me, and its one of the cutest thing that happened to me in campus.

text: Achyut bhai! Itni memories hain apni ki ye memoir chota pd jaye. Phir bhi kuch yaaden taaza karte hue - Wo pehli baar 3rd year ki december mai tujhse milna kya hua, 3 mahino mai hi ghulna milna hogya. Tere aur shobhit ke saath bitaye moments were the most chill moments of my journey of IITK. Wo tere liye techkriti hospi desk ki planning krna, wo glati se tujhse PR ke bacchon ko cheenna, namit ke saath partyion pr jana, C-104 mai yunhi pde rehna, hall-1 mess mai dinner krna, aur wo tere room pr seniors ke saath raat wala session, nhi bhula paunga mai. Kabhi socha na tha ki humari dosti itni gehri hogi, Jitna bhi kahunga kam hi lgega, tu aaya bhale hi late ho, lekin ab aakhir tak ka saath bna rhega. Aakhri mai, Thank you for motivating me and keep pushing me to do great in life. We will meet soon brother...
author: Sahil  Badal

text: Hi Anchal, the PR Head, thanks yaar PR ke bacchon ko bhejne ke liye. You were so kind by heart. Aur wo kabhi na bhula dene wale C104 ke chilling sessions ke liye shukriya. Best wishes for your future.
author: Sahil  Badal

text: Oye Kartik se Oye Dopa ka safar bada hi yaadgaar hai. Humare wing ka dopu aur Aruu ka janu. Wo tere saath arihant ke mze lena bada yaad aata hai. Wo tere liye tinder ki ldkiyon ka reply sochna bada yaad aata hai. Aur humari wing jitna bhi ghumi, usme tera hi to haath tha, tu hi to tha jo sbke saath tha. Wo tere saath late night canteen se lekr NH91 se Z-Square se Nepal tak ka safar yaad aata hai. Aur clg ke aakhri mahine ko mazedar bnane ke liye tahe dil se shukriya. Bas ek hi gham reh gya ki tere saath udaipur ghumna reh gya. But koi na waqt ki kami thodi hai, abhi to bahut bakchodi krni bachi hai, jald hi milenge aur phir machayenge. Best of luck for your future endeavors aur ye duaa hai meri rab se ki tujhe mile tere sapno ki raani jald se.
author: Sahil  Badal

text: Parth bhai, You were one of the chillest person, I met at IITK. Great friend to hang out with. Itni saari memories ko jo tumne yaad dilaya, usse pdhke to mujhe khushi ne rulaya. Tere wo HEC se picha chudane ke tarike bde yaad aaenge. Wo tera "koi kahe kehta rahe, mujhe to wahi krna jo maine hai thana" attitude was lit. My lecture hall buddy, you were funny. Aur wo udghosh ki trip mai jakar hawa khakr wapis aana, hmesha yaad rhega. Shukriya jo tumne humare raaz ko hmesha raaz hi rkha brother. Bhai tera wo SAE ke liye dedication aur rasam ke liye desperation nhi bhula paunga mai. Second year mai sbse jyada dukh tujhse aur arihant se juda hokr hua. Bada khalta hai ki 1st year ke baad jyada samay nhi mila saath mai bitane ko, wrna aur trip krte like Rasam ki treat. Humesha yaad rhoge tum. Best of luck for your future endeavors bro...
author: Sahil  Badal

text: Pawan bro, kya bulayen apko shayar, cricketer, rider ya provider aur bhi anek pehchan hai apki. Saath mai yaaden to summer ki hai jab A4 wing mai cricket khele phir clg ke aakhri waqt ko aur bhi mazedar bnaya with poker and bluff. Hum bhale hi apki duaon mai na aapayen lekin yaadon mai jarur bnaye rkhna, isi treh sabpr kripa bnaye rkhna, phir milenge dost, best wishes for your future...
author: Sahil  Badal

text: Bhai pehli baar dekha to tu repi nazar aaya, dusri baar mila toh rishabh ke saath canteen mai pta chala same branch se hai, phir to ye silsila 2nd year se shuru hokr aakhri din tak chala. Bhai shukriya BSBE lab ko entertaining bnane ke liye aur BSBE class ko chilling bnane ke liye. Phir aaya techkriti ka waqt jo kaise guzar gya pta hi na chala. Aakhir mai jo latke ladkhadate saath diya clg ke aakhri course pass krne ke liye uske liye dhanayawad. Tu chaapu hai bro... milte rehna, aur kafi treat pending hai kahin bhool na jana...
author: Sahil  Badal

text: Bhai Pradeep se OO Pradeepe bulane ka safar nhi bhulunga mai. Mera iklauta sathi wing se same branch ka, tu na hota to mai BSBE deadlines bhool jata. Wo tera mujhe roz class ke liye uthana aur assignment ko saath mai niptana nhi bhulunga mai. 4 saal same wing mai kab guzar gye pta hi na chala, har jageh to saath ghume hain, NH91 se Z Square mall se Ganga Ghat se Nepal tak. Wo wing mai sbke saath baith kr patte khelna nhi bhulunga mai. Aur clg ke aakhri mahine ko mazedar bnane ke liye tahe dil se shukriya. Abhi to bahut smay hai baki jaani, yun hi milke bnate rhenge kabhi na bhula dene wali yaaden.
author: Sahil  Badal

text: Bruh, thank you for always being there for me. You made BSBE hell of a lot easier. I wish you all the success!
author: Sahil  Badal

text:
Shobhit bhai, tere liye har word kam hai describe krne ke liye phir bhi try krun to you are Bakchod!, itni saari memories kaise likhun ek chote se memoir mai, phir bhi let me try - sbse pehle to bsbe lab ko interesting bnaya, phir sikhaya ki chill kaise mara jaye, phir sbse jyada to 3rd year mai time beeta, saal ke saare fest mai saath kaam kiya, lol, pehle udghosh mai to alg alg kaam kiya towards the same goal, phir antaragni mai kya security kri bhaiii, maza hi aagya, ankur ko bhi saath leliya, wo wing to wing bacchon ko ikkhata krna, phir OAT mai unke saath meeting krna, antaragni ke 4 din bakchodi pelna. Phir aaya best time during Techkriti, tere aur achyut ke saath itna maza aaya 3 mahine mai kaam krke, bacchon ka interview lene se unhe calling pr bulane tak, un bacchon ko jabardasti roke rkhne se lekr unhe gyaan batne tak, aur wo namit ke saath partiyan aur wo achyut ke room pr senior ke saath session kaise bhool skte hain... Lockdown mai to jo tera transittion hua as meme master, chumt master, multiple personality shubhita, gadar hi macha diye bhaiya aap to. 

Aaj agar IIM, aasmaan ki bulandiyon ko chuu rha hai to uska shrey sirf ek insaan ko jata hai, bakchod shobhit sachan... Pichle ek saal se tune nirantar, IIM pr memes pr memes diye hain, umeed hai aage bhi deta rhega, Lockdown mai waqt ka sahi upyog, ghante ka poorn istemaal koi tujhse seekhe. Thanks bhai sbki boring life mai entertainment lane ke liye. Isi treh kripa bnaye rkhna aur milte rehna...
author: Sahil  Badal

text:
I am very humbled and overjoyed by your memoir. But the downside was that you covered pretty much all the major incidentsğŸ˜‚. So i need to put on my storyteller hat nowğŸ˜œ
So my friend, brother, guide, inspiration motivator and hopefully we can add more things here in future.

I thought about when we met or when we became friends, and i also don't remember thatğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚.
Straight to the point now 
You have always inspired me with your work ethics, I remember you living almost perfect(in terms of utilisation of time) life during first year summer. Then during the internship season (ok..,I accept we didn't work hard enough ), but you still utilized your time better. Then do you remember development economics midsem , you had read everything and then you taught me(now please don't take your mind to grades) . I was amazed to listen your internship story, the kind of hard work you did was extraordinary. 

You have been a constant support right through. Without you people I would have never stood for the Senator. Do you remember, I was thinking of taking back my nomination and you simply asked what is the worst thing that could happen if I fight. You have  a niche' of saying right things at right timeğŸ˜‚. 
You were a great support during the lockdown and placement process. You were the one who told me about zerodha and kaggle. Without these I would surely not have been at Blackrock.
I have always loved the kind of connection you make with people. You put efforts for the friendships to work(I should also say relationships to workğŸ˜›). I really hope I learn this from you. 

Very thankful for that day when you asked all of us to sing solo(you people were a very good audience, I Would have surely laughed if I was in the audience ğŸ˜‚). I always thought about starting to write and thankfully I wrote my first à¤¶à¤¾à¤¯à¤°à¥€ that day. Whenever I am going to do my first performance, you are going to have a special mention 
On the storytelling part, I have been making stories from 11th class, it was just that for the first time I had an audience ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚

When I came to IITK, having very good friends was at the top of my list. And how lucky I am that we met. You were our only photographer in all the trips, you slept with us on train floor in front of toilet(remember thatğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚!!!!). You planned all the things we did in last 1.5 months. You are the glue of our group, you keep everyone together. You have this ability of thinking about the group before yourself.  Again, commendable!!! 

You are going to excel in anything that you do, but i really hope you find clarity soon. (And please don't overthink after making that decision)
I know, I haven't talked about relationships here (sorry ğŸ˜‚, à¤…à¤¬ à¤¶à¤¾à¤¦à¥€ à¤•à¥€ à¤‰à¤®à¥à¤° à¤¹à¥ˆ à¤¤à¥à¤®à¥à¤¹à¤¾à¤°à¥€)

And yes... Remember those endless discussions we had about issues India faces,we are surely going to work on them. So, take your life path accordingly ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚.

Thanks for making me a better human being.
Love.....
Chalo..... Badhiya(Bear hug) ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚
Shashi Shekhar

text:
Hi lambi,
It is very difficult to write a memoir for a person with whom you have spent most time.. xd!. Do you remember by the time orientation ended. we both were as if we have known for ages. Hum dono ne kitna kuch saath kiya h( ok.. in most of these I forced you ) .Remember blood donation camp, kanpur marathon, antaragani pr, tera bilkul man nhi tha. But, this was the best thing about you, you never said no. Yaad h tune to apna room change hi kar liya tha in 1st year, Shi bakchodi hoti thi ( rishi ne tujhe romantic movie dikhayi thi .. xD., aur teri shaadi...) . We were going to become roommates in 2nd year, but I guess it happened for best. Our friendship hasn't been any short of roller coaster ride. Bc, Maine jitna tujhe manaya h, utna kisi  ladki ko manata to pakka pat jaati. But, here comes your best trait, you have  such a tender heart, and you are such an emotional guy, ki last tk aate aate to ulta teri tension hone lag gyi thi..xD. 
Yaar, we both have been together in some difficult situations be it during internships, then lockdown, and then placements( har test ke baad randi rona krte the...xD). Thanks for being a constant support and partner during these times... Aur haan, jab teri placement nhi lag rhi thi, I was very stressed ki tu chod na de, but the way u handled yourself was lovely,<3. Bohot acha hua ki lockdown ho gya, nhi to hum log ludo hi khel rhe hote placement ke bhi time...xD.
Movies/ tv series- When we first met, I thought ki preparation ke baad aaya h to isliye itna interest hoga, but the kind of dedication,you showed for this, itne mei to pakka dassa aa jaata...xD. During 1st year you used to be 7 hrs on the field, and the rest of time on your laptop( i have never been able to understand how u could do it). Yaad h tune aur piyush ne compete kiya GOT khatam krne ke liye( tu hi jeeta hoga most probably).. Now , i have understood this, movies hobbies(...xD) nhi h lamba ki, they are integral part of u.
Sports- During the first year I was shocked to see ,how can someone have six pack abs without gym. But,you have always been athletic and zero figure. ..xD. text:
Hi Vipin,
My guardian, counsellor, brother and a lovely roomie.
Oh.. Vipin the way we talked when we first met, I never thought you would face the problems that you faced. Now when I think, I guess we connected the moment we met. Okay, really sorry for not understanding the gravity of the situation that u were in.  Respect for the way you came back(more on this later). Asking you to become my roommate in 2nd year, was the best decision I took. (I guess I have always been blessed...xD)
I used to think, that I have a lot of unnecessary drama in my life, and then I met you. I have seen you face every strange kind of problem a person could face( remember the struggle every sem during pre reg. or add drop, the laptop issue, you taking unnecessary difficult courses, and now the pg roll no.). So many experiences for a college life...xD).
You have always supported me, in everything I have done, listened to all the crazy ideas and theories that just keep coming into my mind(You are a very good listener). You have given me a feeling of home, a person with whom, I have shared everything( you are very good at keeping secrets). You have scolded me whenever I have lost my path( I loved it).  You never talked when I used to meditate. You have this exceptional trait of giving everyone space to grow and express. 
The hard work and energy that you would put in everything was exceptional, you would just keep studying until you understand the concept. I was always in awe of the calmness that you exhibited during exams(studying at 4 am in the morning ,still trying to understand concepts instead of remembering them) , remember you once got addicted to rolls( a strange addiction i would say), you are an excellent critic of movies. Your love for suspense thriller took you to Korean movies/shows. And remember u watched korean shows in the middle of exams. Oh. those were crazy times
I haven't seen anyone grown more than you in the past 4 years. Starting from an hindi medium background, struggling to understand the lectures in 1st yer to doing a minor in English literature. Struggling to talk / interact with people in the 1st year, to your present confident self. who would give these excellent 1 liners. A person who was going to leave IITK, to the present self who is going with a dual degree. A person needing psychological help in the first year to the present self ,who can counsel anyone.
Vipin, I know we are going to be friends for life. The way u supported me during internship time,lockdown and placement was very heartwarming. .
Brother, I am always there in every situation u need me. Just call/meet and yes, don't overthink.
I am never going to say goodbye to u.  I have no doubt, you are going to do great things in life. Always be your calm ,confident self. 
Love you brother...
And yes keep calling me....

text:
Real life Rancho of IITK â¤ï¸ Dassa, Violinist, reader, writer, athlete..... One man army h bhai tu toh. Ab to poori ki poori novel v publish hone ja rahi. 

Aesi bht kch baatein likh skta, but tune hi ek baar bola tha agar mai v baakiyon ki trah chaapu aur god bolu to tu mere room p nhi aayega phir. So aaj kch naya sunata hu. Itne chutiyap kiye tune College m, kyu bhai

Acads, har sem SPI 10, kya fayada hua iska? Bas life m thodi success mil jaayegi, kch m(b)illions aa jayenge, bas? CPI vs semesters ka plot bna, ek straight line. Itni simple equation , y = 10. Slope v 0 bc. Bhai ek baar try krta meri trah 7 laane ka. Kya adventurous academic life hoti. Meri dkh cpi vs semesters ki itni complex equation bn rhi, nikaal v nhi paaya. U missed it bro!

Punctuality , bhai yr, har kaam time p. Sare assignments deadlines s phle complete. No fun. Meri stories dkh(Reference OS assignment)- 12 bje deadline h, 11:50 p code compile kra without any errors, 1st run m hi correct output (tera bhai v thoda talented h), 11:55 p dabba power off ho gya bc, 12:03 p submit kra, phir deba ko mail , assignment accepted. Aesi kitne examples h. Procrastination k v apne mze hote h. Kaash tu ye sab kr paata!

Dedication- Again the same thing. Hmesha kch na kch krne ki chull rhti tujhe. One of the highest paying companies m PPO liya, uske baad v tujhe shaanti nhi mili. Palantir ka naam v nhi suna tha maine toh. Usme v internship final hi thi bas ye covid nhi hota. Entrepreneurship m v peeche nhi hi h tu. Kisi din linkedin p post krega, i am starting a new company (Ye seriously kr bro, mai shares kharidne k liye paise jama kr ra). Kya krega itna krke bhai, sab mohmaya h. Kvi kch unproductive kaam v try to kr jaise fan ko ghumte hue dekhna, random useless videos dkhna etc. Mai formal course v kra dunga. Time_Waste_101. Jab v mn ho ek email drop kr diyo, bhai h tu apna, free m krwaunga!

Aur v bht saari baatein h waise toh, but sab kch likhunga to depression m chla jaayega. Isiliye chhor deta hu. Lkin jyada pareshan hone ki baat nhi h, touch m rhiyo, dheere dheere sab thk ho jaayega.

Kch ache kaam v kiye h waise tune, to uska credit v bnta h. Jaise first year m dramatics join Krna, tujhe hi dkh k mai v chla gya tha! OS k assignment m help krne k liye shukriya(wo vfork, cfork to hota hi nhi mere s). CS202 m tune mujhe 3-4 baar bola code krne ko, end m khud hi aa gya tha room p saath m krne!  Aur v bht baar help kri h. Last ek month m mze v bht kre saath m. Holi, Uno, bluff , late night campus tour, sab yaad rhega!

Baaki chill h, mze Krna life m jhaaan v rho. Tune bola tha kisi v country m jao, india wapas aayega. Yaad rkhna. Mai idhar hi khin mil jaunga, kch na kch krte. Bas accent indian hi rkhiyo yr, ye 2 saal bahar rhkar jo British aur American accent m bolne lgte h chutiye lgte h!

Avi k liye itna hi! 

Signing off!
Tera chaapu bhai,
Shivam!

text:
Yo Saini!

At Kanpur Railway station, I checked the hall allocation list, my roommate's name was Abhishek Saini....Hmmm... Cool, milte hai isse!

Because of my own narcissism (Sorry for that), we started off with a communication gap and it prevailed for a long time... Dil bahut halka ho gaya tha when I finally apologized to you for not being a good roommate!

Dil ke bahut acche bande ho tum.

Yaad hai jab light chali gayi thi aur hum A5 me laundon ko daraane gaye the (mai white bedsheet odhkar bhoot bana tha) aur ek senior nikal ke aa gaya tha ek room se..."Y17 ho?....chalo nikalo"
...jo bhi ho, A5 waalon ki phat to gayi thi.

B6 ki roof pe kitni saari memories hai... Baarish ke baad ka sunset dekhna, Nitik aur wingies ke saath horror storytelling and some random bakchodi.

Blue world ki kahani bhi alag hi hai... especially IIT Gate pe mera first time beer try karna (yaar koi acchi beer suggest karte...Kingfisher bhi koi suggestion hai). Kitna darte hue pi thi maine, ki campus pahunchne tak bhand na ho jaaun; aur wo thi bhi itni zyada (lekin bhand phir bhi nahi hua)
and then the walk back to Hall (wo bhi seedhe seedhe nahi kiya gaya hum logon se). 

And remember the freshers' treasure hunt? Bas final destination par pahunch gaye, wahi badi baat thi! Also, Odyssey ka treasure hunt bhi kitna mazedaar tha, diwaar se clue waala paper hi phaad diya tha humne ;).

Aisi hi kitni saari yaadein hai tere saath; big and small, bitter and sweet!

Cheers to all the memories together.
author: Shivansh  Tripathi

text:

It's strange how we find such great friends in people we didn't expect to.
Thanks for always being there to listen to me  especially when I would come to you to rant about the shit in elections.
Keep up with your conviction for self-improvement; it's inspiring.
Whenever you read this and want to talk and rant about life...just give me a call!

text:
Discrete mathematics is the study of mathematical structures that are fundamentally discrete rather than continuous. In contrast to real numbers that have the property of varying "smoothly", the objects studied in discrete mathematics â€“ such as integers, graphs, and statements in logic â€“ do not vary smoothly in this way, but have distinct, separated values.Discrete mathematics therefore excludes topics in "continuous mathematics" such as calculus or Euclidean geometry. Discrete objects can often be enumerated by integers. More formally, discrete mathematics has been characterized as the branch of mathematics dealing with countable sets[4] (finite sets or sets with the same cardinality as the natural numbers). However, there is no exact definition of the term "discrete mathematics." Indeed, discrete mathematics is described less by what is included than by what is excluded: continuously varying quantities and related notions.

The set of objects studied in discrete mathematics can be finite or infinite. The term finite mathematics is sometimes applied to parts of the field of discrete mathematics that deals with finite sets, particularly those areas relevant to business.

Research in discrete mathematics increased in the latter half of the twentieth century partly due to the development of digital computers which operate in discrete steps and store data in discrete bits. Concepts and notations from discrete mathematics are useful in studying and describing objects and problems in branches of computer science, such as computer algorithms, programming languages, cryptography, automated theorem proving, and software development. Conversely, computer implementations are significant in applying ideas from discrete mathematics to real-world problems, such as in operations research.

Although the main objects of study in discrete mathematics are discrete objects, analytic methods from continuous mathematics are often employed as well.

In university curricula, "Discrete Mathematics" appeared in the 1980s, initially as a computer science support course; its contents were somewhat haphazard at the time. The curriculum has thereafter developed in conjunction with efforts by ACM and MAA into a course that is basically intended to develop mathematical maturity in first-year students; therefore, it is nowadays a prerequisite for mathematics majors in some universities as well.Some high-school-level discrete mathematics textbooks have appeared as well.At this level, discrete mathematics is sometimes seen as a preparatory course, not unlike precalculus in this respect.

Arey tumko adesh bolu ya adarshwadi.... roz subah uthna fir nahana fir mandir jaana, itna toh mandir ke pujari bhi nahi karte yaar. Pehli baar jab maine suna ki toh zindagi mai har din nahaya h toh mujhe toh tu ajeeb laga par fir jab train wala kissa suna toh bharosa ho gaya ki tu bhi chutiya hi h

Tu toh apna psuedo bhai h...tera bed mera hi toh h. Anime ki duniya mai haath pakadkar ghuswane ke liye bahut sukriya (aise hi logo ko jabardasti kimi no na wa dikhate rehna...), uske baad toh kaha hi rukna....detective conan...telegu movies....manga partners....aur kya kya cheeze.

Exams ki pehle ki wo raate jab tu chill maarke soo jaata tha aur fir subah uthkar humsab ke saath saraswati vandana sunna karta tha, wo bhi kya din the

Tu aise toh bahut nidarr h, NCC walo se ladd gaye aur bhi aise bahut jagah rahe h jaha tu ladda but yaar tu apne cycle ke liye nahi ladd paaya. Ye mujhe bahut bura laga. ;-(

Aur tu saale kabhi trip pe nahi aata h, humesha kuch na kuch bahana....jaldi se chal le IAS banane ke baad aur time nahi milega...next trip pe mana kiya toh dosti cancel

Chalo baaki yaadon ka kya h wo toh bante rahenge, acche se raho, UPSC nikalo, wing ka naam roshan karo aur kabhi chicken try karna ho toh pata hi h kiske paas aana h....tere roomie ka sudhikaran kar hi diya tha, tera bhi kar dunga.

text:
Raja babu, apse 1st year toh utna bat-cheet hua nahi par fir 2nd year mai hum dono tehre batti wale toh mulakaat toh honi hi thi, par asli ice breaker toh humara summer ka trip hi tha. Tereko mai naa chahte hue scooty partner mil gaya....kaafi mazza aaya tha yaar usme (wo gearge everest jagah hi chutiya tha usme kuch kiya nahi jaa sakta tha).

Fir 3rd year mai toh EE ke courses mai toh milkar hi nayya paar hui h humdono ki (tu kya digital samjhaya tha, mazza hi aa gaya tha). Raghu sahi mai chutiya h par tumne bacha liya usme.

Wo late night baate, tumhari love stories, wo bhi kya din the. Accha hua campus mai atleast akhri 1 mahine toh guzaar paye....baaki tumhari plannings ke kya hi kehne, photoshoot/airstrip dono time pe cover ho gayi.

Ab bas goa chalna h tumhare saath, tum rahoge toh group mai kisi ladki ki aane ka chances bhi badh jayega exponentially.

Aur kya milte h bangalore mai (hopefully mujhe bangalore mil jaaye....haan, ye rr hi h). Bas issi tarah mujhpe kripa banaye rakhna aur bhagwaan bhi tumpe apna krupa banaye rakhenge :-p
