text:
I am sure everyone knows how hardworking you are, how intelligent you are and yada yada yada (who the f**k doesn't ever get even close to getting a B what the f**k man!). 

I still remember the first memory I have of you was the first year when the Prof was trying to derive some detailed result, and midway in his second page he gets stuck. After few minutes of utter silence and confusion, I one guy (out of the odd 400) pointing out that he did a small error somewhere in the first page (!!) of the proof. The image I had of you then is the same I have of you know. Super focused and Super confident. 

I think we got to know each other better from the third-semester thermodynamics and in the time we spent together, I have come to know that you are one of the most helpful and honest guys I have ever met (and probably will meet). Sounds cliche? But people often underestimate the importance of being honest to yourself and others in terms of having a long-term friendship. That is something I will take with me forever. 

This memoir can't encapsulate how grateful I am for getting me through this undergrad (special mention to that horrible "apping" season of 2019-2020). I would never really understand why you chose to be friends with me, help and guide me in almost all walks of life, and share my love for food and music. 

My closest of friendships with everyone else was a result of chance, or a previous common experience, but with you it was purely organic and born out of awe and inspiration for me and I don't f**king know what from you. Nevertheless, I think I cherish this the most. I am sure I will do everything possible to keep it the same and make it grow even stronger than it is. 

Although we didn't get the chance to invade our beloved KD base in the 8th semester (I was anyways planning not to be around in my 7th), you have always been a text away, ready to help/offer your honest criticism. I hope we stay that way forever. Now I know, this won't change anything but please please please please please decide against the K-word we are not allowed to speak about.

Cheers to good times, that were and that will be.
author: Snehal  Raj

text:
Adesh bhai! I had the good fortune of having the best room mates in first year. Ek taraf Keshav, ek taraf tum.

Yaar sach bataun toh first few months were especially challenging for me because I had always been in my shell. But sharing my room with you, three of us being each other's closest friends and passing the time away in jokes and laughter was awesome. I remember tune apna chair sacrifice kar diya kyunki mujhe bed pe padhne ki aadat nahi this. NCC ke liye hum teeno ka rona dhona, Mini Militia ke games, tere school ke kisse, all of those a really good memories I have.

You are not like the most of us jo coaching ke badaulat aa  pahuche. Tune apne dam par phoda tha, apne dam par phoda hai and phodta rahega. Make sure you always remember that you are the literal embodiment of "cream of the nation" and once you put your mind to anything, you are surely going to ace it. 

Yaar tum jaise bando se mil paya, isiliye I think my stay at IITK has come to fruition. You are hardworking, care a lot about your friends, care a lot about your family and now are going to do a lot for this country. I still remember, how nicely you talk to your parents. Sometimes, as we pass the teenage phase, we start neglecting our family and but I learned from you that no matter what, family first.

You are an incredible human and although we didn't get a lot of time to catch up(last sem wapis campus bhi nahi aa paya mai) I will make sure that we meet soon. Ab toh aap bade aadmi banne waale ho so it might be tough for you to take time out, but because I have seen the kind of person you are and I have lived with you closely, I know you would.

Cheers dost
author: Snehal  Raj

text:
The first people from IITK I ever met were you and Ojha. Pehli baar milke aisa laga tha bhai, yeh kaafi shaant swabhaav wala banda hai. Quiet and introverted. After, all these years with you, I can safely say that it was just a facade in front of your parents ;p 

 Kaafi kharab dance kiya tha maine aur tune freshers me, our first group "project". Then, PClub ke game dev competition me tune single-handedly jeeta diya. Tere hi wajah se graphics ka course liya tha jiske liye aaj bhi Keshav gaali deta hai mujhe. I never quite understood how that complex brain of yours thinks. Before studying anything, tu bolta hai ki tujhe nahi aata, and fir thode din baad milo toh bolta hai, arre yeh toh itna obvious tha.

One of the most chaapu and overachiever guys I have met. You always strive for perfection in whatever you do be it coding a game/RM room, making some sketch of a chair infront of you in your notebook, or your work. Super intelligent, kyunki you always ace all the coursework on any project but at the same time, have some out of the ordinary notions regarding Tulsi and whatnot. Having said that, you should know that I respect you a lot.   Goa trip me tere jokes, mere maze lena, and your awesome driving skills hamesha yaad rahenge.

 Let's finalize on that trip in August and will surely arrange one in Europe. You are the most baniya guy I have ever met. Combine that with that big fat brain of yours and we have my richest friend and acquaintance. Baitha hoga kisi hedge fund ka ceo ban ke 10 saal baad toh it's better that hum sab tere se connected rahe :p. 

Grateful for having the opportunity to know people like you. To future times,

Cheers!
author: Snehal  Raj

text:
Bhai apan ek dusre ko Kota se jaante hai and I have seen your progress. Starting from a lower batch to getting the highest rank. You have managed to continue on that trajectory even at UG, and I am sure you will continue it even further along in your professional life.

We didn't have a lot of interaction in Kota but have great memories from the place, and I share that nostalgia with you. We started Undergrad with a freshers dance performance and maannn that was epic. Maybe people don't notice it often, but you can make people laugh and have made me laugh more than anyone in this college. I love your storied be it some incidents about your wing, Subhajit Sir, almost dying while river rafting or our inside jokes.


You are really pure from heart and have always been the most innocent guy.  You always speak about whatever you are feeling. Combine that with you intelligence and that makes you one of the rarest people anyone would come across. You always somehow make time to both work your ass off acing any task that you are assigned with and enjoy yourself to the fullest. You value friendships and relations, and I hope we maintain this friendship we have forever.

 Mai aur keshav ek team and tu aur durgesh ek team she shuruwat ki thi assignments and projects karne ki and that overall group has remained the same ever since  (Ayush had a wildcard entry). 

Every group needs a guy that leads from example and I am sure you already know it, but your are that guy in our group. Whatever task we are assigned to, you make sure that we do it super well and that's a quality which I think you should be proud of.  In this trip that we had, I saw how you were carrying us all. You were the one doing the hard stuff: managing our itinerary, negotiating prices, or taking care no one from our group is left out.  Let's make sure we have many more trips in the future.

I am indebted to IITK (and Kota ) for giving me the opportunity to meet people like you. Stay the same and prosper (which I am sure you would)

Cheers Harshaga
author: Snehal  Raj

text:
There is no hiding how close we are, is it? One of the things I am most grateful for in my entire stay at IITK is the perchance that I got "The" Keshav Bansal as my roommate. That roll of dice, gave me a lifelong friend/mentor/role model and I am super grateful.

Everyone noticed that you were really shy and reserved in the first year but I always felt that you spoke when needed. You do not have any drive whatsoever to keep impressing people around you by talking and have believed in doing the work. Before that, this was something that I had only read or heard about, but with you I have seen it from my own eyes day in and day out. I proudly use you as an example while talking to anyone about what we should strive to be.


Many are humble from the outside, but you see that no one is always humble as you get to know them better. Well, I can attest to the fact that in the four years that I have been your roommate and closely worked with you on countless assignments and projects, you are humble through and through (even to the extent that I sometimes have to convince you of your caliber). 


I would have never learnt as much as I did, throughout the course of my stay here, if I hadn't met you. Your intelligence, ability to power through any task and your downright humbleness is unmatched to anything I have ever seen. And in addition to all of this, you have always been a great friend to me and we have shared countless laughs together. So believe me when I say there is literally nothing that makes me happier than being of any importance whatsoever in your life.  I have seen you transform into a more confident, funnier and a more chill-friendly version of yourself over the undergrad and I like to believe I have had some role to play in that.

There ought to be kinder people at the top of the food chain, and therefore I wish all the success to you.

I still have a lot to learn from you and will, therefore will try my level best to preserve this bond that we have.

Cheers Gawd!
author: Snehal  Raj

text:
One of the nicest human being on campus!

The first memory I have of you is I think our first wing interaction seniors ne karwaya tha and ek bhaari awaaz wala patla dubla ladka. Your voice is opposite to your personality. The first time we talked about football was on the mess table and although it is sad ki you aren't a madrid supporter you have never been irrational in your analysis and passion. (Which is rare trust me)

I remember football,tech, music and dance to be the most common things we share, baaki tu hamesha meri leta toh rehta hi tha for being the 6 pack figure that I am.  I really enjoyed talking to whenever we met and saath me Shubham ki lene me kya maza aati thi.  Bhai bohot kam log hote hai tere jitne ache and dildaar. I have seen how you would never shy away with sharing whatever you own be it tere snacks, tere headphones etc. Tere senheisers ka use I think tere se zyada baaki sab ne kiya hai. Dil se ameer ka hone ka sahi matlab terese seekha hai maine.

Itna kind and selfless hona and on top of that being so intelligent is extremely rare bro. Last sem ka plan kiya tha woh toh pura nahi ho paya but jald hi milenge.  Humara Tomorrowland saath dekhne ka plan yaad toh hai na? Let's add an el classico to that list and make it happen. I will forever remember you as the great human being you are who I had the good fortune of meeting. Stay the same bro, you are rare.

Cheers lambe baal wala messi.
author: Snehal  Raj

text:
Bhai I don't know if you know it, but you are one of my best friends at IITK. Jitna bhi samay Kota ya Kanpur me guzara hai, isse yeh samajh aagaya ki intelligent and acha dono hona bohot rare hai. And you are one of these rare occurences.

Mujhe yaad the great partition of hagga, hagga ke iss paar waale B bot and uss paar waale and some other C bot. The irony is partition hone ke baad hi tumhe ache se jaana and really got to know a golden-hearted individual. Super helpful to anyone, really good natured and always honest and wanting to learn. Tumhara aur mera family background same raha hai and uss wajah se bhi we got close but the thing I like about you most is you make me feel special. Tumhare jaise dost sabke hone chahiye bhai jisse khul ke baat kar sake and important matters pe discuss kar sake. I have the tendency to speak a little more than what is required but you never disliked me for that.

Tum jitna izzat mujhe dete ho, I am sure I don't deserve that but it makes it all the more important for me to continue this friendship for long. Mai beemar pada tha ek baar and tumne kaafi madad ki thi. Kabhi bhi mai thoda anxious hu ya stressed hota tha, toh tumhare room aake hagge ke uss paar waalon se baat karke and hass ke acha lagta tha. Last sem agar campus me hote toh aur bhi bohot saare memories banate but alas we couldn't.

I am sure bade aadmi ban jaoge tum and I think tumne bhi mere saath 10 million lives wala vaada kiya tha. So let's catch up sometime later this year by means of trip and decide on what we are going to do about that promise.

Cheers bhai
author: Snehal  Raj

text:

And sach bolu toh I went ahead with joining the contingent majorly because of you. That was one of the best experiences of my stay here. Forming a team just hours before the deadline, and then going ahead and winning the gold. Raat bhar jag jag ke we completed that presentation and then subah jaake we won the event.

I am sure you already know that you are a really good soul. Just want to reiterate that please stay the same. Milte hai jald. 

Cheers

text:
Dear Roomie,
On our first day at IITK, you showed up late. As everyone was getting to meet their roommates, I wondered, nice if he doesn't show up, I'll have the room to myself ğŸ˜œ, but then you did show up.
Soon after the end of that beautiful 10-day long orientation began the classes. You seemed really into the acads. You used to fall asleep while studying on the chair. At times I was really amazed by your hard work and dedication to your studies.
Remember the time you received the phone call from hall 1? ğŸ˜‚
GPL sabki leni hoti thi par jab khud ki baari aati toh waha kuch na kuch problem ho hi jaati thi. 
Experience to tune sab kar liya heart break se lekar paaji kai sath stalking bas ab Canadian NRI se shaadi baaki hai ğŸ˜‚ (bulana mat bhulna ğŸ˜œ)
Know that I respect you for the way you embrace your weaknesses aur baaki aage toh fod dega tu mehnat se.
Take care and all the best to your Canadian wife ğŸ˜‚

text:
Thank God I met you and that too in the first year !! Do you even know how much I relate to you and how easy it is to be my original self around you. Thanks for being the person who always makes me feel at home <3. Remember the elaborate discussions we had at OAT and do you still remember the club we formed (let it remain a secret though)? Going to literally every fest together, going for most of the quizzes, lectures and labs together and definitely going to canteens together. Ye sab moments were enough to cheer me up for the day. I miss those days so much.
We shared so so many moments together and I love each one of them jaise ki our canteen visits and our shared love for Special fry masala maggi and cold coffee. Har lecture se pehle tumhara mere liye wait krna, yaa lecture hall m always saving a seat for me  yaa cycle bhaga kar lecture hall se mess pahuchna so that breakfast naa miss ho jaaye, saath m movies dekhna after exams, enjoying so many fests together or simply just chilling in your room and what not !! Thanks a lot for being the person I could always hangout with ! Stay the really hard-working, awesome, caring and helpful person that you are !
P.S. Bahut photos bhej di tumne acche khaane ki, jald hi milte hai and and treat me with the tasty cakes and food you make. 
Lots of love !!
Sunamya.

Wo Cricket match bhi yaad hai, uske baad kiya Hall 13 ka breakfast bhi. Kaafi achha time tha, jitna kaam kiya tha saath me utni yaade bhi hai. Keep doing great stuff.
author: Suyash  Singh

text:
"A guy who dropped obsession to know the importance of life, happiness and relationships." - Can a bio get more apt! I still remember seeing the passion to build a team and taking it to heights in your eyes the day we sat together in Hall 2 Common Room. If there is one team of all I know, which can make a Quadruped move in a span of 2 hrs with a defective Maxon motor and a faulty circuit, it's that Robocon team. And it didn't come together, I was made - by us! Couldn't have imagined pulling off an inch of what we did in Robocon, had you not been there. I guess, janta toh me pehle hi tha ki Saini is the most passionate guy when it comes to Robotics, dekh bhi liya un 8-9 mahino me. Starting off from scratch is never easy. Never imagined ki ek team bana denge 10 din me jiske liye 550+ recruitment applications aa jayengi and SnT code me 1 question bhi ban jayega (ab reveal kar sakte hai na? xD). Wo SnT code wali raat bhai, kitne maze kiye the.. and uske baad, the entire Robocon journey. 2.5 saal ki campus life me 1 saal to MR1 MR2 hi banate rahe xD. But it has been one of the most centerpiece learnings of my campus life, and all credits to you! Wo saare birthday celebrations yaad hai, saari meetings me backchodi yaad hai, saare serious discussions bhi yaad hai xD
You are a truly special person. Bohot kind, caring and courageous. Tujhse hi kaafi confidence mila hai kaafi cheeze karne ka. Thank you â€œSainiâ€, for making me believe that a bunch of inexperienced guys can actually create an autonomous bot and a quadruped from a nominal budget and in an unrealistic time frame. Ever grateful for everything. You have a brave heart and I know, youâ€™ll do great in life ahead and forever! Aur Robocon ke reunion pe milte hai fir xD
author: Suyash  Singh

text: Aman bhai, kya bolun yaar tumhare baare me.. Itna chaapa hai tune, itna transformation and itna success gradient shayad hi kisi ne achieve kiya hoga. Hats off to your hard work and dedication bhai. You have always inspired me to push my limits. Your undying attitude, motivation for learning, absorbing capacity and thinking skills have always made me feel the unlimited potential in you. Hamari mulakat Robocon ke recruitment ke baad hi hui thi, Vivek ke through shayad. Initially shayad tu thoda inconfident tha, shayad baaki log sahi se nhi samjhte the but tujhse baat karke humesha ek dediccation wali feel aayi hai. Apne designs ko lekar, processes ko lekar, manufacturing methods ko lekar itne discussions hue hai ki mujhe kaafi seekhne ko mila hai. Tu hamesha question karta tha and cheezo ko sahi krne ki koshish krta tha. Tere inputs and efforts ke bina MR1 would never have existed. Last me jab MR1 me mere saath tu tha tab hamesha I felt supported. I knew ki mujhse jyada tu dekh rha hai sab, tujhe fikar hai cheezo ki. Kaafi kuchh seekha hai bhai tumhare saath kaam karke. Robocon ke baad kaafi confidence aaya hai mujhme bhi. Mujhe apna LHC Foyer me discussion yaad hai, intern ke time. Mujhe pata tha ki tu chaapega hi, kyunki kuchh bhi challenge ho, You never give up. Keep this determination towards your goals intact. Youâ€™ll reach much greater heights. Aur ab bade aadmi ho gye ho bhai, toh hume mat bhul jaana. Yaad kar liya kro kabhi kabhi. Fir zarur milenge bhai ME, Y17 ke reunion pe.

text:
Tere liye kya memoir likhna hai bhai. Apna safar to iss IITK ki journey se kaafi pehle se shuru ho gya tha, and kaafi baad tak milte hi rahenge for sure. But theek hai, aaj tak aise mauka nhi mila kyunki hum dono hi kaafi cool kism ke log hai xD Jay jitni emotional baate nhi likhni aati par haan, tum ho toh bilkul alag personality. 11th me toh darr lagta tha bhai, isaan hai ya bhagwan. Sab pata rehta hai, sab padha hua hai.. Lagta tha wapas JEE de rha hai humare saath, ek do baar nikal hi rakha hoga pehle xD Wese mujhse jyada darr BNM Sir ko lagta tha tbh (haha, lol).
Anyway, wo bhi â€œbadiyaâ€ din the, kyunki tumhare saath sab badiya hi hota hai. JEE ki prep time ki best memories tere saath hi hai kyunki tu hi itna serious tha poore batch me xD. Tests ke baad paper discuss krna toh 11th se hi hai. Pehle sirf meri faadta tha, baad me poore wing ki (specially, buchas fuffa) xD
Last paper ke baad CP ke samne khade hoke â€œAll the Bestâ€ bola tha jab, tab laga tha shayad last time mil rhe hai.. but kya coincidence tha bhai! Same IIT, Same Hall, Same Wing. â€œHum Alwar se aaye hai!â€ will remain our tagline. College me bhi nhi sudhre tum (actually, bigde). Abhi tak wahi Sabhay ho jo sabse jyada magta hai, sabke doubts solve krta hai (CP se hi hai ye to), sab padha sakta hai before exams (kuchh ECO wale log toh isi bharose pass ho rhe hai EE ke courses me xD). But bhai, tera dedication _/\_, mene toh kaafi pehle chhod diya tha but you took this to another level. No doubt you deserve to be at the Top in whatever you do ahead. Your hard work shows, in whatever you have achieved. Kaafi inspire kiya hai bhai itne saal. Tum kar rhe the itni mehnat shayad isiliye sabne kr li thodi bohot jitni ki hai. Robocon ka MPID algorithm toh alag level tha xD xD. Tujhse jyada cool, calm and courageous banda nhi dekha bhai. Kaafi pessimistic hai bas, kabhi toh achha soch liya kar. EE360 me tere hisaab se fail hi ho rhe the hum log at one point. Glad to have travelled this journey with you and literally bhi IITK tak ka safar (Train wala bhi aur life wala bhi) hamesha tumhare saath hi rha hi aur aage bhi rahega (Train wala bhi, Train-Bus-Air wala bhi - Alwar to Aurangabad ka algo figure out kr lena bas). Theek hai, agar yahan tak tumne padha hai (which I doubt,.. beech me chala gya hoga PMI ka project krne), to ye bhi sun lo sehat ka dhyaan rakho aur jeevan me ab thodi aish krlo (#taalis lakh ka sahi upyog krne ke liye tau ko sampark kare, investment se expenditure ki saari maths bata denge). Theek hai bhai, â€œbadiya!â€.

text: Bro, I didn't find your name. This post is one english comprehension exercise you just have to go through, okay? Like I said, I made really, really unlikely friends in the last month. I'd say without you, I'd never have gone through one of the horrible phases so easily, and came out of it really easily. Thank you for standing up for me in front of him and his friends (I loved it, and it'd probably be one of the highlights of your career lol). Though, it seems silly now, I can just go on and on about it. I liked just sitting and existing when our wing was asleep, and hall 1 terrace was legit soul-baring, and the whatsapp scolding was <3. Don't study or work too hard (I say this to everyone to make myself feel better about being vella and jobless) and keep meeting up.

text: I probably didn't give a shit to the family tree in my first year, not knowing hindi made me get out of all the stupid stuff. But, I am glad to have met you. I hope this "closure" finds you safe and well. 

It's been four years since I came across your acquaintance, and my first impression still fits very well.  A guy with a set motive, focussed towards goal, hard-working, and one who can sleep on anyone's bed except on his own.

Let's meet soon and catch up for more "Toh" moments...
All the Best!

text:
Yo dost! 
Well if I go on writing then my hands would surely be in trouble typing on xD
But let me cut through the centre and put some of the most memorable stuffs here.
The voyage begins(Y-1): Well we are just cousin brothers in IITK fam lineage. Sailing through tough times, from sharing headphones to coming back Delhi in Shatabdi the stage was getting setup for the most defining times to come!
Y-2: Well we become SGs! Then comes the reporting day and we cycle through the lanes to reach Hall 13 in a cold morning. Not forgetting the fact that you cycled standing up( bcz of recovering from a back operation) we accompanied each other proving to be the best of the brothers. The whole year was full of ups and downs & surely highs and lows :p but nevertheless the memories which were being formed were the ones to stay forever.
Y-3: Changing circles, changing hobbies were underway. You became Core Team CS, i couldn't. I went to Techkriti, however, half-heartedly. Days passed and each of us explored our interests. We met but less often but the camaraderie was intact. We went high but not so often. Gradually, as a part of human nature, the circles played their roles and a point came when the circumstances created a misunderstanding which couldn't be removed soon. Facing consecutive lows, I was pushed to another place alone and away from the best of my peeps. Naturally, nothing was same. Not even the world which was hit by COVID lol
Y-4: We have moved ahead with the same virus around us and now even more virulent. But, maybe it helped us to connect once again and did something which may not have been that easy!

Lol, if I see we enjoyed a major part of college together and I hope we are in touch in future!
Stay safe
See you bro :)

text:
Kuch to log kahengeâ€¦ Logon ka kaam hai kahna.
Same with me, yaar tu nahi to college kaafi khaali khaali hota. Tujhe follow karte karte photography kar li(thoda utkarsh ke karan bhi). Tere hi kaaran galaxy aur antaragni kar li and most important nashedi bhi tere karan bana(tere alawa aur koi iske liye aisa motivate kar hi nahi sakta tha). Matlab ye sab agar mere life me nahi hota to pata nahi college life ka kya hota.
First year ke baad jab room allocation ho raha tha, mai tere se roomie banne ke liye puch nahi pa raha tha, mujhe lag raha tha ki tune kisi aur ke saath plan kar liya hoga? But andar se feeling aa rahi thi ki apni bond next level banegi and see nowâ€¦. I was right.
Ek bhi birthday me IIT me nahi tha, lekin tujhe gift jaroor chahiye, waah!!  Raat ki parties aur wo luv stories(waise kaafi sahi jodi hai teri,"KAAFI"), Pata nahi mai kitne saare bet haara hoon tujhjse, lucky you, dinner ek saath karna, dp bhi saath change karna, Galaxy saath jeetna, unscheduled movies show, tujhse taash me haarna(ek bas tu hi hai jiske opposite mere  stats kharab hai yaar) aur haan ab room ke lights to mere hi honge...........
Bhut hi jyada shandaar tha college and you were almost in every beautiful memory. I can't imagine IIT without you. Ye sab to mai aise hi likh raha, as you know mujhe likhna nahi aata leki fir bhi you should know that you are very very special to me.
Until next time,

text:
Yo JASSI BOI,
Bc muje day 1 of IITK se pata tha tu kuch banega apne college mein aur akir kar tu bana GENSEC. Now let me tell you why I thought about that, starting se u were pretty much involved in taking the positions like muje yaad hai jab harlem shake kia tha u were leading the group and then dozeball you were captain and at that time I was like isme leadership qualities hai bc and then wing wala kuch tha u and saurav, I think wing coordinator, LOL muje yad nhi hai.

"bhai bhai plz mera TA banade" bhaut randirona kia tha TA ke course mein. I can remember monday ko apna TA hua karta tha and hum do chutiye raat bar TT khelke 4 baje TA banane baith te they and poori raat randirona karte they, thanks to tushar woh jaldi banaleta tha.
First year mein then apun kaffi time CC mein pada karte they mid-sem and end-sem both, suraj bhi apne saath hi tha. Fir bc raat ko doaa canteen jaatein they and I can remember ur words:- " yaar mein abhi addha ghanta so raha, 30 min hotein hi uta dena" and after 30min u know what was your reaction, "abhe 30 min hogaye itni jaldi, abhi aur thoda 5 min sone de"

aur bhai first year mein koi class lagai bhi this kya apun ne, bc math ki class toh 3:45 pe saath jaatein they attendance lagane, who attendance wale bhaiya bolte they "ki bhaiya app toh lecture hall mein they hi nhi " and we were like "bhaiya hum piche they attendance aai hi nhi waha tak"

Aur wing ke sath volleyball khelna aur apun saath mein TT toh bhaut pela hai sala jo bhi senior aata tha sabko pela hai.

Aur bhaiya humein bhi tips dedo GF wagerah banane ke, ek kitab likho tum bhai, bestseller ban hi jayegi, ROMANCE+ACTION+THRILLERf, LoL.......

Bhai aap itna workout kaise karlete ho, humein enlighten karo, itna enthusiastic ho aap is field mein, bc football se lekar volleyball se lekar cycling trips that u had, brilliant yar. EK bar apun ko bhi chalna hai trip pe PLAN banao JASSI boi. Aur chapu toh tum ho hi paidaishi ...bc apne 3year mein GEN-SEC ban gyaa, aur 2nd year mein bc 3year ke launde ko election mein hara dia.....wah bete wah....it will be written down in the history of IITK..ki ek launda aaya tha patiala se m** chod ke chala gaya

Aur last mein hamare GYM trainer bane they bhai aap, "Gand aur chatti thodi si bar nikal...."  LOL...

ek advice bas yahi dunga :- Keep exploring and learning new-new stuffs and start reading a book!!!
aur abb placement aa rahe hai toh badiya se prepare karo aur result toh redundant hi hai ki usme bhi tum chapogey hi!! 
jadli milte hain bhai, till then wish u a lot of success in life and remember "SAB YAAD RAKHA JAAEGA"

FROM-
BABA BOI

P.S:- bhai TT khelte hai jab milengey!! Aur trip ka plan banao

Tera hum log ne kaafi mazaak Udaya h aur kuch nicknames bhi Rakhe hain but ab wo hi mazaak humein tujhe yaad rakhne mein madad karenge.

text:
Dramatics club ki summer coordi ko pranaamğŸ™
Teri vocabulary ko dhyaan mein rakhkar likh rha hu so thank me later.

Hands down bina coordi hote hue jitna kaam tune kiya h utna to coordi hote hue kuch logon ne nhi kiya(not taking any names thoughğŸ˜›). Iss baat k liye to salute hona chahiye ek, shit koi emoji nhi h salute waala.

Anyhow, jitna tune improve Kara h both in Hindi and in acting wo to hum log ne last din drameve2 first year waala nukkad dekh kar hi samajh liya tha. Drameve2 ki dancing expert se lekar Galaxy ka â€œlo aa gye feminism ka nukkad lekarâ€ tak kaafi lambi journey rahi h aur wo bhi tune bina koi compulsion aur full enthu k saath Kari hâ¤ï¸

Baaki tune bahut saare assignments aur quizzes/exams mein madad Kari h uske liye thanks to Banta h. ğŸ™ğŸ™ğŸ™

Waise to main offending aur dominating aur misogynistic(?) baatein karne k liye wrongly famous hu, to agar kabhi anjaane mein tujhe Maine aisa kuch bola ho to maar kar denağŸ˜…. Bombay waali bakchodi hone k baad tu hum log k team mein thi ye yaad karke Abhi bhi kaafi achcha lagta h, nhi to main aur Rochak to nikal hi lete campus se. But uss kaand k baad jis din tune mere room main mere aur Rochak k liye bhand ho kar BT lekar ro rhi thi to sach mein g*nd fat gyi thi. Hum dono k liye itna load lene ki zaroorat nhi h. Agar nikal bhi jaate to bas itna fark hota ki dindor k saath main bhi UPSC ki tayyaari kar rha hotağŸ˜…ğŸ˜…

author: Varun  Jain

text:
Ye memoir likhne ka space hamari memories sambhal nhi payega. Aur apni jaisi personality h to uske hisaab se jyada rr karna bhi sahi nhi lag rha. Jitna kam maza mujhe room par baithke aata h aur jitne jyada easily tere ghar waale tujhe bahar nikalne dete hain apan Milne to waale hain hiğŸ˜. To ab memories likhne se achcha kuch plans likh rha hu jo hum already kar chuke hain but mere fir se karne ki ichcha h.

Pehle to wo December 2019 k pehle 10 din recreate to karne hi hain. As usual main to sober hi rahunga kyunki kisi ko to 3 kutton ko sambhalna hi padega.

Rishikesh waali rafting fir se karte hain. Aur bc iss baar lamba plan banayenge aur unlike last time ek legit jagah party karne jayengeğŸ˜›.

Apna sizzle dazzle brownie bhi rhe gya. Wo to ab shayad campus mein hi afford kar payenge apan log, unless tune placement mein 30lpa score kar liya(best of luckğŸ¤)

Lucknow jaisi trip fir se honi chahiye. Kisi jagah pahunch pe fir chal chal k jo achchi jagah h wahan khane jao, fir bc in 3 din mein 4k Kharcha kar do to bhi chill h. Lekin iss baar KT nhi aaya to pakka uske ghar pahunch jayengeğŸ˜‚

Z-square k pass ki lassi peete hain. Uska raasta mujhe thoda thoda hi yaad h but wo first year ki tatti skit k liye samaan laane k depression k baad alag hi chaap diya tha uss lassi ne. 

Fir se waisa ad banate hain(new shop c waala), matlab ad nhi banayenge, kuch banate time waisi (sacred games k Nawaz waala bencho) waali bakchodiyan fir se karenge. Bothra ki to g*nd maarli thi humne tab. But iss baar bc thoda comfortable ho jaana camera k saamne.

Library k baad doaa chalenge. Ya waisa hi similar experience kisi aur setting mein. Jitna padhte nhi the utna to doaa mein time barbaad kar dete the. Kabhi main tu kt aur Dindor, kabhi Aishwarya k saath, to kabhi bas hum teen hi. Isliye bc latter semesters mein Maine room par hi padhna shuru kar diya tha.

Standup karna bsdk tu. Saath mein script likhenge. Teri wajah se mujhe karna pad gya tha Roorkee mein, although I enjoyed it anyway but still, tujhe karne ki zaroorat h. Kuch nhi to bas 2 min k open mic mein apna best joke hi suna dena but shuru karo bc. Kab tak g*nd fategi tumhariğŸ˜¤

Aage k plans thode chote scale par hain aur kuch to impossible se hain but bear with me. 

Uss din ki tarah skywalk par baarish mein fir se bulla kaatenge. But iss baar apne Baaki laundo ko bhi saath mein le lenge. Alag hi experience tha wo bhi.

Fir se first year ki tarah soc ki (literally)surprise quiz dekar aate hain. Chutiyon ki tarah time pass karenge fir 10 min baad hall mein ghuske gaand fadwayenge.

Fir se waise canteen mein baithke 2 scenes likhte hain. Isi bahane kuch sketch to bana hi lenge. Fir bas 2 actors ki zaroorat hogi shoot karne k liye.

2.2 k 2-4 draft aur bana lete hain. Last mein Raja waala to anshumali ne copied bolkar kata diya tha. But aaj tak samajh nhi aaya wo kahan se copied h.

Flow ki maa ki ch*t Karke ek aur kalua inspired bas bakch*di waala scene bana lete hain. But iss baar kaali pahadi k peeche hi milenge. Construction ka kaam khatam ho gya hoga ab tak to.

Volleyball khelte hain. Jaise hi thoda khelna seekha bc campus hi band ho gya. Smash maarna to seekh hi nhi paaya main.

Squad2.0 banate hain, iss baar Bothra ko nhi lenge. KT k taane nhi sunne fir se. 

Fir se sabke saath poker/mafia/pictionary/csgo/red King/bluff/almost any other game khelte hain.

Fir se canteen chai peene chalte hain. Lalaji ki cheese ball khayenge aur sting bhi le lenge.

Fir se kisi joke ko tab tak extend karte hain jab tak wo funny se bahut jyada door chala jaaye.

Fir se sabke saath ek mjo ka episode ya meri suggest ki hui movie dekhte hain(iss baar pakka mast movie suggest karunga)

Fir se ek bhand night karte hain. Main to obviously sober rahunga tab bhi.

Fir se ek room mein baithkar Apna apna dabba lekar ghanto tak kuch bhi nhi karte hain.

Until next time. Bc BT kam lo aur Bhagwan Kare tumhari body ban jaaye.

CiaoğŸ˜›
author: Varun  Jain

text:
Jai jinendra dostğŸ™ğŸ™
Bhai jaisa nostalgia tune yaad dila diya maza hi aagya. But ab samajh nhi aa rha ki main kya likhunga.
Apne chaaro coordinators k 4C2 combinations mein apni hi sabse kam Banti thi but still apan log ne kaafi kuch saath mein kar liya. Jaise log kehte hain â€œlike repelâ€ isliye mujhe hamesha se lagta h ki hum dono kaafi similar hain in many respects (ab ye tareef h ya bezzati ye tujhe hi decide karna padegağŸ˜‚ğŸ˜). 
Anyway, apna to mujhe dram treat aur Diwali treat k liye sabke room par saath mein bheekh maangna hi sabse jyada yaad aata h. Anshumali k saath almost jugnu ho jaata merağŸ˜°. Bc tere jaate hue maine anshumali k room se awaaz lagayi thi tujhe aur mujhe aaj bhi 95% surety h ki tune suna aur respond nhi kiya thağŸ˜¤. Bansal k 500 teen hazaar mein convert karaye the. Aur finally bc Anaichas waale ko choona lagaya thağŸ¤ªğŸ¤ª

Antaragni k result announce hone k baad sirf hum dono hi fate the, pata nhi ye kyun yaad aa rha h but â€œI feel you broâ€ bolne ki ichcha hi rhi h uss time k liyeğŸ˜‡ Apna interIIT ka second scene shayad iklauta tha jo humne saath mein kiya tha. Sahi tha yaar wo. Usse pehle December mein bitaye 10 din to hamesha hi yaad rahenge. Fir se karenge yaar wo. Rochak Nipun ko bhi bola h Maine to bhai aa jaana kabhi to. Maza aayega.

Bas bhai humko bhool mat jaana (waise lakshan to tumhare waise hi hain bc). Tum log agar bhand nhi hoge to hamara kaarobaar bhi nhi chalegağŸ˜. Baaki I am always available agar Teri kabhi ichcha ho baat karne ki, but you know that anyways. 

Letâ€™s not call this a goodbye. Abhi hum zinda h aur Abhi to kaafi baar tujhe tokenge hamesha ki tarah firse koi bakchodi karne k liye. But hamesha ki tarah kaat mat dena bhai hamarağŸ˜”.

Aasha karte hain tumhara pet tumhari ichcha anusaar badh jaaye.

Apan ne jo 2nd year drameve1 mein scenes improvise Kare the wo bhai hamesha yaad rahenge. Uske alawa to jo apni antaragni mein anginat scenes banaye wo yaad rakhna to thoda mushkil h. Teri ccd waali bakchodi ko to bhool nhi sakta, na main aur na hi ktğŸ˜¤. 

Baaki kabhi C 408 aane ka man Kare to mere darwaaze to hamesha khule hain. Tumko aane ki mehnat karni padegi. Bc har baar ki tarah 10 phone mat karana aur aa rha hu bolkar ek ghante baad mat aana.

Baaki yaar ab Iâ€™m out of words. Kya likhein jise likhne se na mujhe BT ho na tujhe padhne mein ho.

Kabhi BT ho ya kisi ki g*nd maarni ho ya fir kuch nhi ho karne ko to hum to hamesha haazir hain. Placement lagne tak to bc main hi ungli karta rahunga tum log ko. Until next timeâ€¦. Rafting karenge fir se bc. Yaad rakhna.

text:
Krishan urf Kanhaiya, kya bole ab aapke bare m aap to prabhu h XD. BTop pr FBM ki scholarship se shuru huyi batein socha nhi tha ki itni anmol dosti de dengi. Krishan se kab Kanhaiya pr pahunch gye pta hi nhi chla. Tumne IITK ka har kona dekha h. Har jagah ko explore kiya h. Tumhara room pr hi movie nights hoti thi kyunki roomie to room pr rehta nhi tha. Kanpur ki shopping aur late pahunchkr theatre m dekhne wali movies bahut yaad aayengi. Hall 2 ka canteen band hone ke karan apn ne na jane kitne kathi roll mangwaye. Har raat krte the ki kal se nhi mangwayenge aur phir agli raat bhi yhi bat bolte the. Abdullah ke biscuit-chips drawer m bacha kr rakhte the taki koi aaye aur kha jaye. Raat ko mess ke saamne se paani lana aur series ke gappe marna. Mene jo bhi random series dekhi h, unko bas tumhe hi recommend kr skta ho kyunki aur koi to dekhta nhi tha unko. Kafi multi-dimensional ho tum. Tumhara bas chale to sare adventure ke kaam abhi poore kr lo. Apne kaam ko lekr kafi passionate rehte ho. Log chahe kuchh bhi kahe pr tum apni bat pr datkr khade rehte ho. Aese hi thodi SOS ke coordi bne ho ğŸ˜. Y to aese hi h, y to aese hi h, krte krte kafi kuchh chamatkar kiye tumne, chahe Panasonic ki intern ho ya Harvard ki conference. Khi pta chle bad m UPSC bhi tumne aese hi nikal di. Chhoti chhoti baton se lekr badi badi mushkilon m hmesha support kiya h. No matter what the situation is, tum kbhi motivate krna nhi chhode, you always had my back ğŸ¥°â¤.
Bahar jane se pehle muh dhokr apne special comb se hmesha bal sawarte the, halanki bad m bhi wo wese hi rehte the ğŸ˜œ. Aasha h ki Tumhari, meri aur rajat ki dosti aese hi aage chalti rahegi. Sadly na to Manali trip ho payi aur na hi Dehradun wali, iss bar jab mauka milega tab pkka chlenge. Hoping to meet you soon.
Ab life ka ek nya safar shuru hone wala h. All the best for your future endeavours buddy. Aur koi glti huyi ho to maaf kr dena prabhu, apna Sudarshan chakra se prahar mt kr dena hum pr ğŸ˜‚.

text:
Naam h Piyush, pr aapko pyar se sab aapko Raja Babu bolte h. Agr Raja Babu bolte h to aap iss title ke hakdar bhi h, reason: your likeable and pleasant personality. I aspire to have a great personality like you. You treat everyone with respect. You are the glue which holds the group together. You think of others before yourself. You are a keen observer. You exert warm aura of hospitality. On one hand, you have the elderly side of sorting out others differences, on the other hand you possess playful side as well. I have never seen you furious for yourself. If others wrong themselves, I have seen your caring side. I wonder how much patience you have. There is a threshold for caring others. But your care has no bounds. Coming into your room, I have never seen you indulging in your work rather than welcoming others. You are introspecting yourself every day. Your time utilizing skills are commendable. Revisiting your whole schedule of day in mind, and then assessing what changes can be made to optimise time further. You are empathetic. You are sincere to your feelings. Your learning agility, optimism and zeal to contribute for the betterment of the society are beyond praise. You have the quality of leader as well as traits of a good team member. You aspire to be IAS in near future. I am just gonna say that buddy go for it, you have my best wishes. You have what it takes to crack the exam and bear the responsibilities. You are a man of golden heart. You cherish your every single friend. Photography, calligraphy, reading books, writing your thoughts and noting down the impressive phrases are some of your hobbies. My yearbook dp was also clicked by you and it came out amazing thanks to your photography skills. Photography ki bat chl rhi h to Saini ko kese bhool skte h, apne group m to tum dono roomies hi shandaar photographer ho. 
In the last 1.5 months, I get to know you more closely. We played dumb charades and cards, watched movies, sang karaoke in last few months and everything is memorable. Mama-mio to air strip we covered many things and made our last campus memories. Photo-session to last feast at campus, pretty much everything emerged from your mind and could have happened because of your perseverance. From meeting Piyush to getting to know Raja Babu, I have learnt a lot of things from you. From being outlier to assimilating with everyone, you have supported and motivated me. Our friendship is invaluable as well as irreplaceable. I am blessed to have you as friendğŸ’•. Bas sachche pyaar milne wala scene nhi ho paya, pr wo bhi mil jayega bhai, aakhirkar achchi cheezen milne m waqt lagta h. 
I am certain that you will soar higher and achieve new heights. Good luck and best wishes for your future journey. Aur haan, jo plans bnaye h job krne ke time ke, wo bhi poori ho jayenge, bas thoda sa aur patient rho y waqt favourable nhi h. Bas waqt ki ek khasiyaat h ki y nikal jaata h. Corona kaal bhi nikal jayega. And then you would have plenty of time to accomplish everything you planned. 
I am not letting you go and you are not the one who forgets friends as time passes by. So, we would be in touchğŸ˜œ. Hoping to meet you soonğŸ¤—. Last m yhi kahunga ki bahut nek dil insaan ho tum â¤.

text:

Aur jab Masti mode activate hota tha to kbhi academic area m ghoomna hota tha to kbhi DOAA canteen m chai. Z-square bas isliye jaana ki mujhe shopping krni h, tum hmesha taiyaar rehte the. Aur apni theatre wali movies, pta nhi kon panauti h apne m se pr apn movies m hmesha late ho jate the. You were always there for me in my failure as well as my little successes â¤. Apne kaam ko lekr to kafi dedicated and hardworking ho aap. Aesi thodi har kisi ko aage se prof bolta h - â€œTumhe kaha jana h Btech ke bad, btao, m doonga recommendationâ€.

text:
Hello Raman!!
Log pyaar se Lamba bulate h aapko. Same coaching institute tha apna. Pr IITK m aakr hi mulaqaat huyi pehli bar. Pehle bhai bne aur phir sath m SG bhi bne. Poori wing m bas tum hi the mere dept se. Apni dosti dept ke courses jab sath krne lage tab jyada gehri huyi. Stata pe regression chlana, Somesh ka research paper likhna aur ab murli ke liye paper likhna, sab sath m kiya. Kitne ghatiya ghatiya course kiye apn ne sath me. Logon ki himmat nhi hoti aese courses lene ki. But apn ne liye aese courses. Some examples are: MOS, Numerical methods, Game Theory and finally IME. Last one was unpredictable. We didnâ€™t know that there is an ounce of possibility that this course could be this labour intensive (eco se h to eco ki analogy to use kreğŸ˜œ) and shitty. You are the best teammate that I met at IITK. There were groups in many courses. But, courses in which we were a group didnâ€™t feel difficult despite being cumbersome. Somehow, we knew how to finish the work.  We just divided our work and there were no differences whatsoever among us regarding work. Through you, I get to know many of our dept mates.
One of the best qualities you possess is hard work.  You genuinely put efforts to achieve your goal. Placement se pehle bahut chinta thi ki pta nhi kesa hoga, kaha hoga. But you never lost faith in yourself and emerged as a better version of yourself. Aur bhai ne phir ne OYO m placement lagwayiğŸ˜€.
I highly appreciate your passion for sports, anime, movie and TV-series. You manage your time efficiently. You know exactly how much time to spend on study and how much on sports and anime ğŸ˜œ. Tv-series, movies ki recommendation leni ho ya Anime ki gup-shup, you are my go-to person. Agr kisi ko mere alawa saaf room rkhte huye dekha h to wo tum ho. You cleaning skills are far more superior than mine. Buddy, you have grown a lot. From taking chill courses to struggling with difficult courses and acing them. Tumhari padhne ki speed to lazawaab h âš¡âš¡, bhai itna jldi koi kese padh skta h ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚. You are a little shy with the girls. Pr bhai nervous hone ki jagah, confidence se bolo jo bolna h. I am giving you this advice because I know tum kbhi kisi ko disrespecting aur hurt krne wale shabd nhi bologe. 
As this is our memoir, so I wanna confess something. I was hesitant to tell anyone about my crush and the reason was that our crush is the same person ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚. Maybe it was childish not to tell anyone, but yeah it happened ğŸ˜‚.
Almost sare sports khel liye tumne. Cricket, volleyball, basketball se lekr badminton tak. Cricket as a CPA to captaincy of volleyball, you evolved. Yaad h tumhe tum Dual bas isliye krna chahte the taki ek aur Inter-IIT khel pao aur apni team ko jeeta kr le aao. Your intense enthusiasm for sports is praiseworthy. 
You genuinely care for your friends. They are like haemoglobin of you blood. Our friendship canâ€™t be described in words. We have great synergy together and we are a team always â¤. You have helped me throughout my whole IITK journey. Whether it is acads problem or my regular strugglesğŸ˜…, you always motivated me and said â€œChill hai, sab badhiya hoga, chinta mat kr, sath m dekh lenge apnâ€. Enthu ki koi kami nhi h tumme. Semester start hone se lekr grades ka result aane tum dussa la rhe hote hoğŸ˜. Buddy, keep this positive attitude with you always and never lose your simplicity.
You have entered a new phase of your life. Good luck for your future endeavours. Apn to pass m hi rehte h to milter rhenge. Love you brother ğŸ’–.
P.S.: Agr lamba so rha h to koi bhool kr bhi shor mt krna wrna anzaam achcha nhi hogağŸ˜‚, lamba ko neend bahut pyari hğŸ˜´ğŸ˜´.

text:
Hey dear roomie !! 
You are the first Y17 I met in campus. From bhai to roomie to more than a real brother, this was our journey in short. When I came back to campus in 2nd semester, I vividly remember you saying this to one of our batchmates in Hall 2 canteen â€“ â€œBhai abhi abhi aaya h Vipin, thoda time do isko, go easy on him, isko draoo mt wapas thodi bhejna hâ€. It was not that our batchmate was intimidating me, but you understood the gravity of situation I was in and you were protecting me. That was your usual self. You would have done the same thing if anyone else were in my shoes. But Your kind gesture led be to believe that I am not alone. There are people rooting for me to recover and emerge stronger.
You see the best in everything. I am not saying that you donâ€™t see the downfalls. Yes, you can see the both sides of the coin but you donâ€™t ever let negative side dominate the positive side. You have an aura of warm hospitality. Anyone can seek guidance from you on any matter. I have learnt a lot of things from you. Being happy and calm despite difficulties tops this list. You were my home away from home. Thanks to you, I always feels that I have someone who would listen to me without any prejudices whatsoever. You are like a mentor, brother, friend everything wrapped in one.
Choosing you as my roommate was my best decision ever. If I can go back in time, then I would also do the same. From leaving IITK to not been able to leave IITK, I have evolved. I think I couldnâ€™t have gotten my confidence back without your constant support. You always had my back. You never let me face difficulties alone. You motivated whenever I was down. You corrected me whenever I made mistakes. 
You are multidimensional. Who would have thought that sudden senator nomination could lead to the 3rd most vote counts. You are people person. Public speaking is your territory. I have never seen anyone so confident in getting A in HSSğŸ˜‚. You have vast knowledge in almost everything. You are hardworking. You can do anything if you decide to put your mind to it. From cracking into GS interview in intern drive to securing job at Blackrock, everyone has witnessed your hard work.
From learning French at IITK to learning Sanskrit at Mattur (Karnataka) in future, you have diverse array of interests. Cracking UPSC, opening NGO, donating for social cause, working as a social activist these are some things on your bucket list. You have zeal to try new things. OnePlus tagline â€œNever Settleâ€ can be said as epitome of your life motto. I am lucky to have an amazing person like you by my side. Love you brother ğŸ¥°â¤. I would definitely miss the random talks we used to have for hours lying in bed for hours. I donâ€™t think I have to say it, but for the sake of memoir I am going to say it â€“ we are not parting ever. Our bond is not that weak to be broken by passage of time.
You are off to a new journey of your life. Best of luck for your future endeavors and keep spreading positivity. Your smile is contagious, it need needs no reason, keep brightening the world with it.
Itna bda likh diya mene ğŸ˜‚. Roomie ka asar to aayega hi ğŸ˜œ.

text:
Hi Onbin,
  Yaar hum first year se jaante heh and kitne saare funny incidents heh humare. I'm sorry for not checking your treasure hunt request mail till second year XD. Our first interaction was that random DE dance compliment during mid sem and after that, we tried to solve a MTH102 problem the next day ( jo hua nahi tha humse :p). Uske baad toh bas TA202 and all the CHE classes. Pata hi nahi chala kab hum general friends se Super sober brozz to gold, silver, bronze bros to super attractive brozz bangaye. Thanks to you guys, I learnt some weird words Yonsh, smoll, nach-nandini and aarti wali birthday celebration. I miss all 4 of us going on treats and sitting together in classes. I guess I wouldn't have survived midsem/endsem night outs in the library or NCL without having some fun time with you and Nandini. Ohh! also you are my ISPP, but unfortunately, woh sem kabhi aaya hi nahi :'(.   Sound wave wala action kaise bhool sakte, yeh toh bas humhe hi pata chalta tha pure class meh. Also those Bhojpuri song suggestions XD.
   I had a perfect time in CHE because of you guys. Not just in courses but in general, I learnt to have fun in the simplest stuff possible. You are my silver brozz forever! (of course I'm gold and Nandini ko bronze banadenge :p) Aaj Kal toh hum teeno ke old photos meh bhi mujhe aise lagraha jaise meh third weeling karrahi lol.

text:
Hi Esha,
You are the perfect roommate. I have been in the hostel from my 9th standard, and you are the best roommate I have ever made. I am so sorry for the alarm sound ( scooby doo pa pa.. even I hate it now). My first impression of you was she would be super smart, cute and very cheerful, which you really are. I wish we could get one more EDM night to go dance like crazy. Thanks for being there when I was feeling emotionally low in my second year :). I loved when aunty brought those different eatables which she prepared in our room. Please send me the recipe, that flavour is still in memory. Other than studious Esha, which most of the others know, I am glad I got to know Esha, who loves dancing during EDMs and treats, does Zumba, chit-chats, gossips, and is very fun-loving. Of course, never start a year watching Vivah; we know it's going to be a disaster. 

  We will be in touch, love you a lot and all the very best <3

Hi Bro,
I had a great time in my first Sem because of you and Neha. I loved my IITK wali family thing. I admire your flexible personality, energy to try everything, and you mingle with everyone. Even though our interest and friend circle was so different, I'm glad we could bond well. Even I remember the first time we went to Z square and also that mandatory IITK entrance photo.  Thanks for all your bits of advice during winter in my first year. Yaar humne toh DE bhi kiya heh saatme, but treat wale random dance are definitely more fun. While writing this memoir, I remembered the last meeting we had at the campus, in front of GH mess. Let's hope to meet again! All the very best <3.

text:
Hi Chinese don, pinky puchki and what not,
Bro, I miss you already. I don't remember how we first met, but I guess this Navodaya thing was common, and we started talking. Thank you guys for introducing me to K-world; I have got so many new crush XD. I love that we could take time to watch " The bold type" and gossip a lot about the relatable stuff. I would never forget your subtle badass expressions and teasing eyes ( even in the airport XD). But I definitely missed you, me and Manisha hanging out together and chit-chatting about literally everything. Thanks for the slightest but unforgettable memories and constantly motivating me to have lunch and dinner.  ( Next birthday ke liye saunf hi gift milega :p). Don't forget to reach out to your personal skin care assistant whenever you want. Hope to meet you soon! and love you a lot puchki.
       Please behen ki shaadi lockdown meh mat hone dena, I badly want to visit Assam LOL. Yaar, yeh Manisha ne kuch zyaada hi likdiya lagraha heh but see most of it is about K-Pop, bas words zyaada use kiye heh usne, toh mera memoir compare mat karna usse :p
author: Yashika

text:
Hi Nach-Nandini,
  Yaar, thank you so much for waking me up for classes every time, even if you didn't attend the class XD. jaldi utke bhi iconic late entry duo hum hi heh I guess. I dont know when we became this close but it was like accha, CHE meh bas iske saat vibe match karega :p. Ab toh professors ko bhi pata chalgaya heh ki yeh dono saatme hi dikhenge ya satme hi project ya course lete heh.  Thanks for making my IITK stay so much memorable from amazing treats, sitting together in the class, daydreaming or dozing in the class, having weird conversations, teasing each other in library or NCL, helping in coursework and assignments and what not! I don't think I have any memory associated with CHE without you. Even the pandemic couldn't keep us away :p; we had a good number of video calls and texts.
   How can I not mention that chit that we dropped to your neighbour - this is one of the fun things I have done at IITK :p. I wish hum ek do baar aur treats and voh aarti wale birthday celebrate karte. Thanks to you and Onbin for making me find happiness and fun in the slightest thing like those strange Bhojpuri songs and twisted words. (Yonsh, gold, silver, bronze brozz, onbin, themks, smoll and funny stickers). Random photos that we three clicked in your room aren't just photos, but they have lots of emotions now. I hope we get to meet soon, and yes! Our old photos give me third wheeling feels aaj kal :p. You hold a very special place in my journey, and of course, we will keep in touch. Thank you so much for everything.
author: Yashika

text: Love you so so much!!!!!!!! ( This love is prominent than romantic ones XD)

text:
Hi Utsav Akarshan/ Festival attraction ?
            
           Thanks for being such a fantastic person. I can't imagine how I would have survived CHE without you guys. I'll cherish every moment with you, may it be a weird birthday song, long emotional conversations, introspection on what we have become, what could be done better, scolding you for some stuff ;p, treats, funny photos, encouraging each other to do well, exam/ assignments, hectic labs...uff and what not!

I know there is a lot hidden behind this happy face of yours, and it was my pleasure knowing you so personally. You are emotionally and mentally very strong, but don't forget I'll always be there for you when you need something.

 Miss you and Take care. I hope we will meet soon. Until then, adios!

text:
One of the toughest memoirs I'd have to write will be for my brother.

One of the best wing repi, any wing could ever get. Pure wing ka common link tha Nareda. Koi bhi dikkat ho, ya kuch bhi bakchodi krni ho Nareda ke paas jane ka mann krta tha. Humari wing ka Ambani bnne ke liye Thanks, Tu na hota toh kitne get-togethers shayad ho hi nhi pati. Isliye itna bura bhi laga tha mujhe jab tu jaldi nikal gya. 2 din tak toh mai room se nikla bhi nhi :(:(. Ek advice agar mai dena chahun toh woh yhi hogi ki khud ko kisi bhi friendship/relationship mein itna mat invest krna ki saamne wala reciprocate hi na kar paye. (Baki Mario wala gift abhi bhi pending hai ğŸ˜›ğŸ˜›!)

Jaldi se UPSC nikal lena mere aspirant par Abhilash ki tarah mujhe bhul mat jana. Thank you for being such a pleasant part of my life at IITK. One that I'll always cherish and dher saara Good luck aage ke liye bhi.ğŸ˜‡ğŸ˜‡

Ab kuch lines mere favourite gaane se-:

It's been a long day without you, my friend

text:
Hi Somu! Most of this post would be a big Thank you from me to you, so pehle hi heads up! Sach kahun toh during the initial phase of my college I had no idea how I would survive here. First sem toh bura gya hi tha and second sem mein bhi kuch smjh nhi aa rha tha. Uss samay mera inspiration to tha! jitna shiddat se tu TA ka kaam krta tha and jitne dedication se tu padhta tha, it made me realise that If I wanted to achieve something, I'll have to work hard for it! But what was even more admirable was the way you always stuck by your principles right until the end. Final kuch samay ke liye bhi tu college nhi aaya, iske liye dher sari gaaliyan dene ka mann toh kiya; but thoda sa dil main relief bhi tha kyunki chaar saal baad bhi Somu remained the Somu we all knew and loved. 

Iss baar maaf toh krdiya hai but next time koi excuses nhi challenge :P . Bade officer ban jao fir ek mast trip pe challenge! Tab take ke liye dher sara Good Luck! And Thank you for always being an ever dependable friend and such an amazing human being. Lots of love to you, keep in touch :)

text:
Pandeyji ko pranam! _/\_
Sir aapse bada inspiration toh IITK Y17 me koi hoga hi nahi. Aapki jitni tareef kare kum hai. Aapka all round knowledge aur intellect IITK ke itihaas aur hamaze zehen me hamesha zinda rahega. Thoda dukh hua tha sunke aapke Civil Service ki ichchha chod di hai, umeed karte hain ki ye aag kahin fir se jage aur aap desh ko bhi apne jaisi unnati dein!
Jis tarah 4 saal aapne humpe kripa banayi hai waise hi aage banaye rakhen. Samay samay aapko hum yaad kar liya karenge, darshan aur gyaan avashya de dijiyega. Iske liye aapka abhi se aabhar!
Bhavadiya,
Kothari
author: Yugesh Ajit Kothari

text:
Gulati yaar tumhara wo Antaragni wala plan successful ho jaata na IITK life hi sidhdhh ho jaati :P
Hummne kaafi saara samay sath me nikala hai RM me, aur kaafi maza aaya hai tumse baaten karke both in and outside pclub. At one point RM toh hamara permanent home bann hi gaya tha. RM me raat ko AC chalu karna, KD wala wo room aur Blackbox ke samay ka wo pizza sab bohot hi fun tha. Some of the best philosophical conversations I have had have been with you. Kuch cheezen karni thi jo reh gayi, kabhi Amsterdam ya California me koi plan banate hain. Also Maine zyada tareef kari nahi tumhari but you know I know you are exteremly intelligent :P
Touch me rehna :)
author: Yugesh Ajit Kothari

text:
Jai Shiv Shambhu!
Mishraji aapko yaad hai kya hamare paas ke Jharkhand Union ka slack hai? Ab college khatam ho gaya hai toh uspe thoda active hote hain wapas kya kehte hain?
Baaki Mishraji aapke sath toh kaafi mazze kiye hain, shivji ki bhakti jo sikhayi hai aapko yaad rakhiyega aur naye mantra seekhne ke liye milte hain kahbi, koi trip plan karke. CP, Antaragni, CSE, aur aapka dhep apping xD humne 4 saalon me kaafi kuch kiya hai sath me, lekin thoda aur kar zarur sakte the.
Aapko shayad yaad na ho 3rd sem me NCL ke terrace pe aap aur mai galti se mil gaye the aur ek bohot motivating converstaion hua tha apne beech uske liye thanks! :)

Baaki apna toh chalta rahega, aur agar aap apna US wala long term plan execute karenge toh mujhe assistant rakh lijiyega please
author: Yugesh Ajit Kothari
